{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883240916,"sessionID":"ses_2851c7184ffeDepVkFukH2kBxM","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae3b701001QdpFIfUkVbmjEk","messageID":"msg_d7ae3a621001r6LSE1IIh8wCUO","sessionID":"ses_2851c7184ffeDepVkFukH2kBxM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_61040dec95534c3ca0ab5858","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-015-proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-015-proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015: PicoD Command Execution API\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This proposal implements the PicoD command execution API for the `pkg/picod` module in the AgentCube project. The goal is to:\n6: \n7: 1. **Secure Command Execution** - Execute commands within controlled sandbox environments with proper isolation\n8: 2. **Resource Limit Enforcement** - Enforce CPU, memory, time, and output size limits on command execution\n9: 3. **Output Capture and Streaming** - Capture stdout/stderr with optional streaming for long-running commands\n10: 4. **Cancellation Support** - Enable command cancellation via context for graceful termination\n11: 5. **Security Hardening** - Implement security validations to prevent privilege escalation and command injection\n12: \n13: This implementation builds upon the sandbox infrastructure established in AR-012 and provides the execution engine for code interpreters and agent runtimes.\n14: \n15: ## Scope\n16: \n17: **Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n18: **Language:** Go  \n19: **Size:** M\n20: \n21: This AR covers:\n22: \n23: - **In scope:**\n24:   - Core `PicoD` struct and initialization (`picod.go`)\n25:   - Command execution logic with resource limits (`executor.go`)\n26:   - Resource limit configuration and enforcement (`limits.go`)\n27:   - Output capture and streaming (`output.go`)\n28:   - Security validations and sandboxing (`security.go`)\n29:   - Unit tests with mocked executors\n30:   - Integration tests with real command execution\n31:   - Configuration via environment variables\n32: \n33: - **Out of scope:**\n34:   - Container runtime integration (covered in AR-005, AR-009)\n35:   - Network namespace manipulation\n36:   - User namespace management\n37:   - Filesystem isolation beyond chroot/workspace jail\n38:   - Distributed command execution\n39:   - PicoD HTTP daemon (covered in `code-execution/` specs)\n40: \n41: ## Current State Analysis\n42: \n43: ### Existing Sandbox Infrastructure\n44: \n45: The current system has sandbox management infrastructure:\n46: \n47: 1. **Sandbox Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/`):\n48:    - Creates and manages sandbox pods\n49:    - Handles lifecycle (create, update, delete)\n50:    - Supports warm pool for pre-provisioned sandboxes\n51: \n52: 2. **CodeInterpreter CRD** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`):\n53:    - Defines `CodeInterpreterSpec` with image, command, args, env, resources\n54:    - Supports `AuthMode` enum (`picod` or `none`)\n55:    - Default image: `volcanosh/picod:latest`\n56: \n57: 3. **Workload Manager**:\n58:    - Handles `CodeInterpreter` resources\n59:    - Creates underlying sandbox pods\n60:    - Injects `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` when `AuthMode=picod`\n61: \n62: ### Gaps Identified\n63: \n64: 1. **No unified execution API** - Command execution logic is scattered or non-existent\n65: 2. **No resource limit enforcement** - No programmatic way to enforce CPU/memory/time limits\n66: 3. **No output streaming** - Cannot stream output for long-running commands\n67: 4. **No security hardening** - Missing input validation and sandboxing at the API level\n68: 5. **No cancellation support** - Cannot gracefully cancel running commands\n69: \n70: ### PicoD Context\n71: \n72: Per `code-execution/design.md` and `code-execution/spec.md`:\n73: - PicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail\n74: - Exposes health endpoint with JWT (RSA)-protected APIs\n75: - CLI flags: `-port` (default 8080), `-workspace` (default: current working directory)\n76: - Server uses `ReadHeaderTimeout` of 10 seconds\n77: \n78: ## Proposed Changes\n79: \n80: ### 1. Core PicoD Structure (`picod.go`)\n81: \n82: ```go\n83: // PicoD represents a command execution sandbox\n84: type PicoD struct {\n85:     sandboxID    string\n86:     workDir      string\n87:     limits       *ResourceLimits\n88:     securityOpts *SecurityOptions\n89:     logger       klog.Logger\n90: }\n91: \n92: // Option is a functional option for PicoD\n93: type Option func(*PicoD)\n94: \n95: // New creates a new PicoD instance\n96: func New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) *PicoD\n97: \n98: // WithWorkDir sets the working directory\n99: func WithWorkDir(dir string) Option\n100: \n101: // WithLimits sets resource limits\n102: func WithLimits(limits *ResourceLimits) Option\n103: \n104: // WithSecurityOpts sets security options\n105: func WithSecurityOpts(opts *SecurityOptions) Option\n106: \n107: // WithLogger sets the logger\n108: func WithLogger(logger klog.Logger) Option\n109: ```\n110: \n111: ### 2. Resource Limits (`limits.go`)\n112: \n113: ```go\n114: // ResourceLimits defines execution resource limits\n115: type ResourceLimits struct {\n116:     // Timeout is the maximum execution duration\n117:     Timeout time.Duration\n118:     \n119:     // MaxCPU is the maximum CPU cores (e.g., 0.5, 1.0)\n120:     MaxCPU float64\n121:     \n122:     // MaxMemory is the maximum memory in bytes\n123:     MaxMemory int64\n124:     \n125:     // MaxOutputSize is the maximum output size in bytes\n126:     MaxOutputSize int64\n127:     \n128:     // MaxProcesses is the maximum number of processes\n129:     MaxProcesses int\n130: }\n131: \n132: // DefaultResourceLimits returns default resource limits\n133: func DefaultResourceLimits() *ResourceLimits\n134: \n135: // Validate validates resource limits\n136: func (l *ResourceLimits) Validate() error\n137: ```\n138: \n139: ### 3. Security Options (`security.go`)\n140: \n141: ```go\n142: // SecurityOptions defines security settings for command execution\n143: type SecurityOptions struct {\n144:     // UID is the user ID to run commands as\n145:     UID int\n146:     \n147:     // GID is the group ID to run commands as\n148:     GID int\n149:     \n150:     // Capabilities is the list of allowed capabilities\n151:     Capabilities []string\n152:     \n153:     // ReadOnlyFS makes the filesystem read-only\n154:     ReadOnlyFS bool\n155:     \n156:     // NoNetwork disables network access\n157:     NoNetwork bool\n158:     \n159:     // AllowedCommands is an optional allowlist of command paths\n160:     AllowedCommands []string\n161: }\n162: \n163: // DefaultSecurityOpts returns default security options\n164: func DefaultSecurityOpts() *SecurityOptions\n165: \n166: // Validate validates security options\n167: func (o *SecurityOptions) Validate() error\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ### 4. Command Execution API (`executor.go`)\n171: \n172: ```go\n173: // Command represents a command to execute\n174: type Command struct {\n175:     // Path is the command path\n176:     Path string\n177:     \n178:     // Args are the command arguments\n179:     Args []string\n180:     \n181:     // Env is the environment variables\n182:     Env []string\n183:     \n184:     // Dir is the working directory\n185:     Dir string\n186:     \n187:     // Stdin is the standard input\n188:     Stdin io.Reader\n189:     \n190:     // Stdout is the standard output (optional, captured if nil)\n191:     Stdout io.Writer\n192:     \n193:     // Stderr is the standard error (optional, captured if nil)\n194:     Stderr io.Writer\n195: }\n196: \n197: // CommandResult represents the result of command execution\n198: type CommandResult struct {\n199:     // ExitCode is the process exit code\n200:     ExitCode int\n201:     \n202:     // Stdout is the captured standard output\n203:     Stdout []byte\n204:     \n205:     // Stderr is the captured standard error\n206:     Stderr []byte\n207:     \n208:     // Duration is the execution duration\n209:     Duration time.Duration\n210:     \n211:     // OOMKilled indicates if the process was killed due to OOM\n212:     OOMKilled bool\n213:     \n214:     // Timeout indicates if the command timed out\n215:     Timeout bool\n216: }\n217: \n218: // Run executes a command and waits for completion\n219: func (p *PicoD) Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error)\n220: \n221: // Start starts a command without waiting\n222: func (p *PicoD) Start(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*Process, error)\n223: \n224: // Process represents a running process\n225: type Process struct {\n226:     // PID is the process ID\n227:     PID int\n228:     \n229:     // Wait waits for the process to complete\n230:     Wait() (*CommandResult, error)\n231:     \n232:     // Kill sends a signal to the process\n233:     Kill(signal os.Signal) error\n234: }\n235: ```\n236: \n237: ### 5. Output Streaming (`output.go`)\n238: \n239: ```go\n240: // OutputHandler handles streaming output\n241: type OutputHandler interface {\n242:     // OnStdout is called when stdout data is available\n243:     OnStdout(data []byte)\n244:     \n245:     // OnStderr is called when stderr data is available\n246:     OnStderr(data []byte)\n247:     \n248:     // OnComplete is called when execution completes\n249:     OnComplete(result *CommandResult)\n250: }\n251: \n252: // RunWithStreaming executes a command with streaming output\n253: func (p *PicoD) RunWithStreaming(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command, handler OutputHandler) (*CommandResult, error)\n254: ```\n255: \n256: ### 6. Security Validation (`security.go`)\n257: \n258: ```go\n259: // ValidateCommand validates a command for security\n260: func ValidateCommand(cmd *Command, opts *SecurityOptions) error\n261: \n262: // IsPathSafe checks if a path is within the allowed workspace\n263: func IsPathSafe(path, workDir string) bool\n264: \n265: // DropPrivileges drops privileges to the specified UID/GID\n266: func DropPrivileges(uid, gid int) error\n267: \n268: // SetResourceLimits applies resource limits to the current process\n269: func SetResourceLimits(limits *ResourceLimits) error\n270: ```\n271: \n272: ### 7. Configuration\n273: \n274: #### Environment Variables\n275: \n276: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n277: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n278: | `PICOD_WORKDIR` | No | `/tmp/picod` | Base working directory |\n279: | `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | No | `30s` | Default command timeout |\n280: | `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY` | No | `128Mi` | Default memory limit |\n281: | `PICOD_MAX_CPU` | No | `1.0` | Default CPU limit |\n282: | `PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE` | No | `10MB` | Default output size limit |\n283: | `PICOD_MAX_PROCESSES` | No | `10` | Default process limit |\n284: \n285: ### 8. Error Handling\n286: \n287: ```go\n288: // ExecutionError represents an execution error\n289: type ExecutionError struct {\n290:     // Type is the error type\n291:     Type ExecutionErrorType\n292:     \n293:     // Message is the error message\n294:     Message string\n295:     \n296:     // Underlying is the underlying error\n297:     Underlying error\n298: }\n299: \n300: type ExecutionErrorType string\n301: \n302: const (\n303:     ExecutionErrorTimeout    ExecutionErrorType = \"timeout\"\n304:     ExecutionErrorOOM        ExecutionErrorType = \"oom\"\n305:     ExecutionErrorCancelled  ExecutionErrorType = \"cancelled\"\n306:     ExecutionErrorSecurity   ExecutionErrorType = \"security\"\n307:     ExecutionErrorResource   ExecutionErrorType = \"resource\"\n308:     ExecutionErrorExec       ExecutionErrorType = \"exec\"\n309: )\n310: ```\n311: \n312: ## Impact Analysis\n313: \n314: ### Dependencies\n315: \n316: | Package | Purpose |\n317: |---------|---------|\n318: | `context` | Command cancellation and timeouts |\n319: | `os/exec` | Command execution primitives |\n320: | `syscall` | Process management and signals |\n321: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n322: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo type definitions |\n323: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | Type definitions |\n324: \n325: ### Affected Components\n326: \n327: 1. **Sandbox Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/`): Will use PicoD for command execution within sandboxes\n328: 2. **Workload Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/`): Will invoke PicoD APIs for job execution\n329: 3. **Code Interpreter** (standalone daemon): Will use PicoD execution logic\n330: 4. **Security Module**: Will configure security policies for command execution\n331: 5. **Monitoring System**: Will collect metrics from command execution\n332: \n333: ### Backward Compatibility\n334: \n335: - This is a new module with no existing API surface\n336: - No breaking changes to existing components\n337: - Configuration via environment variables and programmatic API\n338: - Existing `CodeInterpreter` CRD already references PicoD image\n339: \n340: ### Risk Assessment\n341: \n342: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n343: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n344: | Command injection | Low | High | Input validation, allowlist-based command selection |\n345: | Resource exhaustion | Medium | High | Enforce strict CPU/memory/time limits |\n346: | Privilege escalation | Low | Critical | Run as non-root, drop capabilities, use namespaces |\n347: | Output buffer overflow | Low | Medium | Stream large outputs, enforce size limits |\n348: | Zombie processes | Medium | Low | Proper process reaping, signal handling |\n349: \n350: ## Alternatives Considered\n351: \n352: ### Alternative 1: Use Existing Library (e.g., go-execute, bazel-remote)\n353: \n354: **Approach**: Leverage existing command execution libraries\n355: \n356: **Pros**:\n357: - Less code to maintain\n358: - Battle-tested implementations\n359: - Community support\n360: \n361: **Cons**:\n362: - May not meet specific security requirements for sandboxed execution\n363: - Additional dependency management overhead\n364: - Less control over resource limit enforcement\n365: - May not support Kubernetes-native patterns\n366: \n367: **Decision**: Implement custom solution for full control over security and limits, and better integration with AgentCube architecture.\n368: \n369: ### Alternative 2: Shell-based Execution\n370: \n371: **Approach**: Execute commands via `/bin/sh -c`\n372: \n373: **Pros**:\n374: - Simple implementation\n375: - Shell features (pipes, redirection) available\n376: - Familiar syntax\n377: \n378: **Cons**:\n379: - Security risks (shell injection attacks)\n380: - Harder to control resource limits accurately\n381: - Additional attack surface\n382: - Non-deterministic behavior across shells\n383: \n384: **Decision**: Use direct execve-style execution for better security and control.\n385: \n386: ### Alternative 3: Container-based Execution\n387: \n388: **Approach**: Spawn a new container for each command\n389: \n390: **Pros**:\n391: - Strong isolation\n392: - Built-in resource limits via cgroups\n393: - Clean environment per command\n394: \n395: **Cons**:\n396: - High overhead (container startup latency)\n397: - Requires container runtime access\n398: - Complex orchestration\n399: - Overkill for simple command execution\n400: \n401: **Decision**: Use process-level isolation with proper limits for lower latency; container isolation is handled at the sandbox pod level (AR-005).\n402: \n403: ## Testing Strategy\n404: \n405: ### Unit Tests\n406: \n407: 1. **TestPicoD_Run_Success**: Basic command execution\n408: 2. **TestPicoD_Run_Timeout**: Command exceeds timeout\n409: 3. **TestPicoD_Run_OOM**: Command exceeds memory limit\n410: 4. **TestPicoD_Run_Cancelled**: Context cancellation\n411: 5. **TestPicoD_OutputCapture**: Stdout/stderr capture\n412: 6. **TestPicoD_SecurityValidation**: Invalid commands rejected\n413: 7. **TestPicoD_ResourceLimits_Validate**: Resource limit validation\n414: 8. **TestPicoD_SecurityOpts_Validate**: Security options validation\n415: 9. **TestPicoD_WithOptions**: Functional options pattern\n416: 10. **TestPicoD_ExecutionErrorTypes**: Error type classification\n417: \n418: ### Integration Tests\n419: \n420: 1. **TestPicoD_Integration_FullLifecycle**: Full execution flow\n421: 2. **TestPicoD_Integration_Concurrent**: Multiple concurrent commands\n422: 3. **TestPicoD_Integration_ResourceLimits**: Verify limits are enforced\n423: 4. **TestPicoD_Integration_Streaming**: Output streaming functionality\n424: 5. **TestPicoD_Integration_SignalHandling**: Process signal handling\n425: \n426: ## Acceptance Criteria\n427: \n428: - [ ] `PicoD` struct implements all required methods\n429: - [ ] Resource limits are enforced (timeout, CPU, memory, output size)\n430: - [ ] Output capture works correctly (stdout, stderr, exit code)\n431: - [ ] Cancellation via context is supported\n432: - [ ] Security validations prevent dangerous operations\n433: - [ ] Streaming output is supported\n434: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n435: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n436: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n437: - [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n438: - [ ] Error types are properly classified and documented\n439: \n440: ## References\n441: \n442: - Sandbox Infrastructure: `changes/AR-012/proposal.md`\n443: - Session Storage: `changes/AR-013/proposal.md`\n444: - Valkey Storage: `changes/AR-014/proposal.md`\n445: - PicoD Spec: `code-execution/spec.md`\n446: - PicoD Design: `code-execution/design.md`\n447: - Client-Go: `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n(End of file - total 447 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015: PicoD Command Execution API\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements the PicoD command execution API for the `pkg/picod` module in the AgentCube project. The goal is to:\n\n1. **Secure Command Execution** - Execute commands within controlled sandbox environments with proper isolation\n2. **Resource Limit Enforcement** - Enforce CPU, memory, time, and output size limits on command execution\n3. **Output Capture and Streaming** - Capture stdout/stderr with optional streaming for long-running commands\n4. **Cancellation Support** - Enable command cancellation via context for graceful termination\n5. **Security Hardening** - Implement security validations to prevent privilege escalation and command injection\n\nThis implementation builds upon the sandbox infrastructure established in AR-012 and provides the execution engine for code interpreters and agent runtimes.\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-015-proposal.md","time":{"start":1775883240881,"end":1775883240914}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883240919,"sessionID":"ses_2851c7184ffeDepVkFukH2kBxM","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae3bc12001CYpUnLRJ2aIP9z","messageID":"msg_d7ae3a621001r6LSE1IIh8wCUO","sessionID":"ses_2851c7184ffeDepVkFukH2kBxM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_4196f3b5758248bebf38b665","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-017-proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-017-proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017: PicoD JWT Middleware\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This proposal implements JWT (JSON Web Token) authentication middleware for the PicoD HTTP daemon in the `pkg/picod` module. The goal is to:\n6: \n7: 1. **Secure API Access** - Protect PicoD HTTP endpoints with RSA-based JWT authentication\n8: 2. **Token Validation** - Validate JWT tokens signed with RSA private keys using the corresponding public key\n9: 3. **Request Authorization** - Intercept and authenticate incoming HTTP requests before allowing access to command execution APIs\n10: 4. **Flexible Configuration** - Support configuration via environment variables and command-line flags\n11: 5. **Health Endpoint Protection** - Optionally protect the health check endpoint with JWT authentication\n12: \n13: This implementation builds upon the PicoD execution infrastructure established in AR-015 and provides the security layer required for multi-tenant code interpreter deployments.\n14: \n15: ## Scope\n16: \n17: **Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n18: **Language:** Go  \n19: **Size:** S\n20: \n21: This AR covers:\n22: \n23: - **In scope:**\n24:   - JWT middleware implementation (`middleware.go`)\n25:   - JWT token validation logic (`jwt.go`)\n26:   - RSA key handling utilities (`crypto.go`)\n27:   - Configuration via environment variables and flags\n28:   - Unit tests with mocked tokens and keys\n29:   - Integration tests with real HTTP server\n30:   - Error handling and logging\n31: \n32: - **Out of scope:**\n33:   - JWT token generation (handled by external auth service)\n34:   - Token refresh mechanisms\n35:   - User/role-based authorization (only authentication)\n36:   - OAuth2 or other authentication protocols\n37:   - Session management (covered in AR-013)\n38:   - PicoD HTTP server implementation (covered in `code-execution/` specs)\n39: \n40: ## Current State Analysis\n41: \n42: ### Existing PicoD Infrastructure\n43: \n44: The current PicoD system has command execution infrastructure:\n45: \n46: 1. **PicoD Core** (`pkg/picod/picod.go`):\n47:    - Main `PicoD` struct with sandbox ID, work directory, limits, and security options\n48:    - Functional options pattern for configuration\n49:    - Structured logging with klog\n50: \n51: 2. **Command Execution** (`pkg/picod/executor.go`):\n52:    - `Run()` and `Start()` methods for command execution\n53:    - Resource limit enforcement (timeout, CPU, memory, output size)\n54:    - Output capture and streaming\n55: \n56: 3. **Security Module** (`pkg/picod/security.go`):\n57:    - Command validation and path safety checks\n58:    - Privilege dropping and capability management\n59:    - Allowlist-based command selection\n60: \n61: 4. **Configuration** (`pkg/picod/config.go`):\n62:    - Environment variable loading\n63:    - Default values for resource limits\n64: \n65: ### Gaps Identified\n66: \n67: 1. **No HTTP authentication** - PicoD HTTP daemon has no authentication layer\n68: 2. **No JWT validation** - Cannot validate JWT tokens from incoming requests\n69: 3. **No RSA key handling** - Missing utilities for loading and using RSA public keys\n70: 4. **No middleware pattern** - No HTTP middleware for request interception\n71: 5. **Health endpoint exposed** - Health check endpoint is publicly accessible\n72: \n73: ### PicoD HTTP Context\n74: \n75: Per `code-execution/design.md` and `code-execution/spec.md`:\n76: - PicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail\n77: - Exposes health endpoint with JWT (RSA)-protected APIs\n78: - CLI flags: `-port` (default 8080), `-workspace` (default: current working directory)\n79: - Server uses `ReadHeaderTimeout` of 10 seconds\n80: - Authentication modes: `picod` (JWT required) or `none` (no auth)\n81: \n82: ### Kubernetes Client-Go Context\n83: \n84: Per `deployment/client-go.md`:\n85: - Generated Kubernetes client for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n86: - `CodeInterpreter` CRD supports `AuthMode` enum (`picod` or `none`)\n87: - Workload manager injects `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` when `AuthMode=picod`\n88: - Public key provided as base64-encoded PEM string\n89: \n90: ## Proposed Changes\n91: \n92: ### 1. JWT Middleware (`middleware.go`)\n93: \n94: ```go\n95: // JWTMiddleware is HTTP middleware that validates JWT tokens\n96: type JWTMiddleware struct {\n97:     // publicKey is the RSA public key for token validation\n98:     publicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n99:     \n100:     // skipPaths is a list of paths to skip authentication\n101:     skipPaths map[string]bool\n102:     \n103:     // logger is the structured logger\n104:     logger klog.Logger\n105: }\n106: \n107: // NewJWTMiddleware creates a new JWT middleware\n108: func NewJWTMiddleware(publicKey *rsa.PublicKey, skipPaths ...string) *JWTMiddleware\n109: \n110: // Middleware returns the HTTP middleware handler\n111: func (m *JWTMiddleware) Middleware(next http.Handler) http.Handler\n112: \n113: // extractToken extracts the JWT token from the Authorization header\n114: func (m *JWTMiddleware) extractToken(r *http.Request) (string, error)\n115: \n116: // shouldSkip checks if a path should skip authentication\n117: func (m *JWTMiddleware) shouldSkip(path string) bool\n118: ```\n119: \n120: ### 2. JWT Validation (`jwt.go`)\n121: \n122: ```go\n123: // Claims represents JWT token claims\n124: type Claims struct {\n125:     // Subject is the token subject\n126:     Sub string `json:\"sub\"`\n127:     \n128:     // Issuer is the token issuer\n129:     Iss string `json:\"iss\"`\n130:     \n131:     // Audience is the token audience\n132:     Aud string `json:\"aud\"`\n133:     \n134:     // Expiration time\n135:     Exp int64 `json:\"exp\"`\n136:     \n137:     // Issued at\n138:     Iat int64 `json:\"iat\"`\n139:     \n140:     // Custom claims for AgentCube\n141:     SandboxID string `json:\"sandbox_id,omitempty\"`\n142:     Namespace string `json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n143: }\n144: \n145: // Validate validates the JWT claims\n146: func (c *Claims) Validate(now time.Time) error\n147: \n148: // ParseAndValidate parses and validates a JWT token\n149: func ParseAndValidate(tokenString string, publicKey *rsa.PublicKey) (*Claims, error)\n150: \n151: // VerifySignature verifies the JWT signature\n152: func VerifySignature(tokenString string, publicKey *rsa.PublicKey) error\n153: ```\n154: \n155: ### 3. RSA Key Handling (`crypto.go`)\n156: \n157: ```go\n158: // LoadPublicKey loads an RSA public key from PEM-encoded data\n159: func LoadPublicKey(pemData []byte) (*rsa.PublicKey, error)\n160: \n161: // LoadPublicKeyFromBase64 loads an RSA public key from base64-encoded PEM\n162: func LoadPublicKeyFromBase64(base64PEM string) (*rsa.PublicKey, error)\n163: \n164: // ParsePEM parses PEM-encoded data and returns the RSA public key\n165: func ParsePEM(pemBlock *pem.Block) (*rsa.PublicKey, error)\n166: \n167: // GenerateKeyPair generates an RSA key pair for testing\n168: func GenerateKeyPair(bits int) (*rsa.PrivateKey, *rsa.PublicKey, error)\n169: ```\n170: \n171: ### 4. Configuration\n172: \n173: #### Environment Variables\n174: \n175: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n176: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n177: | `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` | Conditional | `` | Base64-encoded PEM RSA public key (required if `-auth=picod`) |\n178: | `PICOD_AUTH_MODE` | No | `none` | Authentication mode (`picod` or `none`) |\n179: | `PICOD_AUTH_SKIP_PATHS` | No | `/health` | Comma-separated list of paths to skip auth |\n180: \n181: #### Command-Line Flags\n182: \n183: ```go\n184: // Add to existing PicoD flag parsing\n185: flag.StringVar(&authMode, \"auth\", \"none\", \"Authentication mode: picod or none\")\n186: flag.StringVar(&publicKeyPEM, \"public-key\", \"\", \"RSA public key (base64-encoded PEM)\")\n187: flag.StringVar(&skipPaths, \"skip-paths\", \"/health\", \"Comma-separated paths to skip auth\")\n188: ```\n189: \n190: ### 5. Error Handling\n191: \n192: ```go\n193: // AuthError represents an authentication error\n194: type AuthError struct {\n195:     // Type is the error type\n196:     Type AuthErrorType\n197:     \n198:     // Message is the error message\n199:     Message string\n200:     \n201:     // Underlying is the underlying error\n202:     Underlying error\n203: }\n204: \n205: type AuthErrorType string\n206: \n207: const (\n208:     AuthErrorMissingToken  AuthErrorType = \"missing_token\"\n209:     AuthErrorInvalidToken  AuthErrorType = \"invalid_token\"\n210:     AuthErrorExpiredToken  AuthErrorType = \"expired_token\"\n211:     AuthErrorInvalidSig    AuthErrorType = \"invalid_signature\"\n212:     AuthErrorInvalidClaims AuthErrorType = \"invalid_claims\"\n213:     AuthErrorInternal      AuthErrorType = \"internal_error\"\n214: )\n215: \n216: // HTTPResponse returns the appropriate HTTP status code\n217: func (e *AuthError) HTTPStatus() int\n218: ```\n219: \n220: ### 6. HTTP Response Helpers\n221: \n222: ```go\n223: // WriteJSON writes a JSON response\n224: func WriteJSON(w http.ResponseWriter, status int, data interface{})\n225: \n226: // WriteError writes an error response\n227: func WriteError(w http.ResponseWriter, err error)\n228: \n229: // HealthResponse represents a health check response\n230: type HealthResponse struct {\n231:     // Status is the health status\n232:     Status string `json:\"status\"`\n233:     \n234:     // Timestamp is the current time\n235:     Timestamp time.Time `json:\"timestamp\"`\n236:     \n237:     // SandboxID is the sandbox identifier\n238:     SandboxID string `json:\"sandbox_id,omitempty\"`\n239: }\n240: ```\n241: \n242: ### 7. Integration with Existing Code\n243: \n244: ```go\n245: // SetupHTTPServer creates the HTTP server with JWT middleware\n246: func SetupHTTPServer(picod *PicoD, config *Config) (*http.Server, error) {\n247:     mux := http.NewServeMux()\n248:     \n249:     // Health endpoint (optionally protected)\n250:     mux.HandleFunc(\"/health\", handleHealth(picod))\n251:     \n252:     // Command execution endpoints (protected)\n253:     mux.HandleFunc(\"/api/v1/execute\", handleExecute(picod))\n254:     mux.HandleFunc(\"/api/v1/execute/stream\", handleExecuteStream(picod))\n255:     \n256:     // Apply JWT middleware\n257:     var handler http.Handler = mux\n258:     if config.AuthMode == \"picod\" {\n259:         publicKey, err := LoadPublicKeyFromBase64(config.PublicKeyPEM)\n260:         if err != nil {\n261:             return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to load public key: %w\", err)\n262:         }\n263:         \n264:         middleware := NewJWTMiddleware(publicKey, config.SkipPaths...)\n265:         handler = middleware.Middleware(mux)\n266:     }\n267:     \n268:     return &http.Server{\n269:         Addr:              fmt.Sprintf(\":%d\", config.Port),\n270:         Handler:           handler,\n271:         ReadHeaderTimeout: 10 * time.Second,\n272:     }, nil\n273: }\n274: ```\n275: \n276: ## Impact Analysis\n277: \n278: ### Dependencies\n279: \n280: | Package | Purpose |\n281: |---------|---------|\n282: | `crypto/rsa` | RSA signature verification |\n283: | `crypto/x509` | X.509 key parsing |\n284: | `encoding/pem` | PEM decoding |\n285: | `encoding/base64` | Base64 decoding |\n286: | `encoding/json` | JSON encoding/decoding |\n287: | `net/http` | HTTP middleware |\n288: | `strings` | String manipulation |\n289: | `time` | Time-based token validation |\n290: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n291: \n292: ### Affected Components\n293: \n294: 1. **PicoD HTTP Server** (`code-execution/`): Will integrate JWT middleware into HTTP server setup\n295: 2. **Workload Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/`): Will configure auth mode and inject public key\n296: 3. **Code Interpreter Controller** (`pkg/controller/`): Will set `AuthMode` on `CodeInterpreter` spec\n297: 4. **Authentication Service** (external): Will generate JWT tokens for clients\n298: 5. **Client Applications**: Will include JWT tokens in `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n299: \n300: ### Backward Compatibility\n301: \n302: - Default auth mode is `none` (no authentication) for backward compatibility\n303: - Existing deployments without `AuthMode=picod` continue to work unchanged\n304: - Public key injection is optional and only required when `AuthMode=picod`\n305: - Health endpoint can be configured to skip authentication\n306: \n307: ### Risk Assessment\n308: \n309: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n310: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n311: | Token forgery | Low | Critical | Use RSA-256/512 signatures, verify with strong crypto |\n312: | Key leakage | Low | Critical | Keys managed by Kubernetes secrets, not in code |\n313: | Token replay | Medium | High | Include `iat` and `exp` claims, use short-lived tokens |\n314: | Clock skew | Medium | Medium | Allow configurable clock skew tolerance (30s) |\n315: | Performance overhead | Low | Low | RSA verification is fast (<1ms per request) |\n316: | DoS via invalid tokens | Medium | Low | Rate limiting, early rejection of malformed tokens |\n317: \n318: ## Alternatives Considered\n319: \n320: ### Alternative 1: Use Existing JWT Library (e.g., golang-jwt/jwt)\n321: \n322: **Approach**: Leverage the popular `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` library\n323: \n324: **Pros**:\n325: - Battle-tested, widely used\n326: - Handles edge cases (clock skew, token parsing)\n327: - Active community support\n328: - Supports multiple signature algorithms\n329: \n330: **Cons**:\n331: - Additional dependency\n332: - May be overkill for simple RSA verification\n333: - Larger binary size\n334: \n335: **Decision**: Use a minimal custom implementation for simplicity and control, but structure code to easily swap in `golang-jwt/jwt` if needed. The custom implementation will follow JWT standards (RFC 7519) for compatibility.\n336: \n337: ### Alternative 2: Kubernetes ServiceAccount Token\n338: \n339: **Approach**: Use Kubernetes native ServiceAccount tokens for authentication\n340: \n341: **Pros**:\n342: - Native Kubernetes integration\n343: - No additional key management\n344: - Automatic token rotation\n345: \n346: **Cons**:\n347: - Requires Kubernetes API access for validation\n348: - Tightly couples PicoD to Kubernetes\n349: - More complex validation logic\n350: - Not suitable for non-Kubernetes deployments\n351: \n352: **Decision**: Use RSA-based JWT for deployment flexibility and simpler validation. PicoD should work both inside and outside Kubernetes.\n353: \n354: ### Alternative 3: mTLS (Mutual TLS)\n355: \n356: **Approach**: Use mutual TLS for client authentication\n357: \n358: **Pros**:\n359: - Strong security (certificate-based)\n360: - Built into Go's `http.Server`\n361: - No custom token handling\n362: \n363: **Cons**:\n364: - Complex certificate management\n365: - Requires CA infrastructure\n366: - Harder to debug\n367: - Less flexible for distributed systems\n368: \n369: **Decision**: Use JWT for simpler token-based authentication. mTLS is better suited for service-to-service communication at the infrastructure level.\n370: \n371: ### Alternative 4: API Key Authentication\n372: \n373: **Approach**: Use simple API keys in headers\n374: \n375: **Pros**:\n376: - Simple implementation\n377: - Easy to debug\n378: - Low overhead\n379: \n380: **Cons**:\n381: - No standard claims structure\n382: - Harder to distribute and rotate\n383: - No built-in expiration\n384: - Less secure (symmetric keys)\n385: \n386: **Decision**: Use JWT with RSA signatures for better security, standard claims, and asymmetric key distribution.\n387: \n388: ## Testing Strategy\n389: \n390: ### Unit Tests\n391: \n392: 1. **TestJWTMiddleware_ValidToken**: Valid JWT token passes through\n393: 2. **TestJWTMiddleware_MissingToken**: Missing token returns 401\n394: 3. **TestJWTMiddleware_InvalidToken**: Malformed token returns 401\n395: 4. **TestJWTMiddleware_ExpiredToken**: Expired token returns 401\n396: 5. **TestJWTMiddleware_SkipPath**: Health endpoint skips auth\n397: 6. **TestParseAndValidate_Success**: Valid token parses claims correctly\n398: 7. **TestParseAndValidate_InvalidSignature**: Tampered token fails verification\n399: 8. **TestClaims_Validate_Expired**: Expired claims fail validation\n400: 9. **TestClaims_Validate_Future**: Not-yet-valid claims fail validation\n401: 10. **TestLoadPublicKeyFromBase64**: Correctly loads base64-encoded PEM key\n402: 11. **TestLoadPublicKey_InvalidPEM**: Invalid PEM returns error\n403: 12. **TestAuthError_HTTPStatus**: Error types map to correct HTTP codes\n404: \n405: ### Integration Tests\n406: \n407: 1. **TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_FullFlow**: Full HTTP request with valid token\n408: 2. **TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_MultipleRequests**: Multiple concurrent requests\n409: 3. **TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_KeyRotation**: Server handles key change (restart)\n410: 4. **TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_HealthEndpoint**: Health endpoint with/without auth\n411: \n412: ### Test Fixtures\n413: \n414: ```go\n415: // generateTestToken creates a signed JWT token for testing\n416: func generateTestToken(privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey, claims *Claims) (string, error)\n417: \n418: // testClaims returns standard test claims\n419: func testClaims() *Claims {\n420:     return &Claims{\n421:         Sub:       \"test-user\",\n422:         Iss:       \"test-issuer\",\n423:         Aud:       \"picod\",\n424:         Exp:       time.Now().Add(1 * time.Hour).Unix(),\n425:         Iat:       time.Now().Unix(),\n426:         SandboxID: \"test-sandbox\",\n427:         Namespace: \"default\",\n428:     }\n429: }\n430: \n431: // generateTestKeyPair creates a test RSA key pair\n432: func generateTestKeyPair() (*rsa.PrivateKey, *rsa.PublicKey, error)\n433: ```\n434: \n435: ## Acceptance Criteria\n436: \n437: - [ ] JWT middleware correctly validates tokens\n438: - [ ] Invalid/missing tokens return 401 Unauthorized\n439: - [ ] Expired tokens are rejected\n440: - [ ] Signature verification works with RSA public key\n441: - [ ] Configurable skip paths work correctly\n442: - [ ] Health endpoint can be protected or public\n443: - [ ] Claims are correctly parsed and validated\n444: - [ ] Error types map to appropriate HTTP status codes\n445: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n446: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n447: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n448: - [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n449: - [ ] Compatible with standard JWT libraries (e.g., PyJWT, jose)\n450: \n451: ## References\n452: \n453: - AR-015: PicoD Command Execution API\n454: - AR-013: Session Storage\n455: - `code-execution/spec.md`: PicoD Specification\n456: - `code-execution/design.md`: PicoD Design\n457: - `deployment/client-go.md`: Kubernetes Client-Go\n458: - `deployment/spec.md`: Deployment Configuration\n459: - RFC 7519: JSON Web Token (JWT)\n460: - RFC 7515: JSON Web Signature (JWS)\n\n(End of file - total 460 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017: PicoD JWT Middleware\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements JWT (JSON Web Token) authentication middleware for the PicoD HTTP daemon in the `pkg/picod` module. The goal is to:\n\n1. **Secure API Access** - Protect PicoD HTTP endpoints with RSA-based JWT authentication\n2. **Token Validation** - Validate JWT tokens signed with RSA private keys using the corresponding public key\n3. **Request Authorization** - Intercept and authenticate incoming HTTP requests before allowing access to command execution APIs\n4. **Flexible Configuration** - Support configuration via environment variables and command-line flags\n5. **Health Endpoint Protection** - Optionally protect the health check endpoint with JWT authentication\n\nThis implementation builds upon the PicoD execution infrastructure established in AR-015 and provides the security layer required for multi-tenant code interpreter deployments.\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-017-proposal.md","time":{"start":1775883240884,"end":1775883240917}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883240923,"sessionID":"ses_2851c7184ffeDepVkFukH2kBxM","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae3c1b50014Xufgn8s0zmSP1","messageID":"msg_d7ae3a621001r6LSE1IIh8wCUO","sessionID":"ses_2851c7184ffeDepVkFukH2kBxM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_0cba9cf49fdf49f7b233639a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-005 Sandbox Creation Processor\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document describes the technical implementation for the Sandbox processor module within `pkg/workloadmanager`. The processor handles creation and lifecycle management of sandbox environments using Kubernetes custom resources.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Component Structure\n10: \n11: ```\n12: pkg/workloadmanager/\n13: ├── processor/\n14: │   ├── sandbox_processor.go      # Main processor implementation\n15: │   ├── sandbox_processor_test.go # Unit tests\n16: │   └── interface.go              # Processor interface definition\n17: ├── types/\n18: │   └── sandbox.go                # Sandbox data structures\n19: └── config/\n20:     └── sandbox_config.go         # Configuration structures\n21: ```\n22: \n23: ### Integration Points\n24: \n25: - **Client-go**: Uses generated typed client for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n26: - **Informers**: Watches `CodeInterpreter` and `AgentRuntime` resources\n27: - **Listers**: Provides cached read access to resources\n28: \n29: ## Data Structures\n30: \n31: ### Sandbox Processor\n32: \n33: ```go\n34: type SandboxProcessor struct {\n35:     client       runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n36:     informer     cache.SharedIndexInformer\n37:     lister       runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterLister\n38:     config       *SandboxConfig\n39:     eventHandler cache.ResourceEventHandlerRegistration\n40: }\n41: \n42: type SandboxConfig struct {\n43:     DefaultNamespace     string\n44:     ResourceTimeout      time.Duration\n45:     DefaultCPURequest    string\n46:     DefaultMemoryRequest string\n47:     AllowedRuntimes      []string\n48: }\n49: ```\n50: \n51: ### Sandbox Context\n52: \n53: ```go\n54: type SandboxContext struct {\n55:     Name         string\n56:     Namespace    string\n57:     RuntimeType  string\n58:     Owner        string\n59:     Labels       map[string]string\n60:     Annotations  map[string]string\n61:     Resources    v1.ResourceRequirements\n62: }\n63: ```\n64: \n65: ## API Contracts\n66: \n67: ### Processor Interface\n68: \n69: ```go\n70: type Processor interface {\n71:     Create(ctx context.Context, sandbox *SandboxContext) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n72:     Update(ctx context.Context, sandbox *SandboxContext) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n73:     Delete(ctx context.Context, name, namespace string) error\n74:     Get(ctx context.Context, name, namespace string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n75:     Watch(ctx context.Context, namespace string) (watch.Interface, error)\n76: }\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ### Create Operation\n80: \n81: **Input**: `SandboxContext` with required fields: `Name`, `Namespace`, `RuntimeType`\n82: \n83: **Output**: `*CodeInterpreter` or error\n84: \n85: **Behavior**:\n86: 1. Validate sandbox context (required fields, allowed runtime types)\n87: 2. Check for existing sandbox with same name\n88: 3. Construct `CodeInterpreter` object with proper labels/annotations\n89: 4. Apply resource quotas from config\n90: 5. Call `client.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Create()`\n91: 6. Return created resource or error\n92: \n93: ### Update Operation\n94: \n95: **Input**: `SandboxContext` with `Name`, `Namespace`, and fields to update\n96: \n97: **Output**: `*CodeInterpreter` or error\n98: \n99: **Behavior**:\n100: 1. Fetch existing `CodeInterpreter`\n101: 2. Apply updates (resources, labels, annotations)\n102: 3. Call `client.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Update()`\n103: 4. Return updated resource\n104: \n105: ### Delete Operation\n106: \n107: **Input**: `name`, `namespace`\n108: \n109: **Output**: error\n110: \n111: **Behavior**:\n112: 1. Call `client.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Delete()`\n113: 2. Handle `NotFound` errors gracefully\n114: \n115: ## Error Handling\n116: \n117: ### Error Types\n118: \n119: ```go\n120: var (\n121:     ErrSandboxNotFound     = errors.New(\"sandbox not found\")\n122:     ErrSandboxExists       = errors.New(\"sandbox already exists\")\n123:     ErrInvalidRuntime      = errors.New(\"invalid runtime type\")\n124:     ErrValidationFailed    = errors.New(\"sandbox validation failed\")\n125:     ErrCreateTimeout       = errors.New(\"sandbox creation timeout\")\n126: )\n127: ```\n128: \n129: ### Error Wrapping\n130: \n131: All errors wrapped with context using `fmt.Errorf(\"context: %w\", err)`.\n132: \n133: ### Retry Strategy\n134: \n135: - Transient errors: 3 retries with exponential backoff (100ms, 200ms, 400ms)\n136: - `TooManyRequests`: Respect `Retry-After` header\n137: - Permanent errors: Return immediately without retry\n138: \n139: ## Testing Strategy\n140: \n141: ### Unit Tests\n142: \n143: **File**: `processor/sandbox_processor_test.go`\n144: \n145: **Test Cases**:\n146: 1. `TestCreateSandbox_Success` - Valid sandbox creation\n147: 2. `TestCreateSandbox_InvalidRuntime` - Rejected runtime type\n148: 3. `TestCreateSandbox_AlreadyExists` - Duplicate creation\n149: 4. `TestUpdateSandbox_Success` - Resource update\n150: 5. `TestDeleteSandbox_Success` - Normal deletion\n151: 6. `TestDeleteSandbox_NotFound` - Idempotent delete\n152: 7. `TestGetSandbox_Success` - Retrieve existing sandbox\n153: \n154: ### Test Fixtures\n155: \n156: ```go\n157: func newTestSandboxContext(name, runtime string) *SandboxContext {\n158:     return &SandboxContext{\n159:         Name:        name,\n160:         Namespace:   \"default\",\n161:         RuntimeType: runtime,\n162:         Resources: v1.ResourceRequirements{\n163:             Requests: v1.ResourceList{\n164:                 v1.ResourceCPU:    resource.MustParse(\"100m\"),\n165:                 v1.ResourceMemory: resource.MustParse(\"128Mi\"),\n166:             },\n167:         },\n168:     }\n169: }\n170: ```\n171: \n172: ### Mock Setup\n173: \n174: ```go\n175: func newTestProcessor(client runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface) *SandboxProcessor {\n176:     return &SandboxProcessor{\n177:         client: client,\n178:         config: &SandboxConfig{\n179:             DefaultNamespace: \"default\",\n180:             ResourceTimeout:  30 * time.Second,\n181:             AllowedRuntimes:  []string{\"python\", \"nodejs\", \"go\"},\n182:         },\n183:     }\n184: }\n185: ```\n186: \n187: ### Integration Tests\n188: \n189: **File**: `processor/sandbox_processor_integration_test.go`\n190: \n191: Tests against real Kubernetes cluster (kind) using `envtest`:\n192: 1. Full lifecycle (create → update → delete)\n193: 2. Concurrent operations\n194: 3. Resource quota enforcement\n195: \n196: ## Implementation Notes\n197: \n198: ### Resource Naming\n199: \n200: CodeInterpreter resources follow pattern: `sandbox-{owner}-{uuid}`\n201: \n202: ### Labels\n203: \n204: Standard labels applied to all sandboxes:\n205: - `app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube`\n206: - `app.kubernetes.io/component: sandbox`\n207: - `agentcube.volcano.sh/owner: <owner>`\n208: - `agentcube.volcano.sh/runtime: <runtime-type>`\n209: \n210: ### Annotations\n211: \n212: - `agentcube.volcano.sh/created-at: <RFC3339>`\n213: - `agentcube.volcano.sh/last-updated: <RFC3339>`\n214: \n215: ### Timeout Handling\n216: \n217: Creation uses context with timeout from `config.ResourceTimeout`. Watch for resource to reach `Ready` phase within timeout window.\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n221: # Design: AR-014 Valkey Storage Implementation\n222: \n223: ## Overview\n224: \n225: This document describes the technical implementation of the session store for AgentCube, supporting both Redis and Valkey backends. The store persists sandbox metadata keyed by session ID, with sorted set indexes for expiry and last-activity tracking to enable garbage collection.\n226: \n227: ## Architecture\n228: \n229: ```\n230: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n231: │                     Application Layer                        │\n232: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n233:                             │\n234:                             ▼\n235: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n236: │                    store.Singleton                           │\n237: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n238: │  │ Storage() → Store (sync.Once initialization)         │   │\n239: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n240: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n241:                             │\n242:             ┌───────────────┴───────────────┐\n243:             │ STORE_TYPE (case-insensitive) │\n244:             ▼                               ▼\n245: ┌───────────────────────┐       ┌───────────────────────┐\n246: │    redisStore         │       │    valkeyStore        │\n247: │  - *redisv9.Client    │       │  - valkey.Client      │\n248: │  - sessionPrefix      │       │  - sessionPrefix      │\n249: │  - expiryIndexKey     │       │  - expiryIndexKey     │\n250: │  - lastActivityIndex  │       │  - lastActivityIndex  │\n251: └───────────────────────┘       └───────────────────────┘\n252:             │                               │\n253:             ▼                               ▼\n254: ┌───────────────────────┐       ┌───────────────────────┐\n255: │   Redis Server        │       │   Valkey Server       │\n256: │   - session:{id}      │       │   - session:{id}      │\n257: │   - session:expiry    │       │   - session:expiry    │\n258: │   - session:last_activity│    │   - session:last_activity│\n259: └───────────────────────┘       └───────────────────────┘\n260: ```\n261: \n262: ## Data Structures\n263: \n264: ### SandboxInfo (Primary Document)\n265: \n266: **Package:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`\n267: \n268: ```go\n269: type SandboxInfo struct {\n270:     Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n271:     SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n272:     SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n273:     Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n274:     EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n275:     SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n276:     CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n277:     ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n278:     Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n279: }\n280: \n281: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n282:     Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n283:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n284:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n285: }\n286: ```\n287: \n288: **Storage Format:** JSON-serialized string stored at key `session:{sessionID}`\n289: \n290: ### Index Structures\n291: \n292: | Index | Type | Key | Member | Score |\n293: |-------|------|-----|--------|-------|\n294: | Expiry | Sorted Set | `session:expiry` | sessionID | `ExpiresAt.Unix()` |\n295: | Last Activity | Sorted Set | `session:last_activity` | sessionID | `lastActivity.Unix()` |\n296: \n297: ## Store Interface Contract\n298: \n299: **Package:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`\n300: \n301: ```go\n302: type Store interface {\n303:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n304:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n305:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n306:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n307:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n308:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n309:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n310:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n311:     Close() error\n312: }\n313: ```\n314: \n315: ### Error Handling\n316: \n317: ```go\n318: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n319: ```\n320: \n321: | Error Condition | Error Value |\n322: |-----------------|-------------|\n323: | Key does not exist on GET | `ErrNotFound` |\n324: | Session missing on UpdateSessionLastActivity | `ErrNotFound` |\n325: | SET XX fails on UpdateSandbox (key not exists) | `key not exists` error |\n326: | Nil sandbox on StoreSandbox | validation error |\n327: | Zero ExpiresAt on StoreSandbox | validation error |\n328: \n329: ## Implementation Details\n330: \n331: ### Singleton Pattern (singleton.go)\n332: \n333: ```go\n334: var (\n335:     initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}\n336:     provider      Store\n337: )\n338: \n339: func Storage() Store {\n340:     initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)\n341:     return provider\n342: }\n343: \n344: func initStore() error {\n345:     storeType := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"STORE_TYPE\"))\n346:     if storeType == \"\" {\n347:         storeType = redisStoreType\n348:     }\n349:     \n350:     switch storeType {\n351:     case redisStoreType:\n352:         provider = newRedisStore()\n353:     case valkeyStoreType:\n354:         provider = newValkeyStore()\n355:     default:\n356:         return fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported store type: %s\", storeType)\n357:     }\n358:     return nil\n359: }\n360: ```\n361: \n362: ### Redis Implementation (store_redis.go)\n363: \n364: #### Connection Options\n365: \n366: ```go\n367: func makeRedisOptions() (*redisv9.Options, error) {\n368:     redisAddr := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_ADDR\")\n369:     if redisAddr == \"\" {\n370:         return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_ADDR is required\")\n371:     }\n372:     \n373:     redisPassword := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD\")\n374:     passwordRequired := true\n375:     if v := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"); strings.ToLower(v) == \"false\" {\n376:         passwordRequired = false\n377:     }\n378:     \n379:     if passwordRequired && redisPassword == \"\" {\n380:         return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_PASSWORD is required\")\n381:     }\n382:     \n383:     return &redisv9.Options{\n384:         Addr:     redisAddr,\n385:         Password: redisPassword,\n386:     }, nil\n387: }\n388: ```\n389: \n390: #### Key Operations\n391: \n392: | Operation | Redis Commands | Notes |\n393: |-----------|----------------|-------|\n394: | Ping | `PING` → expect \"PONG\" | Health check |\n395: | GetSandboxBySessionID | `GET session:{id}` | Return `ErrNotFound` on Nil |\n396: | StoreSandbox | Pipeline: `SETNX`, `ZADD expiry`, `ZADD last_activity` | Atomic batch |\n397: | UpdateSandbox | `SET key value XX` | Only update value, not indexes |\n398: | DeleteSandboxBySessionID | Pipeline: `DEL`, `ZREM expiry`, `ZREM last_activity` | Full cleanup |\n399: | ListExpiredSandboxes | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 limit` + pipeline GETs | Skip missing keys |\n400: | ListInactiveSandboxes | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 limit` + pipeline GETs | Skip missing keys |\n401: | UpdateSessionLastActivity | `EXISTS key` → `ZADD last_activity` | Verify key exists first |\n402: \n403: ### Valkey Implementation (store_valkey.go)\n404: \n405: #### Connection Options\n406: \n407: ```go\n408: func makeValkeyOptions() (*valkey.ClientOption, error) {\n409:     valkeyAddr := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_ADDR\")\n410:     if valkeyAddr == \"\" {\n411:         return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")\n412:     }\n413:     \n414:     valkeyPassword := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD\")\n415:     passwordRequired := true\n416:     if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"); strings.ToLower(v) == \"false\" {\n417:         passwordRequired = false\n418:     }\n419:     \n420:     if passwordRequired && valkeyPassword == \"\" {\n421:         return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required\")\n422:     }\n423:     \n424:     opt := &valkey.ClientOption{\n425:         InitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \",\"),\n426:         Password:    valkeyPassword,\n427:     }\n428:     \n429:     if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE\"); v != \"\" {\n430:         if disable, err := strconv.ParseBool(v); err == nil && disable {\n431:             opt.DisableCache = true\n432:         }\n433:     }\n434:     \n435:     if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\"); v != \"\" {\n436:         if force, err := strconv.ParseBool(v); err == nil && force {\n437:             opt.ForceSingleClient = true\n438:         }\n439:     }\n440:     \n441:     if opt.DisableCache || opt.ForceSingleClient {\n442:         klog.V(4).Infof(\"Valkey options: DisableCache=%v, ForceSingleClient=%v\", \n443:             opt.DisableCache, opt.ForceSingleClient)\n444:     }\n445:     \n446:     return opt, nil\n447: }\n448: ```\n449: \n450: #### Key Operations\n451: \n452: | Operation | Valkey API | Notes |\n453: |-----------|------------|-------|\n454: | Ping | `B().Ping()` → string \"PONG\" | Health check |\n455: | GetSandboxBySessionID | `B().Get().Key(key)` | `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n456: | StoreSandbox | `DoMulti`: SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD last_activity | Atomic batch |\n457: | UpdateSandbox | `SET ... XX` | Response must be \"OK\" |\n458: | DeleteSandboxBySessionID | `DoMulti`: DEL, ZREM expiry, ZREM last_activity | Full cleanup |\n459: | ListExpiredSandboxes | `Zrangebyscore` with Min(\"-inf\"), Max(before.Unix), Limit(0, limit) | Use MGET for batch load |\n460: | ListInactiveSandboxes | Same on last_activity key | MGET requires same slot |\n461: | UpdateSessionLastActivity | `Exists` → int64 must be 1, then `Zadd` | Verify existence first |\n462: \n463: #### MGET Optimization Note\n464: \n465: The `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` function uses single `MGET` for batch loading. This assumes all `session:{id}` keys are in the same cluster slot, which should be ensured through deployment configuration (e.g., hash tags or single-node deployment).\n466: \n467: ## Environment Configuration\n468: \n469: ### Common Variables\n470: \n471: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n472: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n473: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Provider selection (`redis` or `valkey`), case-insensitive |\n474: \n475: ### Redis-Specific Variables\n476: \n477: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n478: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n479: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | - | Redis server address (host:port) |\n480: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes* | - | Password for authentication |\n481: | `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to disable password requirement |\n482: \n483: \\* Required unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` (case-insensitive)\n484: \n485: ### Valkey-Specific Variables\n486: \n487: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n488: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n489: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated list of Valkey addresses |\n490: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes* | - | Password for authentication |\n491: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to disable password requirement |\n492: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to disable client-side caching |\n493: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to force single-client mode |\n494: \n495: ## API Contracts\n496: \n497: ### StoreSandbox Validation\n498: \n499: ```go\n500: func (s *redisStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxInfo *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n501:     if sandboxInfo == nil {\n502:         return errors.New(\"sandbox cannot be nil\")\n503:     }\n504:     if sandboxInfo.ExpiresAt.IsZero() {\n505:         return errors.New(\"expiresAt cannot be zero\")\n506:     }\n507:     // ... proceed with atomic pipeline\n508: }\n509: ```\n510: \n511: ### UpdateSandbox Semantics\n512: \n513: - **Only updates the JSON value** using `SET key value XX`\n514: - **Does NOT modify** expiry or last-activity sorted set entries\n515: - **Fails if key does not exist** (Redis: returns false; Valkey: response != \"OK\")\n516: \n517: ### List Operations - Orphan Handling\n518: \n519: Both `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` tolerate orphan ZSET entries (session IDs in the index without corresponding JSON documents):\n520: \n521: ```go\n522: // Skip entries where GET returns nil/empty\n523: if result == nil || result == \"\" {\n524:     continue // orphan ZSET member, skip\n525: }\n526: ```\n527: \n528: ### UpdateSessionLastActivity Preconditions\n529: \n530: 1. Session ID must be non-empty\n531: 2. If `at` is zero time, use `time.Now()`\n532: 3. **Verify session key exists** before ZADD\n533: 4. Return `ErrNotFound` if key does not exist\n534: \n535: ## Testing Strategy\n536: \n537: ### Unit Tests\n538: \n539: **File:** `pkg/store/store_redis_test.go`, `pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go`\n540: \n541: | Test Case | Description |\n542: |-----------|-------------|\n543: | `TestPing_Success` | Verify PING returns PONG |\n544: | `TestGetSandboxBySessionID_NotFound` | Verify `ErrNotFound` on missing key |\n545: | `TestStoreSandbox_NilRejected` | Verify nil sandbox validation |\n546: | `TestStoreSandbox_ZeroExpiresAtRejected` | Verify zero time validation |\n547: | `TestStoreSandbox_Atomicity` | Verify all three commands execute or fail together |\n548: | `TestUpdateSandbox_MissingKey` | Verify error when key doesn't exist |\n549: | `TestDeleteSandboxBySessionID_FullCleanup` | Verify DEL + ZREM operations |\n550: | `TestListExpiredSandboxes_OrphanTolerance` | Verify missing keys are skipped |\n551: | `TestUpdateSessionLastActivity_MissingSession` | Verify `ErrNotFound` on missing key |\n552: | `TestStorage_Singleton` | Verify sync.Once behavior with concurrent calls |\n553: \n554: ### Integration Tests\n555: \n556: **File:** `pkg/store/integration_test.go`\n557: \n558: | Test Case | Backend | Description |\n559: |-----------|---------|-------------|\n560: | `TestIntegration_StoreAndGet` | Redis, Valkey | Full store → get cycle |\n561: | `TestIntegration_ExpiryIndex` | Redis, Valkey | Verify ZSET score is correct |\n562: | `TestIntegration_LastActivityIndex` | Redis, Valkey | Verify activity tracking |\n563: | `TestIntegration_GC_ListExpired` | Redis, Valkey | Garbage collection query |\n564: | `TestIntegration_GC_ListInactive` | Redis, Valkey | Inactivity detection |\n565: | `TestIntegration_ConcurrentAccess` | Redis, Valkey | Concurrent store/update operations |\n566: \n567: ### Test Fixtures\n568: \n569: ```go\n570: func newTestSandbox(sessionID string, expiresAt time.Time) *types.SandboxInfo {\n571:     return &types.SandboxInfo{\n572:         Kind:             \"sandbox\",\n573:         SandboxID:        \"sandbox-123\",\n574:         SandboxNamespace: \"default\",\n575:         Name:             \"test-sandbox\",\n576:         SessionID:        sessionID,\n577:         CreatedAt:        time.Now(),\n578:         ExpiresAt:        expiresAt,\n579:         Status:           \"running\",\n580:         EntryPoints:      []types.SandboxEntryPoint{},\n581:     }\n582: }\n583: ```\n584: \n585: ## Dependencies\n586: \n587: ```go\n588: import (\n589:     // Redis client\n590:     \"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n591:     \n592:     // Valkey client\n593:     \"github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\"\n594:     \n595:     // Logging\n596:     \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n597:     \n598:     // Internal types\n599:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n600: )\n601: ```\n602: \n603: ## File Structure\n604: \n605: ```\n606: pkg/store/\n607: ├── store.go                    # Store interface definition\n608: ├── singleton.go                # Storage() singleton with sync.Once\n609: ├── store_redis.go              # Redis implementation\n610: ├── store_redis_test.go         # Redis unit tests\n611: ├── store_valkey.go             # Valkey implementation\n612: ├── store_valkey_test.go        # Valkey unit tests\n613: ├── integration_test.go         # Integration tests (both backends)\n614: └── errors.go                   # ErrNotFound and other package errors\n615: ```\n616: \n617: ## Regeneration\n618: \n619: Client code regeneration (if Kubernetes client updates are needed):\n620: \n621: ```bash\n622: make gen-client  # Runs hack/update-codegen.sh\n623: ```\n624: \n625: Uses `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 with `--with-watch` flag.\n626: \n627: ---\n628: \n629: # Design: AR-017 PicoD JWT Middleware\n630: \n631: ## Overview\n632: \n633: This document describes the technical implementation of JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD HTTP server. The middleware validates JWT tokens on incoming requests and injects validated claims into the request context for downstream handlers.\n634: \n635: ## Architecture\n636: \n637: ### Component Placement\n638: \n639: ```\n640: ┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐\n641: │   Client    │────▶│  PicoD HTTP  │────▶│ JWT Middle- │────▶│   Handler   │\n642: │  (with JWT) │     │   Server     │     │   ware      │     │  (Business) │\n643: └─────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └─────────────┘     └─────────────┘\n644: ```\n645: \n646: ### Package Structure\n647: \n648: ```\n649: pkg/picod/\n650: ├── jwt/\n651: │   ├── middleware.go      # HTTP middleware handler\n652: │   ├── validator.go       # JWT validation logic\n653: │   ├── claims.go          # Custom claims structure\n654: │   ├── config.go          # Configuration types\n655: │   └── error.go           # Error types\n656: ├── server.go              # PicoD server integration\n657: └── ...\n658: ```\n659: \n660: ### Dependencies\n661: \n662: - `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` - JWT parsing and validation\n663: - Standard library: `net/http`, `context`, `errors`, `fmt`, `strings`\n664: \n665: ## Data Structures\n666: \n667: ### Config\n668: \n669: ```go\n670: type Config struct {\n671:     // SigningKey is the secret key for HMAC verification\n672:     SigningKey []byte\n673:     \n674:     // SigningMethod is the signing algorithm (default: \"HS256\")\n675:     SigningMethod string\n676:     \n677:     // SkipPaths are paths that bypass JWT validation\n678:     SkipPaths map[string]bool\n679:     \n680:     // TokenLookup defines where to extract token from\n681:     // Format: \"header:<name>\" or \"query:<name>\"\n682:     TokenLookup string\n683:     \n684:     // ContextKey is the key to store claims in context\n685:     ContextKey string\n686:     \n687:     // ExpiryMax is the maximum allowed token expiry duration\n688:     ExpiryMax time.Duration\n689: }\n690: ```\n691: \n692: ### Claims\n693: \n694: ```go\n695: type Claims struct {\n696:     jwt.RegisteredClaims\n697:     \n698:     // Custom claims\n699:     UserID    string   `json:\"user_id,omitempty\"`\n700:     Namespace string   `json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n701:     Roles     []string `json:\"roles,omitempty\"`\n702: }\n703: ```\n704: \n705: ### Middleware\n706: \n707: ```go\n708: type Middleware struct {\n709:     config  *Config\n710:     keyFunc jwt.Keyfunc\n711:     parser  *jwt.Parser\n712: }\n713: ```\n714: \n715: ### Context Keys\n716: \n717: ```go\n718: type contextKey string\n719: \n720: const (\n721:     ClaimsKey contextKey = \"jwt_claims\"\n722: )\n723: ```\n724: \n725: ## API Contracts\n726: \n727: ### Middleware Constructor\n728: \n729: ```go\n730: func New(config Config) (*Middleware, error)\n731: ```\n732: \n733: **Behavior**:\n734: 1. Validate config (SigningKey required, valid SigningMethod)\n735: 2. Set defaults (SigningMethod=\"HS256\", TokenLookup=\"header:Authorization\")\n736: 3. Create keyFunc for HMAC verification\n737: 4. Configure parser with allowed methods\n738: 5. Return middleware instance or error\n739: \n740: ### HTTP Handler\n741: \n742: ```go\n743: func (m *Middleware) Handler(next http.Handler) http.Handler\n744: ```\n745: \n746: **Behavior**:\n747: 1. Check if request path is in SkipPaths\n748: 2. Extract token from header/query per TokenLookup\n749: 3. Parse and validate JWT\n750: 4. On success: inject claims to context, call next handler\n751: 5. On failure: return 401/403 with JSON error response\n752: \n753: ### Context Extraction\n754: \n755: ```go\n756: func GetClaims(ctx context.Context) (*Claims, bool)\n757: ```\n758: \n759: **Behavior**:\n760: 1. Extract claims from context using ClaimsKey\n761: 2. Return claims and true if present, nil and false otherwise\n762: \n763: ### Error Response Format\n764: \n765: ```go\n766: type Error struct {\n767:     Code    string `json:\"code\"`\n768:     Message string `json:\"message\"`\n769: }\n770: ```\n771: \n772: **Standard Error Codes**:\n773: | Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n774: |------|-------------|-------------|\n775: | `JWT_MISSING` | 401 | No token provided |\n776: | `JWT_INVALID` | 401 | Token format/structure invalid |\n777: | `JWT_EXPIRED` | 401 | Token has expired |\n778: | `JWT_SIGNATURE_INVALID` | 401 | Signature verification failed |\n779: | `JWT_EXPIRY_EXCEEDED` | 401 | Token expiry exceeds maximum allowed |\n780: \n781: ## Implementation Details\n782: \n783: ### Token Extraction\n784: \n785: ```go\n786: func (m *Middleware) extractToken(r *http.Request) (string, error) {\n787:     parts := strings.SplitN(m.config.TokenLookup, \":\", 2)\n788:     if len(parts) != 2 {\n789:         return \"\", errors.New(\"invalid token lookup format\")\n790:     }\n791:     \n792:     switch parts[0] {\n793:     case \"header\":\n794:         auth := r.Header.Get(parts[1])\n795:         if auth == \"\" {\n796:             return \"\", ErrTokenMissing\n797:         }\n798:         // Strip \"Bearer \" prefix if present\n799:         return strings.TrimPrefix(auth, \"Bearer \"), nil\n800:         \n801:     case \"query\":\n802:         token := r.URL.Query().Get(parts[1])\n803:         if token == \"\" {\n804:             return \"\", ErrTokenMissing\n805:         }\n806:         return token, nil\n807:         \n808:     default:\n809:         return \"\", errors.New(\"unsupported token lookup type\")\n810:     }\n811: }\n812: ```\n813: \n814: ### Validation Flow\n815: \n816: ```go\n817: func (m *Middleware) validate(tokenString string) (*Claims, error) {\n818:     token, err := m.parser.ParseWithClaims(tokenString, &Claims{}, m.keyFunc)\n819:     if err != nil {\n820:         if errors.Is(err, jwt.ErrTokenExpired) {\n821:             return nil, ErrTokenExpired\n822:         }\n823:         if strings.Contains(err.Error(), \"signature\") {\n824:             return nil, ErrSignatureInvalid\n825:         }\n826:         return nil, ErrTokenInvalid\n827:     }\n828:     \n829:     claims, ok := token.Claims.(*Claims)\n830:     if !ok || !token.Valid {\n831:         return nil, ErrTokenInvalid\n832:     }\n833:     \n834:     // Check max expiry\n835:     if m.config.ExpiryMax > 0 && claims.ExpiresAt != nil {\n836:         if time.Until(claims.ExpiresAt.Time) > m.config.ExpiryMax {\n837:             return nil, ErrExpiryExceeded\n838:         }\n839:     }\n840:     \n841:     return claims, nil\n842: }\n843: ```\n844: \n845: ### HTTP Error Response\n846: \n847: ```go\n848: func writeError(w http.ResponseWriter, statusCode int, code, message string) {\n849:     w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n850:     w.WriteHeader(statusCode)\n851:     json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(Error{Code: code, Message: message})\n852: }\n853: ```\n854: \n855: ## Error Handling\n856: \n857: ### Error Types\n858: \n859: ```go\n860: var (\n861:     ErrTokenMissing     = errors.New(\"jwt: token missing\")\n862:     ErrTokenInvalid     = errors.New(\"jwt: token invalid\")\n863:     ErrTokenExpired     = errors.New(\"jwt: token expired\")\n864:     ErrSignatureInvalid = errors.New(\"jwt: signature invalid\")\n865:     ErrExpiryExceeded   = errors.New(\"jwt: token expiry exceeds maximum\")\n866: )\n867: ```\n868: \n869: ### HTTP Response Codes\n870: \n871: | Scenario | Status | Response Body |\n872: |----------|--------|---------------|\n873: | Missing token | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_MISSING\",\"message\":\"Authorization token required\"}` |\n874: | Invalid format | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_INVALID\",\"message\":\"Invalid token format\"}` |\n875: | Expired token | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_EXPIRED\",\"message\":\"Token has expired\"}` |\n876: | Bad signature | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_SIGNATURE_INVALID\",\"message\":\"Invalid token signature\"}` |\n877: | Expiry exceeded | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_EXPIRY_EXCEEDED\",\"message\":\"Token expiry exceeds maximum allowed\"}` |\n878: \n879: ## Testing Strategy\n880: \n881: ### Unit Tests\n882: \n883: **File**: `jwt/middleware_test.go`\n884: \n885: ```go\n886: // Test middleware construction\n887: - TestNew_ValidConfig\n888: - TestNew_MissingSigningKey\n889: - TestNew_InvalidSigningMethod\n890: \n891: // Test token extraction\n892: - TestExtractToken_Header\n893: - TestExtractToken_Query\n894: - TestExtractToken_BearerPrefix\n895: - TestExtractToken_Missing\n896: \n897: // Test validation\n898: - TestValidateToken_ValidToken\n899: - TestValidateToken_ExpiredToken\n900: - TestValidateToken_InvalidSignature\n901: - TestValidateToken_MalformedToken\n902: - TestValidateToken_ExpiryExceeded\n903: \n904: // Test handler\n905: - TestMiddleware_SkipPath\n906: - TestMiddleware_HeaderExtraction\n907: - TestMiddleware_QueryExtraction\n908: - TestMiddleware_ContextInjection\n909: - TestMiddleware_UnauthorizedResponse\n910: ```\n911: \n912: ### Test Helpers\n913: \n914: **File**: `jwt/test_helpers.go`\n915: \n916: ```go\n917: // GenerateTestToken creates a signed JWT for testing\n918: func GenerateTestToken(claims *Claims, key []byte, expiry time.Duration) (string, error)\n919: \n920: // MockHTTPHandler returns a simple handler for testing\n921: func MockHTTPHandler(statusCode int) http.HandlerFunc\n922: \n923: // NewTestRequest creates an HTTP request with optional JWT\n924: func NewTestRequest(token, path, method string) *http.Request\n925: ```\n926: \n927: ### Integration Tests\n928: \n929: **File**: `jwt/integration_test.go`\n930: \n931: ```go\n932: // Full request flow tests\n933: - TestFullRequestFlow_WithValidJWT\n934: - TestFullRequestFlow_WithExpiredJWT\n935: - TestFullRequestFlow_WithoutJWT\n936: - TestFullRequestFlow_WithSkipPath\n937: - TestFullRequestFlow_CustomClaims\n938: ```\n939: \n940: ### Test Fixtures\n941: \n942: ```go\n943: func newTestConfig() Config {\n944:     return Config{\n945:         SigningKey:  []byte(\"test-secret-key\"),\n946:         SigningMethod: \"HS256\",\n947:         SkipPaths:   map[string]bool{\"/health\": true, \"/public\": true},\n948:         TokenLookup: \"header:Authorization\",\n949:         ContextKey:  \"claims\",\n950:         ExpiryMax:   24 * time.Hour,\n951:     }\n952: }\n953: \n954: func newTestClaims(userID, namespace string, roles []string) *Claims {\n955:     return &Claims{\n956:         RegisteredClaims: jwt.RegisteredClaims{\n957:             ExpiresAt: jwt.NewNumericDate(time.Now().Add(time.Hour)),\n958:             IssuedAt:  jwt.NewNumericDate(time.Now()),\n959:             Subject:   userID,\n960:         },\n961:         UserID:    userID,\n962:         Namespace: namespace,\n963:         Roles:     roles,\n964:     }\n965: }\n966: ```\n967: \n968: ## Security Considerations\n969: \n970: 1. **Key Management**: SigningKey should be loaded from environment variables or secret store, never hardcoded\n971: 2. **Algorithm Restriction**: Explicitly set allowed signing methods in parser to prevent algorithm confusion attacks\n972: 3. **Token Expiry**: Enforce reasonable expiry validation via ExpiryMax (default 24h)\n973: 4. **Path Whitelisting**: Default-deny approach; only paths in SkipPaths are public\n974: 5. **Constant-Time Comparison**: Use hmac.Equal for signature verification (handled by jwt library)\n975: \n976: ## Environment Configuration\n977: \n978: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n979: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n980: | `PICOD_JWT_SIGNING_KEY` | Yes | - | Secret key for HMAC verification |\n981: | `PICOD_JWT_SIGNING_METHOD` | No | `HS256` | Signing algorithm (HS256, HS384, HS512) |\n982: | `PICOD_JWT_SKIP_PATHS` | No | - | Comma-separated list of paths to skip |\n983: | `PICOD_JWT_TOKEN_LOOKUP` | No | `header:Authorization` | Token extraction location |\n984: | `PICOD_JWT_EXPIRY_MAX` | No | `24h` | Maximum allowed token expiry duration |\n985: \n986: ## File Structure\n987: \n988: ```\n989: pkg/picod/jwt/\n990: ├── config.go          # Configuration types and defaults\n991: ├── claims.go          # Claims structure\n992: ├── middleware.go      # HTTP middleware implementation\n993: ├── validator.go       # JWT validation logic\n994: ├── error.go           # Error types and messages\n995: ├── test_helpers.go    # Test utilities\n996: ├── config_test.go     # Configuration tests\n997: ├── middleware_test.go # Middleware unit tests\n998: └── integration_test.go # Integration tests\n999: ```\n\n(End of file - total 999 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-005 Sandbox Creation Processor\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for the Sandbox processor module within `pkg/workloadmanager`. The processor handles creation and lifecycle management of sandbox environments using Kubernetes custom resources.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── processor/\n│   ├── sandbox_processor.go      # Main processor implementation\n│   ├── sandbox_processor_test.go # Unit tests\n│   └── interface.go              # Processor interface definition\n├── types/\n│   └── sandbox.go                # Sandbox data structures\n└── config/\n    └── sandbox_config.go         # Configuration structures","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775883240887,"end":1775883240919}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883240928,"sessionID":"ses_2851c7184ffeDepVkFukH2kBxM","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae3b188001bbPowyirD1TE8n","messageID":"msg_d7ae3a621001r6LSE1IIh8wCUO","sessionID":"ses_2851c7184ffeDepVkFukH2kBxM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_75ada72722ad407ca6136327","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CI/CD — Design\n2: \n3: Sources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/.github/workflows/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/test/`, and (for Make targets) `/tmp/agentcube-ref/Makefile`.\n4: \n5: ## GitHub Actions workflows (summary table)\n6: \n7: | Filename | Workflow `name` | Trigger events | Path filters (dorny/paths-filter or notes) | Jobs | Key steps | Env vars (job/step) | Secrets |\n8: |----------|-----------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------|------|-----------|---------------------|---------|\n9: | `main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `build` | Checkout; Docker Buildx setup; verify Docker; `make docker-build` | — | — |\n10: | `e2e.yml` | Agentcube E2E Tests | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `e2e-test` | Checkout; Go 1.23; `helm/kind-action@v1` **install_only** Kind v0.30.0, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`; `export ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`; `make e2e`; on failure upload `e2e-logs/`; `always` → `make e2e-clean` | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (shell) | — |\n11: | `lint.yml` | Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `lint`: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | `golangci` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24; `make lint` | — | — |\n12: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk`: `sdk-python/**` | `python-sdk-tests` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.12 in `sdk-python/`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` | Default `working-directory: sdk-python` | — |\n13: | `python-lint.yml` | Python Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `python`: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, workflow self | `python_lint` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.10; `pip install ruff`; `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` | — | — |\n14: | `test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | `coverage`: `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` | `coverage` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: free disk space; Go 1.24; `go test` with coverage; step summary; Codecov upload; artifact `go-coverage` | `CODECOV_TOKEN` passed to Codecov action when present | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional; declared for `workflow_call`) |\n15: | `codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `codegen`: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | `codegen-check` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24.4; `make gen-check` | — | — |\n16: | `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `copyright`: all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | `build` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: `apt install moreutils`; `make gen-copyright`; `git diff --exit-code` | — | — |\n17: | `codespell.yml` | Codespell | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none — scans tree after temporarily removing some manifests)* | `codespell` | Backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json`; `pip install codespell`; `codespell` with `--check-filenames`, `--skip`, `--ignore-words-list`; restore files | — | — |\n18: | `build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release Images | `push` → `main`; `push` tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | *(none)* | `build-and-push` | Checkout; Go 1.24.4; Buildx; `docker/login-action` to `ghcr.io`; set `TAG` from ref; `make docker-buildx-push` (workload manager), `docker-buildx-push-router`, `docker-buildx-push-picod` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `TAG`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` | `GITHUB_TOKEN` (registry login) |\n19: | `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | *(none)* | `publish` | Download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6; install `yq`; read `manifest.yaml`; package plugin; checkout `author/dify-plugins` with token; move `.difypkg`; branch, commit, push; `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` | `GH_TOKEN` on PR step | `PLUGIN_ACTION` (repo checkout + `gh`; cross-repo PR) |\n20: | `workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows | `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` → `main`, `release-**` | *(logic: first-time contributor vs `ok-to-test` label)* | `approve` | `github-script`: list contributor PRs; if not first-time or has `ok-to-test`, list `action_required` workflow runs for SHA and approve | — | `GITHUB_TOKEN` |\n21: \n22: ### Workflow notes\n23: \n24: - **`e2e.yml`**: Uses Kind action with `install_only: true` so the cluster is created by `run_e2e.sh` (`kind create cluster`), avoiding double-creation.\n25: - **`test-coverage.yml`**: `workflow_call` declares `CODECOV_TOKEN` optional for reusable invocation; PR runs use the repo secret when configured.\n26: - **`build-push-release.yml`**: Uses older action major versions (`checkout@v3`, `setup-go@v4`, `buildx@v2`) than most other workflows.\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## E2E test setup (`test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`)\n31: \n32: ### Kind cluster\n33: \n34: | Item | Value / behavior |\n35: |------|------------------|\n36: | Default cluster name | `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` → `agentcube-e2e` |\n37: | Creation | `kind create cluster --name \"${E2E_CLUSTER_NAME}\"` if missing; if exists and `E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER=true` (default), delete then recreate |\n38: | CI alignment | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` installs Kind **v0.30.0** via `helm/kind-action@v1` (`install_only: true`) |\n39: | Skip setup | `E2E_SKIP_SETUP=true` skips `run_setup` and assumes an existing cluster |\n40: \n41: ### CRD / agent-sandbox installation\n42: \n43: Applied via `kubectl apply --validate=false` after downloading release assets (URLs built from `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`, default **`v0.1.1`**):\n44: \n45: 1. `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/manifest.yaml`\n46: 2. `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/extensions.yaml`\n47: \n48: ### Images pre-pulled and loaded into Kind\n49: \n50: - `registry.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/agent-sandbox-controller:${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}`\n51: - `python:3.9-slim` (echo agent workload)\n52: \n53: Local images built and loaded:\n54: \n55: - `make docker-build` → default `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE` **`workloadmanager:latest`**\n56: - `make docker-build-router` → **`agentcube-router:latest`**\n57: - `make docker-build-picod` → **`picod:latest`**\n58: - `REDIS_IMAGE` default **`redis:7-alpine`** (Deployment + Service in namespace)\n59: \n60: ### Helm (AgentCube chart)\n61: \n62: | Item | Value |\n63: |------|--------|\n64: | Chart path | `manifests/charts/base` |\n65: | Release / namespace | `agentcube` in `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (default `agentcube`), `--create-namespace` |\n66: | Redis addr | `redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379`, password empty |\n67: | Workload manager image | `repository=workloadmanager`, `tag=latest` |\n68: | Router image | `repository=agentcube-router`, `tag=latest` |\n69: | Router RBAC | `router.rbac.create=true`, `router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router` |\n70: | Extra env (JSON via `--set-json`) | Workload manager: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`, `JWT_KEY_SECRET_NAMESPACE=agentcube`; Router: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n71: | Wait | `helm upgrade --install ... --wait` |\n72: \n73: ### Kubernetes fixtures applied during setup\n74: \n75: | Path | Purpose |\n76: |------|---------|\n77: | `test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml` | `AgentRuntime` `echo-agent` in `agentcube` |\n78: | Generated from `echo_agent.yaml` (sed) | `echo-agent-short-ttl` with `sessionTimeout: \"30s\"` for TTL tests |\n79: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` | `CodeInterpreter` `e2e-code-interpreter` in `agentcube` |\n80: \n81: Warm-pool Go tests apply `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` at runtime (not in initial `kubectl apply` list in the shell script).\n82: \n83: ### Port forwards and health checks\n84: \n85: - Workload manager: `kubectl port-forward svc/workloadmanager` → `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT` (default **8080**) → pod 8080\n86: - Router: `kubectl port-forward svc/agentcube-router` → `ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT` (default **8081**) → pod 8080\n87: - Readiness: `curl` to `http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}/health` and `http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}/health/live`\n88: \n89: ### Auth for tests\n90: \n91: - ServiceAccount `e2e-test` in `agentcube` + `ClusterRoleBinding` to `workloadmanager` clusterrole\n92: - API token: `kubectl create token e2e-test -n agentcube --duration=24h` → `API_TOKEN`\n93: \n94: ### Python venv for E2E\n95: \n96: - Directory: `E2E_VENV_DIR` (default `/tmp/agentcube-e2e-venv`)\n97: - `python3 -m venv`, `pip install -e ./sdk-python`, verify `import agentcube`\n98: \n99: ### Test commands invoked by `run_e2e.sh`\n100: \n101: **Go** (from repository root):\n102: \n103: ```bash\n104: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n105: ROUTER_URL=\"http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n106: API_TOKEN=$API_TOKEN \\\n107: go test -v ./test/e2e/...\n108: ```\n109: \n110: **Python** (after `cd` to `test/e2e`):\n111: \n112: ```bash\n113: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"...\" ROUTER_URL=\"...\" API_TOKEN=$API_TOKEN \\\n114: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE=\"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n115: \"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" test_codeinterpreter.py\n116: ```\n117: \n118: (`test_codeinterpreter.py` uses `unittest.main()` and appends `--verbose` if missing.)\n119: \n120: ### Failure artifacts\n121: \n122: On test failure, `collect_component_logs` writes under `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (CI: `${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`): workload manager, router, and sandbox pod logs/describes.\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ## Test directory structure\n127: \n128: ```\n129: test/\n130: ├── OWNERS\n131: └── e2e/\n132:     ├── README.md\n133:     ├── __init__.py\n134:     ├── run_e2e.sh\n135:     ├── e2e_test.go\n136:     ├── test_codeinterpreter.py\n137:     ├── echo_agent.yaml\n138:     ├── e2e_code_interpreter.yaml\n139:     └── e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml\n140: ```\n141: \n142: ### Fixture paths (relative to repo root unless noted)\n143: \n144: | Fixture | Description |\n145: |---------|-------------|\n146: | `test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml` | Echo `AgentRuntime` for router invocation tests |\n147: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` | Standard `CodeInterpreter` (`e2e-code-interpreter`, namespace `agentcube`) |\n148: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` | `CodeInterpreter` with `warmPoolSize: 2` in `default` (loaded by Go tests from **package cwd** as `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml`) |\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## Go test commands and flags in CI\n153: \n154: | Workflow / entrypoint | Command | Flags / notes |\n155: |------------------------|---------|----------------|\n156: | `test-coverage.yml` | `go test` | `-race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` |\n157: | `e2e.yml` via `make e2e` → `run_e2e.sh` | `go test` | `-v ./test/e2e/...` with env `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `API_TOKEN` |\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ## Python test commands in CI\n162: \n163: | Workflow | Working dir | Command |\n164: |----------|-------------|---------|\n165: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | `sdk-python` | `python -m pip install --upgrade pip`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` |\n166: | `e2e.yml` (via `run_e2e.sh`) | Invoked from `test/e2e/` | `\"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" test_codeinterpreter.py` (unittest, verbosity 2) |\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ## Key Make targets referenced by CI\n171: \n172: | Target | Referenced in | Role |\n173: |--------|----------------|------|\n174: | `docker-build` | `main.yml`, `run_e2e.sh` | Build workload manager image |\n175: | `docker-build-router` | `run_e2e.sh` | Build router image |\n176: | `docker-build-picod` | `run_e2e.sh` | Build picod image |\n177: | `docker-buildx-push` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push workload manager image (`IMAGE_REGISTRY`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE=workloadmanager:${TAG}`) |\n178: | `docker-buildx-push-router` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push router image |\n179: | `docker-buildx-push-picod` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push picod image |\n180: | `e2e` | `e2e.yml` | Run `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` |\n181: | `e2e-clean` | `e2e.yml` | `kind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)`; `rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox` |\n182: | `lint` | `lint.yml` | `golangci-lint` (project default) |\n183: | `gen-check` | `codegen-check.yml` | Verify generated code up to date |\n184: | `gen-copyright` | `copyright-check.yml` | Generate copyright headers for check |\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ## Additional reference: E2E README vs script\n189: \n190: `test/e2e/README.md` states Go **1.24+** and generic “install CRDs and agent-sandbox”; the **CI workflow** pins Go **1.23** for E2E, and **run_e2e.sh** pins **agent-sandbox `v0.1.1`** by default (overridable via `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`).\n\n(End of file - total 190 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CI/CD — Design\n\nSources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/.github/workflows/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/test/`, and (for Make targets) `/tmp/agentcube-ref/Makefile`.\n\n## GitHub Actions workflows (summary table)\n\n| Filename | Workflow `name` | Trigger events | Path filters (dorny/paths-filter or notes) | Jobs | Key steps | Env vars (job/step) | Secrets |\n|----------|-----------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------|------|-----------|---------------------|---------|\n| `main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `build` | Checkout; Docker Buildx setup; verify Docker; `make docker-build` | — | — |\n| `e2e.yml` | Agentcube E2E Tests | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `e2e-test` | Checkout; Go 1.23; `helm/kind-action@v1` **install_only** Kind v0.30.0, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`; `export ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`; `make e2e`; on failure upload `e2e-logs/`; `always` → `make e2e-clean` | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (shell) | — |\n| `lint.yml` | Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `lint`: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | `golangci` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24; `make lint` | — | — |\n| `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk`: `sdk-python/**` | `python-sdk-tests` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.12 in `sdk-python/`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` | Default `working-directory: sdk-python` | — |\n| `python-lint.yml` | Python Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `python`: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, workflow self | `python_lint` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.10; `pip install ruff`; `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` | — | — |\n| `test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | `coverage`: `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` | `coverage` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: free disk space; Go 1.24; `go test` with coverage; step summary; Codecov upload; artifact `go-coverage` | `CODECOV_TOKEN` passed to Codecov action when present | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional; declared for `workflow_call`) |\n| `codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `codegen`: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | `codegen-check` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24.4; `make gen-check` | — | — |\n| `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `copyright`: all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | `build` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: `apt install moreutils`; `make gen-copyright`; `git diff --exit-code` | — | — |\n| `codespell.yml` | Codespell | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none — scans tree after temporarily removing some manifests)* | `codespell` | Backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json`; `pip install codespell`; `codespell` with `--check-filenames`, `--skip`, `--ignore-words-list`; restore files | — | — |\n| `build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release Images | `push` → `main`; `push` tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | *(none)* | `build-and-push` | Checkout; Go 1.24.4; Buildx; `docker/login-action` to `ghcr.io`; set `TAG` from ref; `make docker-buildx-push` (workload manager), `docker-buildx-push-router`, `docker-buildx-push-picod` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `TAG`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` | `GITHUB_TOKEN` (registry login) |\n| `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | *(none)* | `publish` | Download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6; install `yq`; read `manifest.yaml`; package plugin; checkout `author/dify-plugins` with token; move `.difypkg`; branch, commit, push; `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` | `GH_TOKEN` on PR step | `PLUGIN_ACTION` (repo checkout + `gh`; cross-repo PR) |\n| `workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows | `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` → `main`, `release-**` | *(logic: first-time contributor vs `ok-to-test` label)* | `approve` | `github-script`: list contributor PRs; if not first-time or has `ok-to-tes