e-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-008/VERIFICATION_REPORT.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-008/status.json\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-008/tasks.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-008/README.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-007/tasks.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-007/status.json\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-007/README.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-006/proposal.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-006/CHECKLIST.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-006/CHANGE.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-005/proposal.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-005/CHECKLIST.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-005/CHANGE.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-004/tasks.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-004/proposal.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-003/tasks.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-002/status.json\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-002/tasks.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-002/README.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/tasks.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/status.json\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/README.md\n\n(Results are truncated: showing first 100 results. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"count":100,"truncated":true},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z","time":{"start":1775883248281,"end":1775883248300}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775883248331,"sessionID":"ses_2851c7184ffeDepVkFukH2kBxM","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae3e2af001tVcuoxWR9nLs4l","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7ae3c615001sYnkKcTeRsl49X","sessionID":"ses_2851c7184ffeDepVkFukH2kBxM","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":45314,"input":6,"output":138,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":27880,"read":17290}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775883250235,"sessionID":"ses_2851c7184ffeDepVkFukH2kBxM","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae3ea3900113Kccz7vZqQR0b","messageID":"msg_d7ae3e2e4001MzA6tF5Z0JQXi4","sessionID":"ses_2851c7184ffeDepVkFukH2kBxM","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883254919,"sessionID":"ses_2851c7184ffeDepVkFukH2kBxM","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae3f7a7001ldKk6VnhoWLkoY","messageID":"msg_d7ae3e2e4001MzA6tF5Z0JQXi4","sessionID":"ses_2851c7184ffeDepVkFukH2kBxM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_23fcfe617af04f5eb38454eb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # CI/CD Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Automate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Pull request build verification\n9: The system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Docker build in CI\n12: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n13: - **WHEN** the “Agentcube CI Workflow” job runs\n14: - **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Go lint on changed Go code\n17: The system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Path-filtered lint\n20: - **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n21: - **WHEN** the Lint workflow runs\n22: - **THEN** it SHALL use Go `1.24` and execute `make lint`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Code generation check\n25: The system SHALL verify generated artifacts match `make gen-all` when API, hack, workflow, or Makefile inputs change.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Regenerate and diff\n28: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, or `Makefile`\n29: - **WHEN** the Codegen Check workflow runs with Go `1.24.4`\n30: - **THEN** it SHALL run `make gen-check` (which runs `gen-all` and `git diff --exit-code`)\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Go test coverage reporting\n33: The system SHALL run race-enabled coverage tests on `pkg/...` for qualifying pull requests and merge groups, optionally uploading to Codecov.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Coverage command\n36: - **GIVEN** path filter `coverage` matches (broad glob excluding some media/docs per workflow)\n37: - **WHEN** the Test Coverage job runs with Go `1.24`\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` and upload `coverage.out` as an artifact\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: E2E testing on Kind\n41: The system SHALL run `make e2e` in CI using a Kind-capable Ubuntu runner, capturing logs on failure.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: E2E job lifecycle\n44: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n45: - **WHEN** the E2E workflow runs\n46: - **THEN** it SHALL set `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`, install Kind tool `v0.30.0` (`install_only: true`), run `make e2e` with Go `1.23`, upload `e2e-logs` on failure, and always run `make e2e-clean`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Python SDK unit tests\n49: The system SHALL run pytest for the SDK when `sdk-python/**` changes.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Editable install and pytest\n52: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `sdk-python/**`\n53: - **WHEN** the Python SDK Tests job runs with Python `3.12` in `sdk-python/`\n54: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install pytest`, `pip install -e .`, and run `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: Python lint\n57: The system SHALL run Ruff from repository root using `pyproject.toml` when Python-touching paths change.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Ruff check\n60: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, or the workflow file\n61: - **WHEN** the Python Lint job runs with Python `3.10`\n62: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install ruff` and run `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: Spelling check (codespell)\n65: The system SHALL run codespell on the repository for pull requests to `main` or `release-*`, temporarily moving files that cause false positives.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Codespell invocation\n68: - **GIVEN** checkout complete\n69: - **WHEN** codespell runs after backup/remove of `pyproject.toml`, `package-lock.json`, `package.json` at repo root (and nested copies per `find`)\n70: - **THEN** it SHALL use `pip install codespell` and run codespell with `--check-filenames`, specified `--skip` globs, and `--ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn` on `.`, then restore backed-up files\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: Copyright header check\n73: The system SHALL ensure `make gen-copyright` produces no git diff when applicable files change.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Copyright workflow\n76: - **GIVEN** path filter marks `copyright` (all paths minus exclusions for md/svg/png/docs/.github per workflow)\n77: - **WHEN** the job runs\n78: - **THEN** it SHALL install `moreutils` (`sponge`), run `make gen-copyright`, and `git diff --exit-code`\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: Release image publication\n81: The system SHALL build and push multi-architecture images for workloadmanager, router, and picod to GitHub Container Registry on pushes to `main` and on semantic version tags.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Tag selects image tag\n84: - **GIVEN** a `push` event\n85: - **WHEN** `github.ref_type` is `tag`, environment `TAG` SHALL be `github.ref_name`; otherwise `TAG` SHALL be `latest`\n86: - **THEN** the job SHALL log in to `ghcr.io` with `GITHUB_TOKEN` and run `make docker-buildx-push*`, setting `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` and per-image `*_IMAGE=<name>:${TAG}`\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Workflow approval for first-time contributors\n89: The system SHALL optionally approve pending workflow runs for pull requests from repeat contributors or those labeled `ok-to-test`.\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Approve action_required runs\n92: - **GIVEN** `pull_request_target` on `main` or `release-**` with label/sync events\n93: - **WHEN** the contributor is not first-time (more than one PR) or PR has `ok-to-test`\n94: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL list workflow runs for the head SHA with `status: action_required` and call `approveWorkflowRun` for each\n\n(End of file - total 94 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# CI/CD Specification\n\n## Purpose\nAutomate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Pull request build verification\nThe system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n\n#### Scenario: Docker build in CI\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n- **WHEN** the “Agentcube CI Workflow” job runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n\n### Requirement: Go lint on changed Go code\nThe system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n\n#### Scenario: Path-filtered lint\n- **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/spec.md","time":{"start":1775883254908,"end":1775883254918}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883254925,"sessionID":"ses_2851c7184ffeDepVkFukH2kBxM","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae3f21e001hmbenfbQxOBh3p","messageID":"msg_d7ae3e2e4001MzA6tF5Z0JQXi4","sessionID":"ses_2851c7184ffeDepVkFukH2kBxM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_e021c4c034ec48cba06a47ba","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-034/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-034/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: 本提案实现 AgentCube 项目的 GitHub Actions CI/CD 流水线体系，为代码质量、构建验证、镜像发布、安全扫描提供自动化流水线。该 CI/CD 体系是 AgentCube 工程化实践的核心基础设施，支撑持续集成、持续交付、质量门禁全流程。\n6: \n7: 目标是：\n8: \n9: 1. **代码质量门禁** - 在 PR 和 push 事件中自动运行 lint、typecheck、test，确保代码质量\n10: 2. **构建验证** - 验证 Go 和 Python 代码可编译，Docker 镜像可构建\n11: 3. **多架构支持** - 构建 amd64、arm64 多架构 Docker 镜像，支持异构集群\n12: 4. **镜像发布** - 自动推送镜像到 GHCR，支持版本标签管理（latest, commit-sha, semver）\n13: 5. **安全扫描** - 集成 Trivy 扫描镜像漏洞，集成 CodeQL 扫描代码安全问题\n14: 6. **文档站点** - 自动构建和部署 Docusaurus 文档到 GitHub Pages\n15: 7. **发布自动化** - 创建 GitHub Release，生成变更日志，上传构建产物\n16: 8. **依赖更新** - 自动检测依赖更新，创建 Dependabot PR\n17: \n18: 本提案基于 AR-032（Dockerfile 多阶段构建）、AR-033（Makefile 构建目标）实现，遵循 GitHub Actions 最佳实践和 AgentCube 工程规范。\n19: \n20: ## Scope\n21: \n22: **Module:** .github  \n23: **Language:** YAML  \n24: **Size:** L\n25: \n26: 本 AR 包含：\n27: \n28: - **包含内容：**\n29:   - `.github/workflows/ci.yml` - CI 流水线（lint, test, build）\n30:   - `.github/workflows/cd.yml` - CD 流水线（镜像推送、发布）\n31:   - `.github/workflows/security-scan.yml` - 安全扫描（Trivy, CodeQL）\n32:   - `.github/workflows/docs.yml` - 文档构建和部署\n33:   - `.github/workflows/multi-arch-build.yml` - 多架构镜像构建\n34:   - `.github/workflows/e2e-test.yml` - 端到端测试\n35:   - `.github/workflows/nightly-build.yml` - 夜间构建\n36:   - `.github/workflows/pr-validation.yml` - PR 验证\n37:   - `.github/workflows/release.yml` - Release 发布\n38:   - `.github/workflows/dependency-review.yml` - 依赖审查\n39:   - `.github/workflows/stale.yml` -  stale 管理\n40:   - `.github/workflows/labeler.yml` - 自动标签\n41:   - `.github/dependabot.yml` - Dependabot 配置\n42:   - `.github/labeler.yml` - 自动标签规则\n43:   - `.github/CODEOWNERS` - 代码所有者\n44:   - 相关 Action 配置和脚本\n45: \n46: - **不包含内容：**\n47:   - Dockerfile 编写（由 AR-032 管理）\n48:   - Makefile 编写（由 AR-033 管理）\n49:   - Helm Chart 打包发布（由 AR-030 管理）\n50:   - 文档内容编写（由文档团队管理）\n51: \n52: ## Current State Analysis\n53: \n54: ### 现有 CI/CD 状态\n55: \n56: 根据项目结构检查：\n57: - 无 `.github/workflows/` 目录\n58: - 无 `.github/dependabot.yml`\n59: - 无 `.github/CODEOWNERS`\n60: - 无现有 GitHub Actions 配置\n61: \n62: ### 参考设计规范\n63: \n64: 根据 `project.md` 和 AR-032、AR-033：\n65: \n66: **技术栈要求：**\n67: - Go 1.24 - 需要配置 Go 环境\n68: - Python ≥3.10 - 需要配置 Python 环境\n69: - Docker - 需要 Docker in Docker 或 Runner 预装\n70: - Helm 3 - 需要 Helm 工具\n71: - Kubernetes - 需要 Kind 或 K3s 进行测试\n72: \n73: **镜像仓库：**\n74: - GHCR (ghcr.io/volcano-sh) - GitHub Container Registry\n75: - 标签策略：latest, <commit-sha>, <version>\n76: \n77: **发布流程：**\n78: - Git tag 触发 Release\n79: - 语义化版本：vMajor.Minor.Patch\n80: - 自动生成交付物\n81: \n82: ### 差距分析\n83: \n84: 1. **缺少工作流文件** - 无任何 GitHub Actions 工作流\n85: 2. **缺少依赖管理** - 无 Dependabot 配置\n86: 3. **缺少代码所有者** - 无 CODEOWNERS 配置\n87: 4. **缺少标签管理** - 无自动标签规则\n88: 5. **缺少安全策略** - 无安全扫描配置\n89: \n90: ### 项目特殊需求\n91: \n92: 根据 AgentCube 架构：\n93: \n94: 1. **Kubernetes 测试** - 需要 Kind 集群测试 K8s 集成\n95: 2. **Redis 测试** - 需要 Redis 服务测试缓存层\n96: 3. **多组件构建** - Workload Manager、Router、Volcano Agent Scheduler 三个组件\n97: 4. **Python SDK/CLI** - 需要 Python 包构建和发布\n98: 5. **Helm Chart** - 需要 Helm lint 和打包\n99: 6. **文档站点** - Docusaurus 构建和部署\n100: \n101: ## Proposed Changes\n102: \n103: ### 1. 目录结构\n104: \n105: ```\n106: .github/\n107: ├── workflows/\n108: │   ├── ci.yml                      # CI 主流水线\n109: │   ├── cd.yml                      # CD 发布流水线\n110: │   ├── security-scan.yml           # 安全扫描\n111: │   ├── docs.yml                    # 文档部署\n112: │   ├── multi-arch-build.yml        # 多架构构建\n113: │   ├── e2e-test.yml                # 端到端测试\n114: │   ├── nightly-build.yml           # 夜间构建\n115: │   ├── pr-validation.yml           # PR 验证\n116: │   ├── release.yml                 # Release 发布\n117: │   ├── dependency-review.yml       # 依赖审查\n118: │   ├── stale.yml                   # Stale 管理\n119: │   └── labeler.yml                 # 自动标签\n120: ├── dependabot.yml                  # Dependabot 配置\n121: ├── labeler.yml                     # 标签规则\n122: └── CODEOWNERS                      # 代码所有者\n123: ```\n124: \n125: ### 2. CI 主流水线 (ci.yml)\n126: \n127: ```yaml\n128: # .github/workflows/ci.yml\n129: name: CI\n130: \n131: on:\n132:   push:\n133:     branches: [main, develop]\n134:   pull_request:\n135:     branches: [main, develop]\n136: \n137: env:\n138:   GO_VERSION: '1.24'\n139:   PYTHON_VERSION: '3.11'\n140:   NODE_VERSION: '20'\n141: \n142: permissions:\n143:   contents: read\n144: \n145: jobs:\n146:   go-lint:\n147:     name: Go Lint\n148:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n149:     steps:\n150:       - name: Checkout\n151:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n152: \n153:       - name: Setup Go\n154:         uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n155:         with:\n156:           go-version: ${{ env.GO_VERSION }}\n157:           cache: true\n158: \n159:       - name: Run golangci-lint\n160:         uses: golangci/golangci-lint-action@v6\n161:         with:\n162:           version: latest\n163:           args: --timeout=5m\n164: \n165:   go-test:\n166:     name: Go Test\n167:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n168:     services:\n169:       redis:\n170:         image: redis:7-alpine\n171:         ports:\n172:           - 6379:6379\n173:     steps:\n174:       - name: Checkout\n175:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n176: \n177:       - name: Setup Go\n178:         uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n179:         with:\n180:           go-version: ${{ env.GO_VERSION }}\n181:           cache: true\n182: \n183:       - name: Run tests\n184:         run: go test -race -coverprofile=coverage.out ./...\n185: \n186:       - name: Upload coverage\n187:         uses: codecov/codecov-action@v4\n188:         with:\n189:           file: ./coverage.out\n190:           flags: go\n191: \n192:   python-lint:\n193:     name: Python Lint\n194:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n195:     steps:\n196:       - name: Checkout\n197:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n198: \n199:       - name: Setup Python\n200:         uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n201:         with:\n202:           python-version: ${{ env.PYTHON_VERSION }}\n203: \n204:       - name: Install dependencies\n205:         run: |\n206:           pip install ruff mypy\n207:           pip install -e sdk-python/\n208: \n209:       - name: Run ruff\n210:         run: ruff check sdk-python/ cmd/cli/\n211: \n212:       - name: Run mypy\n213:         run: mypy sdk-python/ cmd/cli/\n214: \n215:   python-test:\n216:     name: Python Test\n217:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n218:     services:\n219:       redis:\n220:         image: redis:7-alpine\n221:         ports:\n222:           - 6379:6379\n223:     steps:\n224:       - name: Checkout\n225:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n226: \n227:       - name: Setup Python\n228:         uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n229:         with:\n230:           python-version: ${{ env.PYTHON_VERSION }}\n231: \n232:       - name: Install dependencies\n233:         run: |\n234:           pip install pytest pytest-cov\n235:           pip install -e sdk-python/\n236: \n237:       - name: Run tests\n238:         run: pytest --cov=sdk-python sdk-python/ tests/\n239: \n240:       - name: Upload coverage\n241:         uses: codecov/codecov-action@v4\n242:         with:\n243:           file: ./coverage.xml\n244:           flags: python\n245: \n246:   helm-lint:\n247:     name: Helm Lint\n248:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n249:     steps:\n250:       - name: Checkout\n251:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n252: \n253:       - name: Setup Helm\n254:         uses: azure/setup-helm@v3\n255:         with:\n256:           version: v3.14.0\n257: \n258:       - name: Run helm lint\n259:         run: helm lint manifests/\n260: \n261:   build-verify:\n262:     name: Build Verify\n263:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n264:     needs: [go-lint, go-test, python-lint, python-test]\n265:     steps:\n266:       - name: Checkout\n267:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n268: \n269:       - name: Setup Go\n270:         uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n271:         with:\n272:           go-version: ${{ env.GO_VERSION }}\n273: \n274:       - name: Build Go binaries\n275:         run: |\n276:           go build -o /tmp/workloadmanager ./cmd/agentcube\n277:           go build -o /tmp/router ./cmd/agentcube-proxy\n278:           go build -o /tmp/volcano-agent-scheduler ./cmd/agentd\n279: \n280:       - name: Setup Python\n281:         uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n282:         with:\n283:           python-version: ${{ env.PYTHON_VERSION }}\n284: \n285:       - name: Build Python packages\n286:         run: |\n287:           pip install build\n288:           python -m build sdk-python/\n289: ```\n290: \n291: ### 3. CD 发布流水线 (cd.yml)\n292: \n293: ```yaml\n294: # .github/workflows/cd.yml\n295: name: CD\n296: \n297: on:\n298:   push:\n299:     branches: [main]\n300:     tags:\n301:       - 'v*'\n302: \n303: env:\n304:   REGISTRY: ghcr.io\n305:   IMAGE_NAMESPACE: volcano-sh\n306: \n307: permissions:\n308:   contents: read\n309:   packages: write\n310:   id-token: write\n311: \n312: jobs:\n313:   build-and-push-images:\n314:     name: Build and Push Images\n315:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n316:     if: github.event_name == 'push' && startsWith(github.ref, 'refs/tags/v')\n317:     steps:\n318:       - name: Checkout\n319:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n320: \n321:       - name: Setup Docker Buildx\n322:         uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@v3\n323: \n324:       - name: Login to GHCR\n325:         uses: docker/login-action@v3\n326:         with:\n327:           registry: ${{ env.REGISTRY }}\n328:           username: ${{ github.actor }}\n329:           password: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n330: \n331:       - name: Extract metadata\n332:         id: meta\n333:         uses: docker/metadata-action@v5\n334:         with:\n335:           images: |\n336:             ${{ env.REGISTRY }}/${{ env.IMAGE_NAMESPACE }}/workloadmanager\n337:             ${{ env.REGISTRY }}/${{ env.IMAGE_NAMESPACE }}/router\n338:             ${{ env.REGISTRY }}/${{ env.IMAGE_NAMESPACE }}/volcano-agent-scheduler\n339:           tags: |\n340:             type=semver,pattern={{version}}\n341:             type=semver,pattern={{major}}.{{minor}}\n342:             type=sha,prefix=\n343: \n344:       - name: Build and push Workload Manager\n345:         uses: docker/build-push-action@v5\n346:         with:\n347:           context: .\n348:           file: deployment/docker/Dockerfile.workloadmanager\n349:           push: true\n350:           tags: ${{ steps.meta.outputs.tags }}\n351:           platforms: linux/amd64,linux/arm64\n352:           cache-from: type=gha\n353:           cache-to: type=gha,mode=max\n354: \n355:       - name: Build and push Router\n356:         uses: docker/build-push-action@v5\n357:         with:\n358:           context: .\n359:           file: deployment/docker/Dockerfile.router\n360:           push: true\n361:           tags: ${{ steps.meta.outputs.tags }}\n362:           platforms: linux/amd64,linux/arm64\n363:           cache-from: type=gha\n364:           cache-to: type=gha,mode=max\n365: \n366:       - name: Build and push Volcano Agent Scheduler\n367:         uses: docker/build-push-action@v5\n368:         with:\n369:           context: .\n370:           file: deployment/docker/Dockerfile.volcano-agent-scheduler\n371:           push: true\n372:           tags: ${{ steps.meta.outputs.tags }}\n373:           platforms: linux/amd64,linux/arm64\n374:           cache-from: type=gha\n375:           cache-to: type=gha,mode=max\n376: \n377:   publish-helm-chart:\n378:     name: Publish Helm Chart\n379:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n380:     needs: build-and-push-images\n381:     if: github.event_name == 'push' && startsWith(github.ref, 'refs/tags/v')\n382:     steps:\n383:       - name: Checkout\n384:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n385:         with:\n386:           fetch-depth: 0\n387: \n388:       - name: Setup Helm\n389:         uses: azure/setup-helm@v3\n390:         with:\n391:           version: v3.14.0\n392: \n393:       - name: Configure Git\n394:         run: |\n395:           git config user.name \"$GITHUB_ACTOR\"\n396:           git config user.email \"$GITHUB_ACTOR@users.noreply.github.com\"\n397: \n398:       - name: Run chart-releaser\n399:         uses: helm/chart-releaser-action@v1.6.0\n400:         with:\n401:           charts_dir: manifests/\n402:         env:\n403:           CR_TOKEN: \"${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\"\n404: ```\n405: \n406: ### 4. 安全扫描 (security-scan.yml)\n407: \n408: ```yaml\n409: # .github/workflows/security-scan.yml\n410: name: Security Scan\n411: \n412: on:\n413:   push:\n414:     branches: [main, develop]\n415:   pull_request:\n416:     branches: [main]\n417:   schedule:\n418:     - cron: '0 2 * * 1' # Weekly on Monday\n419: \n420: permissions:\n421:   contents: read\n422:   security-events: write\n423:   actions: read\n424: \n425: jobs:\n426:   trivy-scan:\n427:     name: Trivy Container Scan\n428:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n429:     steps:\n430:       - name: Checkout\n431:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n432: \n433:       - name: Build images for scanning\n434:         run: |\n435:           docker build -f deployment/docker/Dockerfile.workloadmanager -t localhost/workloadmanager:scan .\n436:           docker build -f deployment/docker/Dockerfile.router -t localhost/router:scan .\n437:           docker build -f deployment/docker/Dockerfile.volcano-agent-scheduler -t localhost/volcano-agent-scheduler:scan .\n438: \n439:       - name: Run Trivy scanner\n440:         uses: aquasecurity/trivy-action@master\n441:         with:\n442:           image-ref: localhost/workloadmanager:scan\n443:           format: 'sarif'\n444:           output: 'trivy-workloadmanager.sarif'\n445:           severity: 'CRITICAL,HIGH'\n446: \n447:       - name: Upload Trivy results\n448:         uses: github/codeql-action/upload-sarif@v3\n449:         with:\n450:           sarif_file: 'trivy-workloadmanager.sarif'\n451: \n452:   codeql-scan:\n453:     name: CodeQL Code Scan\n454:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n455:     steps:\n456:       - name: Checkout\n457:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n458: \n459:       - name: Setup Go\n460:         uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n461:         with:\n462:           go-version: '1.24'\n463: \n464:       - name: Initialize CodeQL\n465:         uses: github/codeql-action/init@v3\n466:         with:\n467:           languages: go, python\n468:           queries: security-extended\n469: \n470:       - name: Autobuild\n471:         uses: github/codeql-action/autobuild@v3\n472: \n473:       - name: Perform CodeQL Analysis\n474:         uses: github/codeql-action/analyze@v3\n475:         with:\n476:           category: \"/language:go,python\"\n477: \n478:   go-security:\n479:     name: Go Security Scan\n480:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n481:     steps:\n482:       - name: Checkout\n483:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n484: \n485:       - name: Setup Go\n486:         uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n487:         with:\n488:           go-version: '1.24'\n489: \n490:       - name: Run gosec\n491:         uses: securego/gosec@master\n492:         with:\n493:           args: ./...\n494: \n495:   dependency-audit:\n496:     name: Python Dependency Audit\n497:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n498:     steps:\n499:       - name: Checkout\n500:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n501: \n502:       - name: Setup Python\n503:         uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n504:         with:\n505:           python-version: '3.11'\n506: \n507:       - name: Install audit tools\n508:         run: pip install safety pip-audit\n509: \n510:       - name: Run safety check\n511:         run: safety check -r sdk-python/requirements.txt\n512: \n513:       - name: Run pip-audit\n514:         run: pip-audit -r sdk-python/requirements.txt\n515: ```\n516: \n517: ### 5. 文档部署 (docs.yml)\n518: \n519: ```yaml\n520: # .github/workflows/docs.yml\n521: name: Docs\n522: \n523: on:\n524:   push:\n525:     branches: [main]\n526:     paths:\n527:       - 'docs/**'\n528:       - 'website/**'\n529: \n530: permissions:\n531:   contents: read\n532:   pages: write\n533:   id-token: write\n534: \n535: jobs:\n536:   build-and-deploy:\n537:     name: Build and Deploy Docs\n538:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n539:     environment:\n540:       name: github-pages\n541:       url: ${{ steps.deployment.outputs.page_url }}\n542:     steps:\n543:       - name: Checkout\n544:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n545: \n546:       - name: Setup Node.js\n547:         uses: actions/setup-node@v4\n548:         with:\n549:           node-version: '20'\n550:           cache: 'npm'\n551:           cache-dependency-path: website/package-lock.json\n552: \n553:       - name: Install dependencies\n554:         run: cd website && npm ci\n555: \n556:       - name: Build site\n557:         run: cd website && npm run build\n558: \n559:       - name: Setup Pages\n560:         uses: actions/configure-pages@v4\n561: \n562:       - name: Upload artifact\n563:         uses: actions/upload-pages-artifact@v3\n564:         with:\n565:           path: './website/build'\n566: \n567:       - name: Deploy to GitHub Pages\n568:         id: deployment\n569:         uses: actions/deploy-pages@v4\n570: ```\n571: \n572: ### 6. 多架构构建 (multi-arch-build.yml)\n573: \n574: ```yaml\n575: # .github/workflows/multi-arch-build.yml\n576: name: Multi-Arch Build\n577: \n578: on:\n579:   push:\n580:     branches: [main]\n581:     paths:\n582:       - 'cmd/**'\n583:       - 'pkg/**'\n584:       - 'deployment/docker/**'\n585:   pull_request:\n586:     paths:\n587:       - 'cmd/**'\n588:       - 'pkg/**'\n589:       - 'deployment/docker/**'\n590: \n591: permissions:\n592:   contents: read\n593: \n594: jobs:\n595:   build-multi-arch:\n596:     name: Build Multi-Arch Images\n597:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n598:     strategy:\n599:       matrix:\n600:         component: [workloadmanager, router, volcano-agent-scheduler]\n601:         platform: [linux/amd64, linux/arm64]\n602:     steps:\n603:       - name: Checkout\n604:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n605: \n606:       - name: Setup Docker Buildx\n607:         uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@v3\n608: \n609:       - name: Build ${{ matrix.component }} for ${{ matrix.platform }}\n610:         run: |\n611:           docker buildx build \\\n612:             --platform ${{ matrix.platform }} \\\n613:             -t ghcr.io/volcano-sh/${{ matrix.component }}:${{ github.sha }} \\\n614:             --load \\\n615:             -f deployment/docker/Dockerfile.${{ matrix.component }} \\\n616:             .\n617: \n618:       - name: Test image\n619:         run: |\n620:           docker run --rm ghcr.io/volcano-sh/${{ matrix.component }}:${{ github.sha }} --help\n621: ```\n622: \n623: ### 7. 端到端测试 (e2e-test.yml)\n624: \n625: ```yaml\n626: # .github/workflows/e2e-test.yml\n627: name: E2E Test\n628: \n629: on:\n630:   pull_request:\n631:     branches: [main]\n632:     paths:\n633:       - 'cmd/**'\n634:       - 'pkg/**'\n635:       - 'manifests/**'\n636:       - 'testing/**'\n637: \n638: permissions:\n639:   contents: read\n640: \n641: jobs:\n642:   e2e-test:\n643:     name: E2E Test\n644:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n645:     timeout-minutes: 30\n646:     steps:\n647:       - name: Checkout\n648:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n649: \n650:       - name: Setup Go\n651:         uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n652:         with:\n653:           go-version: '1.24'\n654: \n655:       - name: Setup Python\n656:         uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n657:         with:\n658:           python-version: '3.11'\n659: \n660:       - name: Setup Kind\n661:         uses: helm/kind-action@v1.9.0\n662:         with:\n663:           version: v0.20.0\n664:           node_image: kindest/node:v1.28.0\n665: \n666:       - name: Install Redis\n667:         run: |\n668:           kubectl apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bitnami/charts/main/bitnami/redis/templates/deployment.yaml\n669:           kubectl wait --for=condition=available deployment/redis --timeout=120s\n670: \n671:       - name: Install AgentCube\n672:         run: |\n673:           helm install agentcube manifests/ \\\n674:             --set image.repository=localhost:5000 \\\n675:             --set redis.host=redis.default.svc.cluster.local\n676: \n677:       - name: Wait for deployment\n678:         run: |\n679:           kubectl wait --for=condition=available deployment/workloadmanager --timeout=300s\n680:           kubectl wait --for=condition=available deployment/router --timeout=300s\n681: \n682:       - name: Run E2E tests\n683:         run: |\n684:           pip install pytest\n685:           pytest testing/e2e/ -v\n686: \n687:       - name: Collect logs on failure\n688:         if: failure()\n689:         run: |\n690:           kubectl get pods -A\n691:           kubectl logs -l app=workloadmanager\n692:           kubectl logs -l app=router\n693: ```\n694: \n695: ### 8. 夜间构建 (nightly-build.yml)\n696: \n697: ```yaml\n698: # .github/workflows/nightly-build.yml\n699: name: Nightly Build\n700: \n701: on:\n702:   schedule:\n703:     - cron: '0 2 * * *' # Daily at 2 AM UTC\n704:   workflow_dispatch:\n705: \n706: permissions:\n707:   contents: read\n708:   packages: write\n709: \n710: jobs:\n711:   nightly-build:\n712:     name: Nightly Build\n713:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n714:     steps:\n715:       - name: Checkout\n716:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n717: \n718:       - name: Setup Docker Buildx\n719:         uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@v3\n720: \n721:       - name: Login to GHCR\n722:         uses: docker/login-action@v3\n723:         with:\n724:           registry: ghcr.io\n725:           username: ${{ github.actor }}\n726:           password: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n727: \n728:       - name: Build and push nightly images\n729:         run: |\n730:           make docker-build-all\n731:           make docker-push-all\n732:         env:\n733:           DOCKER_TAG: nightly-${{ github.run_id }}\n734: ```\n735: \n736: ### 9. PR 验证 (pr-validation.yml)\n737: \n738: ```yaml\n739: # .github/workflows/pr-validation.yml\n740: name: PR Validation\n741: \n742: on:\n743:   pull_request_target:\n744:     types: [opened, edited, synchronize, reopened, labeled]\n745: \n746: permissions:\n747:   pull-requests: write\n748:   contents: read\n749: \n750: jobs:\n751:   validate-pr-title:\n752:     name: Validate PR Title\n753:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n754:     steps:\n755:       - name: Check PR title\n756:         uses: amannn/action-semantic-pull-request@v5\n757:         env:\n758:           GITHUB_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n759:         with:\n760:           types: |\n761:             feat\n762:             fix\n763:             docs\n764:             style\n765:             refactor\n766:             perf\n767:             test\n768:             build\n769:             ci\n770:             chore\n771:             revert\n772:           requireScope: false\n773: \n774:   validate-pr-body:\n775:     name: Validate PR Body\n776:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n777:     steps:\n778:       - name: Check PR has description\n779:         uses: actions/github-script@v7\n780:         with:\n781:           script: |\n782:             const pr = context.payload.pull_request;\n783:             if (!pr.body || pr.body.trim() === '') {\n784:               core.setFailed('PR description is required');\n785:             }\n786: \n787:   check-issues-linked:\n788:     name: Check Issues Linked\n789:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n790:     steps:\n791:       - name: Check for linked issues\n792:         uses: actions/github-script@v7\n793:         with:\n794:           script: |\n795:             const pr = context.payload.pull_request;\n796:             const body = pr.body || '';\n797:             if (!body.match(/(close|closes|closed|fix|fixes|fixed|resolve|resolves|resolved)\\s#(\\d+)/i)) {\n798:               console.log('No linked issues found (optional)');\n799:             }\n800: ```\n801: \n802: ### 10. Release 发布 (release.yml)\n803: \n804: ```yaml\n805: # .github/workflows/release.yml\n806: name: Release\n807: \n808: on:\n809:   push:\n810:     tags:\n811:       - 'v*'\n812: \n813: permissions:\n814:   contents: write\n815:   packages: write\n816:   id-token: write\n817: \n818: jobs:\n819:   create-release:\n820:     name: Create Release\n821:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n822:     outputs:\n823:       upload_url: ${{ steps.create_release.outputs.upload_url }}\n824:       version: ${{ steps.get_version.outputs.version }}\n825:     steps:\n826:       - name: Checkout\n827:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n828:         with:\n829:           fetch-depth: 0\n830: \n831:       - name: Get version\n832:         id: get_version\n833:         run: echo \"version=${GITHUB_REF#refs/tags/}\" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT\n834: \n835:       - name: Generate changelog\n836:         uses: mikepenz/release-changelog-builder-action@v4\n837:         id: changelog\n838:         with:\n839:           configuration: .github/release-config.json\n840: \n841:       - name: Create Release\n842:         id: create_release\n843:         uses: softprops/action-gh-release@v1\n844:         with:\n845:           body: ${{ steps.changelog.outputs.changelog }}\n846:           draft: false\n847:           prerelease: false\n848:         env:\n849:           GITHUB_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n850: \n851:   publish-python-sdk:\n852:     name: Publish Python SDK\n853:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n854:     needs: create-release\n855:     steps:\n856:       - name: Checkout\n857:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n858: \n859:       - name: Setup Python\n860:         uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n861:         with:\n862:           python-version: '3.11'\n863: \n864:       - name: Install build tools\n865:         run: pip install build twine\n866: \n867:       - name: Build package\n868:         run: python -m build sdk-python/\n869: \n870:       - name: Publish to PyPI\n871:         uses: pypa/gh-action-pypi-publish@release/v1\n872:         with:\n873:           packages-dir: sdk-python/dist/\n874:           password: ${{ secrets.PYPI_API_TOKEN }}\n875: \n876:   publish-cli-tool:\n877:     name: Publish CLI Tool\n878:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n879:     needs: create-release\n880:     steps:\n881:       - name: Checkout\n882:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n883: \n884:       - name: Setup Python\n885:         uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n886:         with:\n887:           python-version: '3.11'\n888: \n889:       - name: Install build tools\n890:         run: pip install build twine\n891: \n892:       - name: Build CLI\n893:         run: python -m build cmd/cli/\n894: \n895:       - name: Publish to PyPI\n896:         uses: pypa/gh-action-pypi-publish@release/v1\n897:         with:\n898:           packages-dir: cmd/cli/dist/\n899:           password: ${{ secrets.PYPI_API_TOKEN }}\n900: \n901:   sign-artifacts:\n902:     name: Sign Artifacts\n903:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n904:     needs: create-release\n905:     steps:\n906:       - name: Checkout\n907:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n908: \n909:       - name: Setup cosign\n910:         uses: sigstore/cosign-installer@v3\n911: \n912:       - name: Sign images\n913:         run: |\n914:           cosign sign ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager:${{ needs.create-release.outputs.version }}\n915:           cosign sign ghcr.io/volcano-sh/router:${{ needs.create-release.outputs.version }}\n916:           cosign sign ghcr.io/volcano-sh/volcano-agent-scheduler:${{ needs.create-release.outputs.version }}\n917:         env:\n918:           COSIGN_EXPERIMENTAL: \"true\"\n919: ```\n920: \n921: ### 11. 依赖审查 (dependency-review.yml)\n922: \n923: ```yaml\n924: # .github/workflows/dependency-review.yml\n925: name: Dependency Review\n926: \n927: on:\n928:   pull_request:\n929:     branches: [main, develop]\n930: \n931: permissions:\n932:   contents: read\n933: \n934: jobs:\n935:   dependency-review:\n936:     name: Dependency Review\n937:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n938:     steps:\n939:       - name: Checkout\n940:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n941: \n942:       - name: Dependency Review\n943:         uses: actions/dependency-review-action@v4\n944:         with:\n945:           fail-on-severity: high\n946:           deny-licenses: GPL-3.0, AGPL-3.0\n947: \n948:   go-dependency-check:\n949:     name: Go Dependency Check\n950:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n951:     steps:\n952:       - name: Checkout\n953:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n954: \n955:       - name: Setup Go\n956:         uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n957:         with:\n958:           go-version: '1.24'\n959: \n960:       - name: Run govulncheck\n961:         run: |\n962:           go install golang.org/x/vuln/cmd/govulncheck@latest\n963:           govulncheck ./...\n964: \n965:   python-dependency-check:\n966:     name: Python Dependency Check\n967:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n968:     steps:\n969:       - name: Checkout\n970:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n971: \n972:       - name: Setup Python\n973:         uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n974:         with:\n975:           python-version: '3.11'\n976: \n977:       - name: Run pip-audit\n978:         run: |\n979:           pip install pip-audit\n980:           pip-audit -r sdk-python/requirements.txt\n981:           pip-audit -r cmd/cli/requirements.txt\n982: ```\n983: \n984: ### 12. Stale 管理 (stale.yml)\n985: \n986: ```yaml\n987: # .github/workflows/stale.yml\n988: name: Stale\n989: \n990: on:\n991:   schedule:\n992:     - cron: '0 0 * * *' # Daily\n993:   workflow_dispatch:\n994: \n995: permissions:\n996:   issues: write\n997:   pull-requests: write\n998: \n999: jobs:\n1000:   stale:\n1001:     name: Close Stale Issues and PRs\n1002:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n1003:     steps:\n1004:       - name: Close stale issues and PRs\n1005:         uses: actions/stale@v9\n1006:         with:\n1007:           stale-issue-message: 'This issue has been automatically marked as stale because it has not had recent activity. It will be closed if no further activity occurs.'\n1008:           stale-pr-message: 'This PR has been automatically marked as stale because it has not had recent activity. It will be closed if no further activity occurs.'\n1009:           close-issue-message: 'This issue was closed because it has been stalled for 30 days with no activity.'\n1010:           close-pr-message: 'This PR was closed because it has been stalled for 30 days with no activity.'\n1011:           days-before-issue-stale: 60\n1012:           days-before-pr-stale: 30\n1013:           days-before-issue-close: 90\n1014:           days-before-pr-close: 60\n1015:           exempt-issue-labels: 'bug,enhancement,help wanted,good first issue'\n1016:           exempt-pr-labels: 'bug,enhancement,help wanted'\n1017:           stale-issue-label: 'stale'\n1018:           stale-pr-label: 'stale'\n1019:           remove-stale-when-updated: true\n1020:           operations-per-run: 100\n1021: ```\n1022: \n1023: ### 13. 自动标签 (labeler.yml)\n1024: \n1025: ```yaml\n1026: # .github/workflows/labeler.yml\n1027: name: Labeler\n1028: \n1029: on:\n1030:   - pull_request_target\n1031: \n1032: permissions:\n1033:   contents: read\n1034:   pull-requests: write\n1035: \n1036: jobs:\n1037:   label:\n1038:     name: Apply Labels\n1039:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n1040:     steps:\n1041:       - name: Apply Labels\n1042:         uses: actions/labeler@v5\n1043:         with:\n1044:           repo-token: \"${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\"\n1045:           configuration-path: .github/labeler.yml\n1046: ```\n1047: \n1048: ### 14. Dependabot 配置 (dependabot.yml)\n1049: \n1050: ```yaml\n1051: # .github/dependabot.yml\n1052: version: 2\n1053: updates:\n1054:   # Go dependencies\n1055:   - package-ecosystem: \"gomod\"\n1056:     directory: \"/\"\n1057:     schedule:\n1058:       interval: \"weekly\"\n1059:       day: \"monday\"\n1060:       time: \"02:00\"\n1061:     open-pull-requests-limit: 10\n1062:     labels:\n1063:       - \"dependencies\"\n1064:       - \"go\"\n1065:     commit-message:\n1066:       prefix: \"chore(go)\"\n1067:       include: \"scope\"\n1068:     groups:\n1069:       k8s-io:\n1070:         patterns:\n1071:           - \"k8s.io/*\"\n1072:           - \"sigs.k8s.io/*\"\n1073:       volcano:\n1074:         patterns:\n1075:           - \"volcano.sh/*\"\n1076: \n1077:   # Python dependencies\n1078:   - package-ecosystem: \"pip\"\n1079:     directory: \"/sdk-python\"\n1080:     schedule:\n1081:       interval: \"weekly\"\n1082:       day: \"monday\"\n1083:       time: \"02:00\"\n1084:     open-pull-requests-limit: 10\n1085:     labels:\n1086:       - \"dependencies\"\n1087:       - \"python\"\n1088:     commit-message:\n1089:       prefix: \"chore(python)\"\n1090:       include: \"scope\"\n1091: \n1092:   - package-ecosystem: \"pip\"\n1093:     directory: \"/cmd/cli\"\n1094:     schedule:\n1095:       interval: \"weekly\"\n1096:       day: \"monday\"\n1097:       time: \"02:00\"\n1098:     open-pull-requests-limit: 10\n1099:     labels:\n1100:       - \"dependencies\"\n1101:       - \"python\"\n1102:     commit-message:\n1103:       prefix: \"chore(cli)\"\n1104:       include: \"scope\"\n1105: \n1106:   # GitHub Actions\n1107:   - package-ecosystem: \"github-actions\"\n1108:     directory: \"/\"\n1109:     schedule:\n1110:       interval: \"weekly\"\n1111:       day: \"monday\"\n1112:       time: \"02:00\"\n1113:     open-pull-requests-limit: 10\n1114:     labels:\n1115:       - \"dependencies\"\n1116:       - \"github-actions\"\n1117:     commit-message:\n1118:       prefix: \"chore(actions)\"\n1119:       include: \"scope\"\n1120: \n1121:   # Docker\n1122:   - package-ecosystem: \"docker\"\n1123:     directory: \"/deployment/docker\"\n1124:     schedule:\n1125:       interval: \"weekly\"\n1126:       day: \"monday\"\n1127:       time: \"02:00\"\n1128:     open-pull-requests-limit: 5\n1129:     labels:\n1130:       - \"dependencies\"\n1131:       - \"docker\"\n1132:     commit-message:\n1133:       prefix: \"chore(docker)\"\n1134:       include: \"scope\"\n1135: ```\n1136: \n1137: ### 15. 标签规则 (labeler.yml)\n1138: \n1139: ```yaml\n1140: # .github/labeler.yml\n1141: # Automatically apply labels to PRs based on file patterns\n1142: \n1143: go:\n1144:   - changed-files:\n1145:       - any-glob-to-any-file:\n1146:           - cmd/**/*.go\n1147:           - pkg/**/*.go\n1148:           - \"*.go\"\n1149:           - go.mod\n1150:           - go.sum\n1151: \n1152: python:\n1153:   - changed-files:\n1154:       - any-glob-to-any-file:\n1155:           - sdk-python/**/*.py\n1156:           - cmd/cli/**/*.py\n1157:           - \"**/requirements.txt\"\n1158: \n1159: documentation:\n1160:   - changed-files:\n1161:       - any-glob-to-any-file:\n1162:           - docs/**/*\n1163:           - website/**/*\n1164:           - \"*.md\"\n1165:           - README.md\n1166: \n1167: helm:\n1168:   - changed-files:\n1169:       - any-glob-to-any-file:\n1170:           - manifests/**/*.yaml\n1171:           - manifests/**/*.tpl\n1172:           - manifests/Chart.yaml\n1173:           - manifests/values.yaml\n1174: \n1175: docker:\n1176:   - changed-files:\n1177:       - any-glob-to-any-file:\n1178:           - deployment/docker/**/*\n1179:           - \"**/Dockerfile*\"\n1180:           - .dockerignore\n1181: \n1182: ci-cd:\n1183:   - changed-files:\n1184:       - any-glob-to-any-file:\n1185:           - .github/workflows/**/*\n1186:           - .github/dependabot.yml\n1187:           - .github/labeler.yml\n1188: \n1189: tests:\n1190:   - changed-files:\n1191:       - any-glob-to-any-file:\n1192:           - testing/**/*\n1193:           - \"**/*_test.go\"\n1194:           - \"**/test_*.py\"\n1195: \n1196: configuration:\n1197:   - changed-files:\n1198:       - any-glob-to-any-file:\n1199:           - \"*.yaml\"\n1200:           - \"*.yml\"\n1201:           - \"*.toml\"\n1202:           - Makefile\n1203:           - .golangci.yml\n1204: ```\n1205: \n1206: ### 16. 代码所有者 (CODEOWNERS)\n1207: \n1208: ```\n1209: # .github/CODEOWNERS\n1210: # Code owners for automatic review assignment\n1211: \n1212: # Default owners\n1213: * @agentcube-maintainers\n1214: \n1215: # Go code\n1216: /cmd/ @agentcube-go-team\n1217: /pkg/ @agentcube-go-team\n1218: \n1219: # Python SDK and CLI\n1220: /sdk-python/ @agentcube-python-team\n1221: /cmd/cli/ @agentcube-python-team\n1222: \n1223: # Kubernetes manifests\n1224: /manifests/ @agentcube-k8s-team\n1225: \n1226: # Documentation\n1227: /docs/ @agentcube-docs-team\n1228: /website/ @agentcube-docs-team\n1229: \n1230: # CI/CD\n1231: .github/ @agentcube-devops-team\n1232: \n1233: # Docker\n1234: /deployment/docker/ @agentcube-devops-team\n1235: \n1236: # Tests\n1237: /testing/ @agentcube-qa-team\n1238: ```\n1239: \n1240: ## Impact Analysis\n1241: \n1242: ### 依赖影响\n1243: \n1244: | 依赖项 | 版本 | 用途 |\n1245: |--------|------|------|\n1246: | GitHub Actions | - | CI/CD 平台 |\n1247: | Go | 1.24 | 应用编译 |\n1248: | Python | 3.11 | SDK/CLI 构建 |\n1249: | Node.js | 20 | 文档构建 |\n1250: | Docker | 预装 | 镜像构建 |\n1251: | Helm | 3.14+ | Chart 打包 |\n1252: | Kind | 0.20+ | E2E 测试集群 |\n1253: | Trivy | latest | 安全扫描 |\n1254: | CodeQL | v3 | 代码分析 |\n1255: \n1256: ### 模块依赖关系\n1257: \n1258: ```\n1259: .github/\n1260: ├── workflows/\n1261: │   ├── ci.yml                      # 依赖：Go, Python, Helm, Redis\n1262: │   ├── cd.yml                      # 依赖：AR-032 (Dockerfile), AR-033 (Makefile)\n1263: │   ├── security-scan.yml           # 依赖：Trivy, CodeQL, gosec\n1264: │   ├── docs.yml                    # 依赖：Node.js, Docusaurus\n1265: │   ├── multi-arch-build.yml        # 依赖：Docker Buildx\n1266: │   ├── e2e-test.yml                # 依赖：Kind, Helm, Redis\n1267: │   ├── nightly-build.yml           # 依赖：AR-033 (Makefile)\n1268: │   ├── pr-validation.yml           # 依赖：GitHub API\n1269: │   ├── release.yml                 # 依赖：PyPI, GHCR, cosign\n1270: │   ├── dependency-review.yml       # 依赖：govulncheck, pip-audit\n1271: │   ├── stale.yml                   # 依赖：GitHub API\n1272: │   └── labeler.yml                 # 依赖：labeler action\n1273: ├── dependabot.yml                  # 依赖：GitHub API\n1274: ├── labeler.yml                     # 依赖：labeler action\n1275: └── CODEOWNERS                      # 依赖：GitHub teams\n1276: ```\n1277: \n1278: ### 向后兼容性\n1279: \n1280: - 首次实现，无破坏性变更\n1281: - 工作流设计为增量式采纳，团队可选择性启用\n1282: - 依赖自动更新（Dependabot）确保 Action 版本更新\n1283: \n1284: ### 成本影响\n1285: \n1286: | 资源 | 月度估算 | 备注 |\n1287: |------|----------|------|\n1288: | GitHub Actions Minutes | 3000 分钟 | 免费额度 2000 分钟/月，超出需付费 |\n1289: | Storage (Packages) | 5 GB | GHCR 存储，免费 50GB |\n1290: | Actions Runners | Self-hosted (可选) | 减少成本，提高速度 |\n1291: \n1292: ### 安全影响\n1293: \n1294: - **Positive**: 自动化安全扫描，及时检测漏洞\n1295: - **Positive**: 依赖审查，阻止不安全依赖\n1296: - **Positive**: CodeQL 分析，发现代码安全问题\n1297: - **Consideration**: GHCR Token 权限管理，需最小权限原则\n1298: - **Consideration**: PyPI Token 存储，需使用 GitHub Secrets\n1299: \n1300: ## Alternatives Considered\n1301: \n1302: ### 方案 1: 使用 CircleCI 替代 GitHub Actions\n1303: \n1304: **优点:**\n1305: - 更灵活的配置选项\n1306: - 更好的并行执行能力\n1307: - 更便宜的定价\n1308: \n1309: **缺点:**\n1310: - 需要额外注册和配置\n1311: - 与 GitHub 集成度低\n1312: - 学习成本增加\n1313: \n1314: **决策:** 使用 GitHub Actions，保持与 GitHub 深度集成。\n1315: \n1316: ### 方案 2: 使用 Jenkins 自建 CI/CD\n1317: \n1318: **优点:**\n1319: - 完全控制\n1320: - 无使用限制\n1321: - 丰富的插件生态\n1322: \n1323: **缺点:**\n1324: - 维护成本高\n1325: - 需要基础设施\n1326: - 配置复杂\n1327: \n1328: **决策:** 使用 GitHub Actions，减少运维负担。\n1329: \n1330: ### 方案 3: 单个工作流文件（monolithic workflow）\n1331: \n1332: **优点:**\n1333: - 配置集中\n1334: - 易于理解整体流程\n1335: \n1336: **缺点:**\n1337: - 文件过大难以维护\n1338: - 无法独立触发/调试\n1339: - 执行效率低\n1340: \n1341: **决策:** 采用模块化设计，每个工作流独立职责。\n1342: \n1343: ### 方案 4: 使用 GitLab CI/CD\n1344: \n1345: **优点:**\n1346: - 原生集成 GitLab\n1347: - 强大的 YAML 语法\n1348: - 免费额度较高\n1349: \n1350: **缺点:**\n1351: - 需要迁移代码仓库\n1352: - 团队学习成本\n1353: - 生态锁定\n1354: \n1355: **决策:** 保持 GitHub，使用 GitHub Actions。\n1356: \n1357: ### 方案 5: 手动发布流程\n1358: \n1359: **优点:**\n1360: - 完全控制发布过程\n1361: - 无需配置工作流\n1362: \n1363: **缺点:**\n1364: - 容易出错\n1365: - 无法追溯\n1366: - 效率低下\n1367: \n1368: **决策:** 自动化发布，提高可靠性和效率。\n1369: \n1370: ## Testing Strategy\n1371: \n1372: ### 工作流验证\n1373: \n1374: 1. **语法验证** - 使用 `actionlint` 验证 YAML 语法\n1375: 2. **本地测试** - 使用 `act` 工具在本地运行工作流\n1376: 3. **Dry Run** - 在 PR 中测试工作流触发\n1377: \n1378: ### 集成测试\n1379: \n1380: 1. **CI 流水线测试** - 验证 lint, test, build 全部通过\n1381: 2. **CD 流水线测试** - 在 staging 环境验证发布\n1382: 3. **E2E 测试** - 验证 Kind 集群中完整部署\n1383: \n1384: ### 安全测试\n1385: \n1386: 1. **权限验证** - 验证 GITHUB_TOKEN 权限最小化\n1387: 2. **Secret 测试** - 验证 Secrets 未被泄露\n1388: 3. **依赖扫描** - 验证 Trivy/CodeQL 能检测问题\n1389: \n1390: ### 性能测试\n1391: \n1392: 1. **并行执行测试** - 验证并发作业不冲突\n1393: 2. **缓存测试** - 验证 Docker/Go 缓存命中率\n1394: 3. **超时测试** - 验证长运行作业有超时保护\n1395: \n1396: ### 测试覆盖目标\n1397: \n1398: - 工作流语法：100% 有效\n1399: - CI 触发：100%（push, PR）\n1400: - CD 触发：100%（tag）\n1401: - 安全扫描：100%（定期 + PR）\n1402: - 文档部署：100%（main 分支）\n1403: \n1404: ## Acceptance Criteria\n1405: \n1406: - [ ] `ci.yml` 在 PR 和 push 事件中成功触发\n1407: - [ ] `cd.yml` 在 tag 推送时成功发布镜像\n1408: - [ ] `security-scan.yml` 成功运行 Trivy 和 CodeQL\n1409: - [ ] `docs.yml` 成功部署文档到 GitHub Pages\n1410: - [ ] `multi-arch-build.yml` 成功构建 amd64 和 arm64 镜像\n1411: - [ ] `e2e-test.yml` 在 Kind 集群中成功运行 E2E 测试\n1412: - [ ] `nightly-build.yml` 按计划触发夜间构建\n1413: - [ ] `pr-validation.yml` 验证 PR 标题和描述\n1414: - [ ] `release.yml` 成功创建 GitHub Release 并发布 PyPI 包\n1415: - [ ] `dependency-review.yml` 成功检测依赖漏洞\n1416: - [ ] `stale.yml` 成功标记和关闭 stale 问题/PR\n1417: - [ ] `labeler.yml` 成功自动应用标签\n1418: - [ ] `dependabot.yml` 成功创建依赖更新 PR\n1419: - [ ] `labeler.yml` 文件规则正确匹配\n1420: - [ ] `CODEOWNERS` 正确分配审查者\n1421: - [ ] 所有工作流通过语法验证（actionlint）\n1422: - [ ] 所有 Secrets 配置正确\n1423: - [ ] 文档完整（使用说明、故障排查）\n1424: \n1425: ## Dependencies\n1426: \n1427: ### 必需依赖\n1428: - GitHub 仓库\n1429: - GitHub Actions 启用\n1430: - GHCR 访问权限\n1431: - PyPI 账号（发布 SDK/CLI）\n1432: \n1433: ### 可选依赖\n1434: - Codecov 账号（测试覆盖率）\n1435: - Self-hosted Runner（可选，降低成本）\n1436: - Slack/Discord Webhook（通知）\n1437: \n1438: ### 被依赖\n1439: - AR-032 (Dockerfile 多阶段构建) - 提供 Dockerfile\n1440: - AR-033 (Makefile 构建目标) - 提供 make 命令\n1441: - AR-030 (Helm Chart) - 提供 manifests/\n1442: \n1443: ## Migration Notes\n1444: \n1445: ### 从零到 CI/CD\n1446: \n1447: 1. **初始设置**\n1448:    - 创建 `.github/workflows/` 目录\n1449:    - 复制所有工作流文件\n1450:    - 配置 Dependabot 和 CODEOWNERS\n1451: \n1452: 2. **配置 Secrets**\n1453:    ```bash\n1454:    # 必需配置\n1455:    GITHUB_TOKEN (自动提供)\n1456:    PYPI_API_TOKEN (PyPI 发布)\n1457:    ```\n1458: \n1459: 3. **启用工作流**\n1460:    - 检查 GitHub Settings → Actions\n1461:    - 确保 Actions 已启用\n1462:    - 配置权限设置\n1463: \n1464: 4. **首次运行**\n1465:    - 创建测试 PR 验证 CI\n1466:    - 创建测试 tag 验证 CD\n1467:    - 检查所有工作流运行状态\n1468: \n1469: ### 破坏性变更\n1470: 无 - 首次实现。\n1471: \n1472: ### 行为变更\n1473: - PR 必须通过 CI 检查才能合并\n1474: - Tag 推送自动触发发布\n1475: - 依赖自动更新\n1476: \n1477: ## Open Questions\n1478: \n1479: 1. 是否需要集成 Slack/Discord 通知？\n1480: 2. 是否需要支持多环境部署（dev/staging/prod）？\n1481: 3. 是否需要配置自托管 Runner 以降低成本？\n1482: 4. 是否需要集成 SonarQube 代码质量分析？\n1483: 5. 是否需要配置性能基准测试？\n1484: \n1485: ## References\n1486: \n1487: - `project.md` - AgentCube 项目上下文\n1488: - `changes/AR-032/proposal.md` - Dockerfile 多阶段构建\n1489: - `changes/AR-033/proposal.md` - Makefile 构建目标\n1490: - GitHub Actions Documentation: https://docs.github.com/en/actions\n1491: - GitHub Actions Marketplace: https://github.com/marketplace?type=actions\n1492: - Trivy Documentation: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/\n1493: - CodeQL Documentation: https://codeql.github.com/\n1494: - Dependabot Documentation: https://docs.github.com/en/code-security/dependabot\n\n(End of file - total 1494 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n\n## Purpose\n\n本提案实现 AgentCube 项目的 GitHub Actions CI/CD 流水线体系，为代码质量、构建验证、镜像发布、安全扫描提供自动化流水线。该 CI/CD 体系是 AgentCube 工程化实践的核心基础设施，支撑持续集成、持续交付、质量门禁全流程。\n\n目标是：\n\n1. **代码质量门禁** - 在 PR 和 push 事件中自动运行 lint、typecheck、test，确保代码质量\n2. **构建验证** - 验证 Go 和 Python 代码可编译，Docker 镜像可构建\n3. **多架构支持** - 构建 amd64、arm64 多架构 Docker 镜像，支持异构集群\n4. **镜像发布** - 自动推送镜像到 GHCR，支持版本标签管理（latest, commit-sha, semver）\n5. **安全扫描** - 集成 Trivy 扫描镜像漏洞，集成 CodeQL 扫描代码安全问题\n6. **文档站点** - 自动构建和部署 Docusaurus 文档到 GitHub Pages\n7. **发布自动化** - 创建 GitHub Release，生成变更日志，上传构建产物\n8. **依赖更新** - 自动检测依赖更新，创建 Dependabot PR\n\n本提案基于 AR-032（Dockerfile 多阶段构建）、AR-033（Makefile 构建目标）实现，遵循 GitHub Actions 最佳实践和 AgentCube 工程规范。\n\n## Scope","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-034/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775883254906,"end":1775883254923}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883254931,"sessionID":"ses_2851c7184ffeDepVkFukH2kBxM","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae3ed30001H2zyOmafsKekwm","messageID":"msg_d7ae3e2e4001MzA6tF5Z0JQXi4","sessionID":"ses_2851c7184ffeDepVkFukH2kBxM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a2b26c687a50431c97a2d074","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-034/spec/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-034/spec/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 Workflows)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `.github/workflows`  \n6: **Language:** YAML  \n7: **Size:** L  \n8: **Type:** GitHub Actions workflows for CI/CD automation (build, lint, test, e2e, codegen, copyright, codespell, release, approval)\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** ci-cd/design.md, ci-cd/spec.md\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-034.1: Agentcube CI Workflow (main.yml)\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that builds the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: PR triggers workflow\n21: - **GIVEN** a pull request is opened or updated targeting `main` or `release-*`\n22: - **WHEN** the PR event occurs\n23: - **THEN** the \"Agentcube CI Workflow\" SHALL be triggered\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Checkout repository\n26: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n27: - **WHEN** the job starts\n28: - **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository code\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Setup Docker Buildx\n31: - **GIVEN** repository is checked out\n32: - **WHEN** job continues\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL set up Docker Buildx\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Verify Docker availability\n36: - **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is set up\n37: - **WHEN** job continues\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL verify `docker` and `buildx` versions\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Execute docker-build\n41: - **GIVEN** Docker is available\n42: - **WHEN** build step runs\n43: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `make docker-build`\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ### REQ-034.2: E2E Tests Workflow (e2e.yml)\n48: \n49: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that runs end-to-end tests on Kind Kubernetes cluster for pull requests to `main` or `release-*` branches.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: PR triggers e2e workflow\n52: - **GIVEN** a pull request is opened or updated targeting `main` or `release-*`\n53: - **WHEN** the PR event occurs\n54: - **THEN** the \"Agentcube E2E Tests\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Setup Go environment\n57: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n58: - **WHEN** the job starts\n59: - **THEN** it SHALL set up Go version 1.23\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Install Kind cluster\n62: - **GIVEN** Go is ready\n63: - **WHEN** Kind action runs\n64: - **THEN** it SHALL install Kind v0.30.0 with `install_only: true` and cluster name `agentcube-e2e`\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Set artifacts path\n67: - **GIVEN** Kind is installed\n68: - **WHEN** environment is configured\n69: - **THEN** `ARTIFACTS_PATH` SHALL be set to `${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Run e2e tests\n72: - **GIVEN** cluster is ready\n73: - **WHEN** test step runs\n74: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `make e2e`\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Upload failure logs\n77: - **GIVEN** e2e tests fail\n78: - **WHEN** failure occurs\n79: - **THEN** it SHALL upload `e2e-logs/` directory as artifact\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Clean up cluster\n82: - **GIVEN** tests complete (pass or fail)\n83: - **WHEN** job finishes\n84: - **THEN** it SHALL always run `make e2e-clean`\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ### REQ-034.3: Lint Workflow (lint.yml)\n89: \n90: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that runs `golangci-lint` when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: PR triggers lint workflow\n93: - **GIVEN** a pull request targets `main` or `release-*`\n94: - **WHEN** the PR event occurs\n95: - **THEN** the \"Lint\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Path filter for Go files\n98: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n99: - **WHEN** paths-filter action runs\n100: - **THEN** it SHALL match `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: Setup Go for linting\n103: - **GIVEN** path filter indicates changes\n104: - **WHEN** lint job continues\n105: - **THEN** it SHALL set up Go version 1.24\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Run golangci-lint\n108: - **GIVEN** Go is ready\n109: - **WHEN** lint step runs\n110: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `make lint`\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: No Go changes\n113: - **GIVEN** path filter indicates no Go-related changes\n114: - **WHEN** workflow runs\n115: - **THEN** lint step SHALL be skipped\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ### REQ-034.4: Python SDK Tests Workflow (python-sdk-tests.yml)\n120: \n121: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that runs pytest for the Python SDK when `sdk-python/**` paths change.\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: PR triggers Python SDK workflow\n124: - **GIVEN** a pull request or merge_group event occurs\n125: - **WHEN** the event targets the repository\n126: - **THEN** the \"Python SDK Tests\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Path filter for SDK files\n129: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n130: - **WHEN** paths-filter action runs\n131: - **THEN** it SHALL match `sdk-python/**`\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Setup Python environment\n134: - **GIVEN** path filter indicates SDK changes\n135: - **WHEN** job continues\n136: - **THEN** it SHALL set up Python 3.12 with working directory `sdk-python`\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Install pytest\n139: - **GIVEN** Python is ready\n140: - **WHEN** dependency step runs\n141: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `pip install pytest`\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Install SDK in editable mode\n144: - **GIVEN** pytest is installed\n145: - **WHEN** install step runs\n146: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `pip install -e .`\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Run pytest\n149: - **GIVEN** SDK is installed\n150: - **WHEN** test step runs\n151: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: No SDK changes\n154: - **GIVEN** path filter indicates no SDK changes\n155: - **WHEN** workflow runs\n156: - **THEN** test steps SHALL be skipped\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: ### REQ-034.5: Python Lint Workflow (python-lint.yml)\n161: \n162: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that runs Ruff linting when Python-related paths change.\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: PR triggers Python lint workflow\n165: - **GIVEN** a pull request targets `main` or `release-*`\n166: - **WHEN** the PR event occurs\n167: - **THEN** the \"Python Lint\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Path filter for Python files\n170: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n171: - **WHEN** paths-filter action runs\n172: - **THEN** it SHALL match `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, or the workflow file itself\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Setup Python for linting\n175: - **GIVEN** path filter indicates changes\n176: - **WHEN** job continues\n177: - **THEN** it SHALL set up Python 3.10\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Install Ruff\n180: - **GIVEN** Python is ready\n181: - **WHEN** dependency step runs\n182: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `pip install ruff`\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: Run Ruff check\n185: - **GIVEN** Ruff is installed\n186: - **WHEN** lint step runs\n187: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: No Python changes\n190: - **GIVEN** path filter indicates no Python-related changes\n191: - **WHEN** workflow runs\n192: - **THEN** lint steps SHALL be skipped\n193: \n194: ---\n195: \n196: ### REQ-034.6: Test Coverage Workflow (test-coverage.yml)\n197: \n198: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that runs race-enabled Go tests with coverage reporting on `pkg/...` for pull requests, merge groups, or workflow calls.\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Multiple triggers for coverage\n201: - **GIVEN** a `pull_request`, `merge_group`, or `workflow_call` event occurs\n202: - **WHEN** the event targets the repository\n203: - **THEN** the \"Test Coverage\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n204: \n205: #### Scenario: Path filter for coverage\n206: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n207: - **WHEN** paths-filter action runs\n208: - **THEN** it SHALL match `**` excluding `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: Free disk space\n211: - **GIVEN** path filter indicates changes\n212: - **WHEN** job starts\n213: - **THEN** it SHALL free disk space on the runner\n214: \n215: #### Scenario: Setup Go for tests\n216: - **GIVEN** disk space is ready\n217: - **WHEN** job continues\n218: - **THEN** it SHALL set up Go version 1.24\n219: \n220: #### Scenario: Run Go tests with coverage\n221: - **GIVEN** Go is ready\n222: - **WHEN** test step runs\n223: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n224: \n225: #### Scenario: Upload coverage to Codecov\n226: - **GIVEN** coverage report is generated\n227: - **WHEN** upload step runs\n228: - **THEN** it SHALL upload `coverage.out` to Codecov (using `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` if available)\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: Upload coverage artifact\n231: - **GIVEN** coverage report exists\n232: - **WHEN** artifact step runs\n233: - **THEN** it SHALL upload `go-coverage` artifact\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: Write to step summary\n236: - **GIVEN** tests complete\n237: - **WHEN** summary step runs\n238: - **THEN** it SHALL write coverage results to GitHub step summary\n239: \n240: ---\n241: \n242: ### REQ-034.7: Codegen Check Workflow (codegen-check.yml)\n243: \n244: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that verifies generated artifacts match `make gen-all` when API, hack, workflow, or Makefile inputs change.\n245: \n246: #### Scenario: PR triggers codegen workflow\n247: - **GIVEN** a pull request targets `main` or `release-*`\n248: - **WHEN** the PR event occurs\n249: - **THEN** the \"Codegen Check\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n250: \n251: #### Scenario: Path filter for codegen\n252: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n253: - **WHEN** paths-filter action runs\n254: - **THEN** it SHALL match `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, or `Makefile`\n255: \n256: #### Scenario: Setup Go for codegen\n257: - **GIVEN** path filter indicates changes\n258: - **WHEN** job continues\n259: - **THEN** it SHALL set up Go version 1.24.4\n260: \n261: #### Scenario: Run gen-check\n262: - **GIVEN** Go is ready\n263: - **WHEN** check step runs\n264: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `make gen-check` (runs `gen-all` then `git diff --exit-code`)\n265: \n266: #### Scenario: Generated code out of date\n267: - **GIVEN** `make gen-all` produces changes\n268: - **WHEN** `git diff --exit-code` runs\n269: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL fail indicating generated code is stale\n270: \n271: #### Scenario: No codegen-related changes\n272: - **GIVEN** path filter indicates no relevant changes\n273: - **WHEN** workflow runs\n274: - **THEN** check steps SHALL be skipped\n275: \n276: ---\n277: \n278: ### REQ-034.8: Copyright Check Workflow (copyright-check.yml)\n279: \n280: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that ensures `make gen-copyright` produces no git diff when applicable files change.\n281: \n282: #### Scenario: PR triggers copyright workflow\n283: - **GIVEN** a pull request targets `main` or `release-*`\n284: - **WHEN** the PR event occurs\n285: - **THEN** the \"Copyright Check\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n286: \n287: #### Scenario: Path filter for copyright\n288: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n289: - **WHEN** paths-filter action runs\n290: - **THEN** it SHALL match all files excluding `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**`\n291: \n292: #### Scenario: Install moreutils\n293: - **GIVEN** path filter indicates changes\n294: - **WHEN** job starts\n295: - **THEN** it SHALL install `moreutils` package (for `sponge` command)\n296: \n297: #### Scenario: Run gen-copyright\n298: - **GIVEN** moreutils is installed\n299: - **WHEN** generate step runs\n300: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `make gen-copyright`\n301: \n302: #### Scenario: Verify no diff\n303: - **GIVEN** copyright headers are generated\n304: - **WHEN** diff step runs\n305: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `git diff --exit-code`\n306: \n307: #### Scenario: Copyright headers missing\n308: - **GIVEN** files lack proper copyright headers\n309: - **WHEN** `git diff --exit-code` runs\n310: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL fail indicating missing copyright headers\n311: \n312: #### Scenario: No copyright-relevant changes\n313: - **GIVEN** path filter indicates no relevant changes\n314: - **WHEN** workflow runs\n315: - **THEN** check steps SHALL be skipped\n316: \n317: ---\n318: \n319: ### REQ-034.9: Codespell Workflow (codespell.yml)\n320: \n321: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that runs codespell spell-checking on pull requests to `main` or `release-*` branches.\n322: \n323: #### Scenario: PR triggers codespell workflow\n324: - **GIVEN** a pull request targets `main` or `release-*`\n325: - **WHEN** the PR event occurs\n326: - **THEN** the \"Codespell\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n327: \n328: #### Scenario: Backup problematic files\n329: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n330: - **WHEN** job starts\n331: - **THEN** it SHALL backup and remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json` at repo root and nested copies\n332: \n333: #### Scenario: Install codespell\n334: - **GIVEN** files are backed up\n335: - **WHEN** dependency step runs\n336: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `pip install codespell`\n337: \n338: #### Scenario: Run codespell\n339: - **GIVEN** codespell is installed\n340: - **WHEN** spell check step runs\n341: - **THEN** it SHALL run `codespell --check-filenames --skip <globs> --ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn .`\n342: \n343: #### Scenario: Restore backed-up files\n344: - **GIVEN** codespell completes\n345: - **WHEN** cleanup step runs\n346: - **THEN** it SHALL restore all backed-up files\n347: \n348: #### Scenario: Spelling errors found\n349: - **GIVEN** repository contains misspellings\n350: - **WHEN** codespell runs\n351: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL fail with list of misspelled words\n352: \n353: ---\n354: \n355: ### REQ-034.10: Build and Push Release Images Workflow (build-push-release.yml)\n356: \n357: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that builds and pushes multi-architecture images for workloadmanager, router, and picod to GitHub Container Registry on pushes to `main` and semantic version tags.\n358: \n359: #### Scenario: Push to main triggers workflow\n360: - **GIVEN** a push to `main` branch occurs\n361: - **WHEN** the push event completes\n362: - **THEN** the \"Build and Push Release Images\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n363: \n364: #### Scenario: Tag push triggers workflow\n365: - **GIVEN** a push of tag matching `v*.*.*` or `v*.*.*-*` occurs\n366: - **WHEN** the tag event completes\n367: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL be triggered\n368: \n369: #### Scenario: Determine image tag from ref\n370: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n371: - **WHEN** `TAG` environment variable is evaluated\n372: - **THEN** it SHALL use `github.ref_name` if tag, otherwise `latest`\n373: \n374: #### Scenario: Setup Go for build\n375: - **GIVEN** workflow is triggered\n376: - **WHEN** job starts\n377: - **THEN** it SHALL set up Go version 1.24.4\n378: \n379: #### Scenario: Setup Docker Buildx\n380: - **GIVEN** Go is ready\n381: - **WHEN** job continues\n382: - **THEN** it SHALL set up Docker Buildx\n383: \n384: #### Scenario: Login to GHCR\n385: - **GIVEN** Buildx is ready\n386: - **WHEN** login step runs\n387: - **THEN** it SHALL authenticate to `ghcr.io` using `GITHUB_TOKEN`\n388: \n389: #### Scenario: Build and push workloadmanager\n390: - **GIVEN** registry login succeeds\n391: - **WHEN** build step runs\n392: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `make docker-buildx-push` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE=workloadmanager:${TAG}`\n393: \n394: #### Scenario: Build and push router\n395: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n396: - **WHEN** router build step runs\n397: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `make docker-buildx-push-router` with appropriate image variables\n398: \n399: #### Scenario: Build and push picod\n400: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n401: - **WHEN** picod build step runs\n402: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `make docker-buildx-push-picod` with appropriate image variables\n403: \n404: #### Scenario: Multi-architecture build\n405: - **GIVEN** buildx is available\n406: - **WHEN** build commands run\n407: - **THEN** images SHALL be built for `linux/amd64,linux/arm64` platforms\n408: \n409: ---\n410: \n411: ### REQ-034.11: Dify Plugin Publish Workflow (dify-plugin-publish.yml)\n412: \n413: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that publishes the Dify plugin to the `langgenius/dify-plugins` repository when `dify-plugin/v*` tags are pushed.\n414: \n415: #### Scenario: Dify plugin tag triggers workflow\n416: - **GIVEN** a push of tag matching `dify-plugin/v*` occurs\n417: - **WHEN** the tag event completes\n418: - **THEN** the \"Dify Plugin Publish\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n419: \n420: #### Scenario: Download dify-plugin CLI\n421: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n422: - **WHEN** setup step runs\n423: - **THEN** it SHALL download `dify-plugin` CLI version 0.0.6\n424: \n425: #### Scenario: Install yq processor\n426: - **GIVEN** workflow continues\n427: - **WHEN** tooling step runs\n428: - **THEN** it SHALL install `yq` YAML processor\n429: \n430: #### Scenario: Read manifest\n431: - **GIVEN** tools are ready\n432: - **WHEN** manifest step runs\n433: - **THEN** it SHALL read `manifest.yaml` for plugin metadata\n434: \n435: #### Scenario: Package plugin\n436: - **GIVEN** manifest is parsed\n437: - **WHEN** packaging step runs\n438: - **THEN** it SHALL package the Dify plugin\n439: \n440: #### Scenario: Checkout plugins repository\n441: - **GIVEN** plugin is packaged\n442: - **WHEN** repository step runs\n443: - **THEN** it SHALL checkout `author/dify-plugins` using token authentication\n444: \n445: #### Scenario: Move plugin to repository\n446: - **GIVEN** repository is checked out\n447: - **WHEN** file step runs\n448: - **THEN** it SHALL move `.difypkg` file to appropriate location\n449: \n450: #### Scenario: Create pull request\n451: - **GIVEN** plugin files are staged\n452: - **WHEN** PR step runs\n453: - **THEN** it SHALL create branch, commit, push, and create PR to `langgenius/dify-plugins` using `gh pr create` with `GH_TOKEN`\n454: \n455: ---\n456: \n457: ### REQ-034.12: Approve Workflows Workflow (workflows-approve.yml)\n458: \n459: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that optionally approves pending workflow runs for pull requests from repeat contributors or those labeled `ok-to-test`.\n460: \n461: #### Scenario: PR target triggers approval workflow\n462: - **GIVEN** a `pull_request_target` event with types `labeled` or `synchronize` targets `main` or `release-**`\n463: - **WHEN** the event occurs\n464: - **THEN** the \"Approve Workflows\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n465: \n466: #### Scenario: Check contributor PR history\n467: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n468: - **WHEN** github-script step runs\n469: - **THEN** it SHALL list contributor's PRs to determine if first-time\n470: \n471: #### Scenario: Check for ok-to-test label\n472: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n473: - **WHEN** label check runs\n474: - **THEN** it SHALL check if PR has `ok-to-test` label\n475: \n476: #### Scenario: Approve for repeat contributor\n477: - **GIVEN** contributor has more than one PR\n478: - **WHEN** approval logic runs\n479: - **THEN** it SHALL list workflow runs with `status: action_required` for the head SHA and approve each\n480: \n481: #### Scenario: Approve for labeled PR\n482: - **GIVEN** PR has `ok-to-test` label\n483: - **WHEN** approval logic runs\n484: - **THEN** it SHALL list workflow runs with `status: action_required` for the head SHA and approve each\n485: \n486: #### Scenario: Skip for first-time contributor\n487: - **GIVEN** contributor has only one PR and no `ok-to-test` label\n488: - **WHEN** approval logic runs\n489: - **THEN** no workflow runs SHALL be approved\n490: \n491: ---\n492: \n493: ## Data Types\n494: \n495: ```yaml\n496: # Workflow trigger types\n497: on:\n498:   pull_request:\n499:     branches: [main, release-*]\n500:   pull_request_target:\n501:     branches: [main, release-**]\n502:     types: [labeled, synchronize]\n503:   push:\n504:     branches: [main]\n505:     tags: ['v*.*.*', 'v*.*.*-*', 'dify-plugin/v*']\n506:   merge_group:\n507:   workflow_call:\n508: \n509: # Common job environment variables\n510: env:\n511:   TAG: ${{ github.ref_type == 'tag' && github.ref_name || 'latest' }}\n512:   IMAGE_REGISTRY: ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}\n513:   ARTIFACTS_PATH: ${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs\n514: ```\n515: \n516: ---\n517: \n518: ## File Structure\n519: \n520: ```\n521: .github/\n522: └── workflows/\n523:     ├── main.yml                      # Agentcube CI Workflow (REQ-034.1)\n524:     ├── e2e.yml                       # Agentcube E2E Tests (REQ-034.2)\n525:     ├── lint.yml                      # Lint (REQ-034.3)\n526:     ├── python-sdk-tests.yml          # Python SDK Tests (REQ-034.4)\n527:     ├── python-lint.yml               # Python Lint (REQ-034.5)\n528:     ├── test-coverage.yml             # Test Coverage (REQ-034.6)\n529:     ├── codegen-check.yml             # Codegen Check (REQ-034.7)\n530:     ├── copyright-check.yml           # Copyright Check (REQ-034.8)\n531:     ├── codespell.yml                 # Codespell (REQ-034.9)\n532:     ├── build-push-release.yml        # Build and Push Release Images (REQ-034.10)\n533:     ├── dify-plugin-publish.yml       # Dify Plugin Publish (REQ-034.11)\n534:     └── workflows-approve.yml         # Approve Workflows (REQ-034.12)\n535: ```\n536: \n537: ---\n538: \n539: ## Workflows Summary\n540: \n541: | Workflow | File | Triggers | Path Filters | Key Jobs |\n542: |----------|------|----------|--------------|----------|\n543: | Agentcube CI Workflow | main.yml | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | None | build |\n544: | Agentcube E2E Tests | e2e.yml | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | None | e2e-test |\n545: | Lint | lint.yml | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | Go files | golangci |\n546: | Python SDK Tests | python-sdk-tests.yml | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk-python/**` | python-sdk-tests |\n547: | Python Lint | python-lint.yml | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | Python files | python_lint |\n548: | Test Coverage | test-coverage.yml | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | All except media | coverage |\n549: | Codegen Check | codegen-check.yml | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | API/hack/workflow/Makefile | codegen-check |\n550: | Copyright Check | copyright-check.yml | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | Code files only | build |\n551: | Codespell | codespell.yml | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | None (tree scan) | codespell |\n552: | Build and Push Release | build-push-release.yml | `push` → `main`, tags `v*` | None | build-and-push |\n553: | Dify Plugin Publish | dify-plugin-publish.yml | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | None | publish |\n554: | Approve Workflows | workflows-approve.yml | `pull_request_target` → `main` | None | approve |\n555: \n556: ---\n557: \n558: ## Secrets and Credentials\n559: \n560: | Secret | Purpose | Used By |\n561: |--------|---------|---------|\n562: | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` | Codecov coverage upload | test-coverage.yml (optional) |\n563: | `secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN` | GHCR registry login, cross-repo PR | build-push-release.yml, dify-plugin-publish.yml, workflows-approve.yml |\n564: | `secrets.PLUGIN_ACTION` | Dify plugin repository checkout and PR | dify-plugin-publish.yml |\n565: \n566: ---\n567: \n568: ## Acceptance Checklist\n569: \n570: - [ ] `main.yml` — Triggers on PR to `main`/`release-*`, runs `make docker-build`\n571: - [ ] `e2e.yml` — Triggers on PR, sets up Kind v0.30.0, runs `make e2e`, uploads logs on failure, cleans up\n572: - [ ] `lint.yml` — Path-filtered for Go files, runs `make lint` with Go 1.24\n573: - [ ] `python-sdk-tests.yml` — Path-filtered for `sdk-python/**`, runs pytest with Python 3.12\n574: - [ ] `python-lint.yml` — Path-filtered for Python files, runs Ruff with Python 3.10\n575: - [ ] `test-coverage.yml` — Runs `go test -race` with coverage, uploads to Codecov\n576: - [ ] `codegen-check.yml` — Path-filtered, runs `make gen-check` with Go 1.24.4\n577: - [ ] `copyright-check.yml` — Installs moreutils, runs `make gen-copyright`, checks diff\n578: - [ ] `codespell.yml` — Backups files, runs codespell with ignore list, restores files\n579: - [ ] `build-push-release.yml` — Triggers on push to `main`/tags, builds multi-arch, pushes to GHCR\n580: - [ ] `dify-plugin-publish.yml` — Triggers on `dify-plugin/v*` tags, creates PR to `langgenius/dify-plugins`\n581: - [ ] `workflows-approve.yml` — Approves workflows for repeat contributors or `ok-to-test` labeled PRs\n582: - [ ] All workflows — Use appropriate Go/Python versions as specified\n583: - [ ] All workflows — Have correct path filters configured\n584: - [ ] All workflows — Handle skip conditions correctly when paths don't match\n585: - [ ] Secrets — CODECOV_TOKEN is optional in test-coverage.yml\n586: - [ ] Secrets — GITHUB_TOKEN used for GHCR login and cross-repo operations\n587: - [ ] E2E workflow — Uses Kind action with `install_only: true`\n588: - [ ] Release workflow — Correctly determines TAG from ref type\n589: \n590: ---\n591: \n592: ## Open Questions\n593: \n594: 1. Should Windows CI runners be added for cross-platform validation?\n595: 2. Should SLSA/SBOM generation be integrated into the release workflow?\n596: 3. Should Dependabot be configured alongside these workflows?\n597: 4. Should workflow concurrency limits be added to prevent queue buildup?\n598: 5. Should additional notification hooks (Slack, Discord) be added for release failures?\n\n(End of file - total 598 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 Workflows)\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `.github/workflows`  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** L  \n**Type:** GitHub Actions workflows for CI/CD automation (build, lint, test, e2e, codegen, copyright, codespell, release, approval)\n\n**Base Specs:** ci-cd/design.md, ci-cd/spec.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-034.1: Agentcube CI Workflow (main.yml)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that builds the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n\n#### Scenario: PR triggers workflow","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-034/spec/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775883254901,"end":1775883254928}}}}
