{"type":"text","timestamp":1775883260772,"sessionID":"ses_2851c7184ffeDepVkFukH2kBxM","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae4122e0015WQJDl1cFdy6nZ","messageID":"msg_d7ae3fcc3001EW3FAH0SaP805U","sessionID":"ses_2851c7184ffeDepVkFukH2kBxM","type":"text","text":"Now I have all the context needed to write the design.md for AR-034. Let me create the comprehensive technical design document.","time":{"start":1775883260770,"end":1775883260770}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883427339,"sessionID":"ses_2851c7184ffeDepVkFukH2kBxM","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae41363001Ep7T4g5fCk2PLU","messageID":"msg_d7ae3fcc3001EW3FAH0SaP805U","sessionID":"ses_2851c7184ffeDepVkFukH2kBxM","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_4210134070424f188151ca02","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-034/design/design.md","content":"# Design: AR-034 CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 Workflows)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for 12 GitHub Actions workflows that provide comprehensive CI/CD automation for the AgentCube project. The workflows cover build verification, linting, testing, security scanning, release automation, and community management.\n\n**Module:** `.github/workflows`  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** L\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Workflow Categories\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    CI/CD Workflow Architecture               │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n        ┌─────────────────────┼─────────────────────┐\n        │                     │                     │\n        ▼                     ▼                     ▼\n┌───────────────┐    ┌───────────────┐    ┌───────────────┐\n│   Validation  │    │    Release    │    │  Community    │\n│   Workflows   │    │   Workflows   │    │  Workflows    │\n└───────────────┘    └───────────────┘    └───────────────┘\n        │                     │                     │\n        ├─ main.yml           ├─ build-push-        ├─ workflows-\n        ├─ lint.yml           │  release.yml        │  approve.yml\n        ├─ e2e.yml            ├─ dify-plugin-       ├─ labeler.yml\n        ├─ python-*.yml       │  publish.yml        └─ stale.yml\n        ├─ test-coverage.yml  └─ release.yml\n        ├─ codegen-check.yml\n        ├─ copyright-check.yml\n        └─ codespell.yml\n```\n\n### Trigger Hierarchy\n\n```\nEvent Types:\n├── pull_request (PR validation)\n│   ├── main branch\n│   └── release-* branches\n├── push (release/deployment)\n│   ├── main branch\n│   └── tags (v*.*, dify-plugin/v*)\n├── pull_request_target (approval workflow)\n├── merge_group (queue validation)\n└── schedule (periodic tasks)\n    └── cron expressions\n```\n\n### Workflow Dependencies\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ Workflow Dependency Graph                                     │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\nmain.yml ──────────────────┐\n                           │\nlint.yml ──────────────────┤\n                           ├────► (validation gate for merges)\ntest-coverage.yml ─────────┤\n                           │\ne2e.yml ───────────────────┘\n\nbuild-push-release.yml ────► GHCR ────► Kubernetes clusters\n                                  │\nrelease.yml ──────────────────────┤\n                                  │\ndify-plugin-publish.yml ─────────► langgenius/dify-plugins\n\nworkflows-approve.yml ───────────► Enables pending runs\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Workflow Trigger Configuration\n\n```yaml\n# Common trigger patterns\non:\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [main, release-*]\n    types: [opened, synchronize, reopened, labeled]\n  \n  pull_request_target:\n    branches: [main, release-**]\n    types: [labeled, synchronize]\n  \n  push:\n    branches: [main]\n    tags: ['v*.*.*', 'v*.*.*-*', 'dify-plugin/v*']\n  \n  merge_group:\n    types: [checks_requested]\n  \n  workflow_call:\n    inputs:\n      # Optional inputs for reusable workflows\n  \n  schedule:\n    - cron: '0 0 * * *'  # Daily at midnight UTC\n  \n  workflow_dispatch:  # Manual trigger\n```\n\n### Job Environment Variables\n\n```yaml\n# Standard environment variables across workflows\nenv:\n  # Go version for build/test jobs\n  GO_VERSION: '1.24'\n  \n  # Python versions (varies by workflow)\n  PYTHON_VERSION_SDK: '3.12'  # SDK tests\n  PYTHON_VERSION_LINT: '3.10'  # Linting\n  PYTHON_VERSION_E2E: '3.11'  # E2E tests\n  \n  # Docker/registry configuration\n  IMAGE_REGISTRY: ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}\n  TAG: ${{ github.ref_type == 'tag' && github.ref_name || 'latest' }}\n  \n  # E2E test configuration\n  ARTIFACTS_PATH: ${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs\n  E2E_CLUSTER_NAME: agentcube-e2e\n```\n\n### Path Filter Definitions\n\n```yaml\n# Path filters for conditional job execution\nfilters:\n  lint:\n    - '**/*.go'\n    - 'go.mod'\n    - 'go.sum'\n    - '.golangci.yml'\n    - '.github/workflows/lint.yml'\n  \n  coverage:\n    - '**'\n    exclude:\n      - '*.md'\n      - '*.svg'\n      - '*.png'\n  \n  codegen:\n    - 'pkg/apis/**'\n    - 'hack/**'\n    - '.github/workflows/**'\n    - 'Makefile'\n  \n  copyright:\n    - '**'\n    exclude:\n      - '*.md'\n      - '*.svg'\n      - '*.png'\n      - 'docs/**'\n      - '.github/**'\n  \n  sdk:\n    - 'sdk-python/**'\n  \n  python:\n    - 'cmd/cli/**'\n    - 'sdk-python/**'\n    - 'example/**'\n    - 'test/**/*.py'\n    - 'pyproject.toml'\n    - '.github/workflows/python-lint.yml'\n```\n\n### Job Output Structures\n\n```yaml\n# Release workflow outputs\noutputs:\n  upload_url: ${{ steps.create_release.outputs.upload_url }}\n  version: ${{ steps.get_version.outputs.version }}\n  image_tags: ${{ steps.meta.outputs.tags }}\n\n# E2E workflow outputs\noutputs:\n  artifacts_path: ${{ env.ARTIFACTS_PATH }}\n  cluster_name: ${{ env.E2E_CLUSTER_NAME }}\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Workflow Inputs/Outputs\n\n#### test-coverage.yml (Reusable Workflow)\n\n```yaml\n# workflow_call interface\ninputs:\n  go_version:\n    description: 'Go version to use'\n    required: false\n    default: '1.24'\n    type: string\n  \n  upload_codecov:\n    description: 'Whether to upload to Codecov'\n    required: false\n    default: true\n    type: boolean\n\noutputs:\n  coverage_report:\n    description: 'Path to coverage report'\n    value: ${{ jobs.coverage.outputs.coverage_path }}\n\nsecrets:\n  CODECOV_TOKEN:\n    required: false\n    description: 'Codecov upload token (optional for PRs)'\n```\n\n#### build-push-release.yml (Image Build Contract)\n\n```yaml\n# Expected Make targets\nmake_targets:\n  - docker-buildx-push          # Workload Manager\n  - docker-buildx-push-router   # Router\n  - docker-buildx-push-picod    # PicoD\n\n# Environment variables required\nenv:\n  IMAGE_REGISTRY: ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}\n  WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE: workloadmanager:${{ env.TAG }}\n  ROUTER_IMAGE: router:${{ env.TAG }}\n  PICOD_IMAGE: picod:${{ env.TAG }}\n```\n\n### Job Permission Contracts\n\n```yaml\n# Minimum permissions per workflow type\npermissions:\n  # Validation workflows (read-only)\n  contents: read\n  \n  # Release workflows (write packages)\n  contents: write\n  packages: write\n  id-token: write  # For OIDC authentication\n  \n  # PR management workflows\n  pull-requests: write\n  contents: read\n  \n  # Security scanning\n  security-events: write\n  actions: read\n```\n\n### Secret References\n\n```yaml\n# Required secrets by workflow\nsecrets:\n  # build-push-release.yml\n  GITHUB_TOKEN:  # Automatic, for GHCR login\n  \n  # dify-plugin-publish.yml\n  GITHUB_TOKEN:  # Cross-repo PR creation\n  PLUGIN_ACTION:  # Repository checkout token\n  \n  # release.yml (if implemented)\n  PYPI_API_TOKEN:  # Python package publishing\n  \n  # test-coverage.yml (optional)\n  CODECOV_TOKEN:  # Codecov upload\n```\n\n---\n\n## Workflow Implementations\n\n### 1. main.yml — Agentcube CI Workflow\n\n**Purpose:** Build Workload Manager Docker image on PRs\n\n```yaml\nname: Agentcube CI Workflow\n\non:\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [main, release-*]\n\njobs:\n  build:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      \n      - uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@v3\n      \n      - name: Verify Docker\n        run: |\n          docker --version\n          docker buildx version\n      \n      - name: Build Workload Manager\n        run: make docker-build\n```\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n- Uses Docker Buildx for future multi-arch support\n- Build verification only (no push)\n- No path filters — runs on all PR changes\n\n---\n\n### 2. e2e.yml — Agentcube E2E Tests\n\n**Purpose:** Run end-to-end tests on Kind cluster\n\n```yaml\nname: Agentcube E2E Tests\n\non:\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [main, release-*]\n\njobs:\n  e2e-test:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    env:\n      ARTIFACTS_PATH: ${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs\n    \n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      \n      - uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n        with:\n          go-version: '1.23'\n      \n      - uses: helm/kind-action@v1\n        with:\n          version: v0.30.0\n          install_only: true\n          cluster_name: agentcube-e2e\n      \n      - name: Run E2E Tests\n        run: make e2e\n      \n      - name: Upload Failure Logs\n        if: failure()\n        uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4\n        with:\n          name: e2e-logs\n          path: ${{ env.ARTIFACTS_PATH }}/\n      \n      - name: Clean Up\n        if: always()\n        run: make e2e-clean\n```\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n- Kind action uses `install_only: true` (cluster created by `run_e2e.sh`)\n- Go 1.23 (not 1.24) for E2E tests\n- Log collection on failure only\n- Always runs cleanup to avoid resource leaks\n\n---\n\n### 3. lint.yml — Go Linting\n\n**Purpose:** Run golangci-lint on Go code changes\n\n```yaml\nname: Lint\n\non:\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [main, release-*]\n\njobs:\n  golangci:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    \n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      \n      - uses: dorny/paths-filter@v3\n        id: filter\n        with:\n          filters: |\n            lint:\n              - '**/*.go'\n              - 'go.mod'\n              - 'go.sum'\n              - '.golangci.yml'\n              - '.github/workflows/lint.yml'\n      \n      - uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n        if: steps.filter.outputs.lint == 'true'\n        with:\n          go-version: '1.24'\n      \n      - name: Run golangci-lint\n        if: steps.filter.outputs.lint == 'true'\n        run: make lint\n```\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n- Path-filtered to avoid unnecessary runs\n- Go 1.24 for latest linting rules\n- Skipped if no Go-related changes\n\n---\n\n### 4. python-sdk-tests.yml — Python SDK Tests\n\n**Purpose:** Run pytest for Python SDK changes\n\n```yaml\nname: Python SDK Tests\n\non:\n  pull_request:\n  merge_group:\n\njobs:\n  python-sdk-tests:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    \n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      \n      - uses: dorny/paths-filter@v3\n        id: filter\n        with:\n          filters: |\n            sdk:\n              - 'sdk-python/**'\n      \n      - uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n        if: steps.filter.outputs.sdk == 'true'\n        with:\n          python-version: '3.12'\n          cache: 'pip'\n          cache-dependency-path: sdk-python/requirements.txt\n      \n      - name: Install Dependencies\n        if: steps.filter.outputs.sdk == 'true'\n        working-directory: sdk-python\n        run: |\n          pip install pytest\n          pip install -e .\n      \n      - name: Run Tests\n        if: steps.filter.outputs.sdk == 'true'\n        working-directory: sdk-python\n        run: python -m pytest tests/ -v\n```\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n- Triggers on `merge_group` for merge queue support\n- Python 3.12 with pip caching\n- Editable install for accurate testing\n- Working directory set to `sdk-python`\n\n---\n\n### 5. python-lint.yml — Python Linting\n\n**Purpose:** Run Ruff on Python code changes\n\n```yaml\nname: Python Lint\n\non:\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [main, release-*]\n\njobs:\n  python_lint:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    \n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      \n      - uses: dorny/paths-filter@v3\n        id: filter\n        with:\n          filters: |\n            python:\n              - 'cmd/cli/**'\n              - 'sdk-python/**'\n              - 'example/**'\n              - 'test/**/*.py'\n              - 'pyproject.toml'\n              - '.github/workflows/python-lint.yml'\n      \n      - uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n        if: steps.filter.outputs.python == 'true'\n        with:\n          python-version: '3.10'\n      \n      - name: Install Ruff\n        if: steps.filter.outputs.python == 'true'\n        run: pip install ruff\n      \n      - name: Run Ruff\n        if: steps.filter.outputs.python == 'true'\n        run: python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml\n```\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n- Python 3.10 (older version for compatibility)\n- Runs from repository root with `pyproject.toml` config\n- Comprehensive path filters for all Python code\n\n---\n\n### 6. test-coverage.yml — Go Test Coverage\n\n**Purpose:** Run race-enabled tests with coverage reporting\n\n```yaml\nname: Test Coverage\n\non:\n  pull_request:\n  merge_group:\n  workflow_call:\n    inputs:\n      go_version:\n        type: string\n        default: '1.24'\n    secrets:\n      CODECOV_TOKEN:\n        required: false\n\njobs:\n  coverage:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    outputs:\n      coverage_path: coverage.out\n    \n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      \n      - uses: dorny/paths-filter@v3\n        id: filter\n        with:\n          filters: |\n            coverage:\n              - '**'\n              exclude:\n                - '*.md'\n                - '*.svg'\n                - '*.png'\n      \n      - name: Free Disk Space\n        if: steps.filter.outputs.coverage == 'true'\n        run: |\n          sudo rm -rf /usr/share/dotnet\n          sudo rm -rf /opt/ghc\n          sudo rm -rf \"/usr/local/share/boost\"\n      \n      - uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n        if: steps.filter.outputs.coverage == 'true'\n        with:\n          go-version: '1.24'\n      \n      - name: Run Tests with Coverage\n        if: steps.filter.outputs.coverage == 'true'\n        run: |\n          go test -race -v \\\n            -coverprofile=coverage.out \\\n            -coverpkg=./pkg/... \\\n            ./pkg/...\n      \n      - name: Upload to Codecov\n        if: steps.filter.outputs.coverage == 'true'\n        uses: codecov/codecov-action@v4\n        with:\n          file: ./coverage.out\n          token: ${{ secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN }}\n          fail_ci_if_error: false\n      \n      - name: Upload Coverage Artifact\n        if: steps.filter.outputs.coverage == 'true'\n        uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4\n        with:\n          name: go-coverage\n          path: coverage.out\n      \n      - name: Write Summary\n        if: always()\n        run: |\n          echo \"## Coverage Report\" >> $GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY\n          go tool cover -func=coverage.out >> $GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY\n```\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n- Supports `workflow_call` for reusable usage\n- Optional `CODECOV_TOKEN` secret\n- Free disk space for large runners\n- Race detection enabled\n- Coverage limited to `pkg/...`\n\n---\n\n### 7. codegen-check.yml — Code Generation Check\n\n**Purpose:** Verify generated code is up-to-date\n\n```yaml\nname: Codegen Check\n\non:\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [main, release-*]\n\njobs:\n  codegen-check:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    \n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      \n      - uses: dorny/paths-filter@v3\n        id: filter\n        with:\n          filters: |\n            codegen:\n              - 'pkg/apis/**'\n              - 'hack/**'\n              - '.github/workflows/**'\n              - 'Makefile'\n      \n      - uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n        if: steps.filter.outputs.codegen == 'true'\n        with:\n          go-version: '1.24.4'\n      \n      - name: Run gen-check\n        if: steps.filter.outputs.codegen == 'true'\n        run: make gen-check\n```\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n- Go 1.24.4 (specific patch version for codegen tools)\n- Runs `make gen-check` which:\n  1. Executes `make gen-all`\n  2. Runs `git diff --exit-code`\n- Path-filtered for API/hack/workflow changes\n\n---\n\n### 8. copyright-check.yml — Copyright Header Check\n\n**Purpose:** Ensure all files have proper copyright headers\n\n```yaml\nname: Copyright Check\n\non:\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [main, release-*]\n\njobs:\n  build:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    \n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      \n      - uses: dorny/paths-filter@v3\n        id: filter\n        with:\n          filters: |\n            copyright:\n              - '**'\n              exclude:\n                - '*.md'\n                - '*.svg'\n                - '*.png'\n                - 'docs/**'\n                - '.github/**'\n      \n      - name: Install moreutils\n        if: steps.filter.outputs.copyright == 'true'\n        run: sudo apt-get install -y moreutils\n      \n      - name: Generate Copyright Headers\n        if: steps.filter.outputs.copyright == 'true'\n        run: make gen-copyright\n      \n      - name: Verify No Changes\n        if: steps.filter.outputs.copyright == 'true'\n        run: git diff --exit-code\n```\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n- Uses `moreutils` package for `sponge` command\n- Excludes documentation and workflow files\n- Fails if `git diff` shows changes (missing headers)\n\n---\n\n### 9. codespell.yml — Spelling Check\n\n**Purpose:** Detect typos and misspellings\n\n```yaml\nname: Codespell\n\non:\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [main, release-*]\n\njobs:\n  codespell:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    \n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      \n      - name: Backup Problematic Files\n        run: |\n          # Backup and remove files that cause false positives\n          for file in pyproject.toml package.json package-lock.json; do\n            if [ -f \"$file\" ]; then\n              cp \"$file\" \"$file.bak\"\n              rm \"$file\"\n            fi\n          done\n          \n          # Remove nested copies\n          find . -name pyproject.toml -not -path \"./pyproject.toml\" -delete\n          find . -name package.json -not -path \"./package.json\" -delete\n          find . -name package-lock.json -not -path \"./package-lock.json\" -delete\n      \n      - name: Install Codespell\n        run: pip install codespell\n      \n      - name: Run Codespell\n        run: |\n          codespell \\\n            --check-filenames \\\n            --skip \"*.min.js,*.min.css,node_modules,vendor\" \\\n            --ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn \\\n            .\n      \n      - name: Restore Files\n        if: always()\n        run: |\n          for file in pyproject.toml package.json package-lock.json; do\n            if [ -f \"$file.bak\" ]; then\n              mv \"$file.bak\" \"$file\"\n            fi\n          done\n```\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n- Backs up and removes problematic config files\n- Custom ignore list for common false positives\n- Restores files even on failure\n\n---\n\n### 10. build-push-release.yml — Build and Push Release Images\n\n**Purpose:** Build multi-arch images and push to GHCR\n\n```yaml\nname: Build and Push Release Images\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [main]\n  push:\n    tags:\n      - 'v*.*.*'\n      - 'v*.*.*-*'\n\nenv:\n  TAG: ${{ github.ref_type == 'tag' && github.ref_name || 'latest' }}\n  IMAGE_REGISTRY: ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}\n\njobs:\n  build-and-push:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    \n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      \n      - uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n        with:\n          go-version: '1.24.4'\n      \n      - uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@v2\n      \n      - name: Login to GHCR\n        uses: docker/login-action@v3\n        with:\n          registry: ghcr.io\n          username: ${{ github.actor }}\n          password: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n      \n      - name: Build and Push Workload Manager\n        run: make docker-buildx-push\n        env:\n          WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE: workloadmanager:${{ env.TAG }}\n      \n      - name: Build and Push Router\n        run: make docker-buildx-push-router\n        env:\n          ROUTER_IMAGE: router:${{ env.TAG }}\n      \n      - name: Build and Push PicoD\n        run: make docker-buildx-push-picod\n        env:\n          PICOD_IMAGE: picod:${{ env.TAG }}\n```\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n- Uses older action versions (checkout@v3, setup-go@v4, buildx@v2)\n- TAG determination: semver tag → tag name, else `latest`\n- Pushes to `ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}`\n- Multi-architecture builds via Buildx\n\n---\n\n### 11. dify-plugin-publish.yml — Dify Plugin Publish\n\n**Purpose:** Publish plugin to langgenius/dify-plugins repository\n\n```yaml\nname: Dify Plugin Publish\n\non:\n  push:\n    tags:\n      - 'dify-plugin/v*'\n\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    \n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      \n      - name: Download dify-plugin CLI\n        uses: robinraju/release-downloader@v1\n        with:\n          repository: langgenius/dify-plugins\n          fileName: dify-plugin\n          tag: 'v0.0.6'\n      \n      - name: Install yq\n        uses: mikefarah/yq@master\n      \n      - name: Read Manifest\n        id: manifest\n        run: |\n          VERSION=$(yq -r '.version' manifest.yaml)\n          echo \"version=$VERSION\" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT\n      \n      - name: Package Plugin\n        run: dify-plugin package\n      \n      - name: Checkout Plugins Repository\n        uses: actions/checkout@v4\n        with:\n          repository: author/dify-plugins\n          token: ${{ secrets.PLUGIN_ACTION }}\n          path: plugins-repo\n      \n      - name: Move Plugin\n        run: mv *.difypkg plugins-repo/plugins/\n      \n      - name: Create Pull Request\n        uses: peter-evans/create-pull-request@v6\n        with:\n          token: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n          path: plugins-repo\n          commit-message: 'Add plugin ${{ steps.manifest.outputs.version }}'\n          branch: plugin-${{ steps.manifest.outputs.version }}\n          title: 'Add plugin ${{ steps.manifest.outputs.version }}'\n          body: |\n            Automated PR from dify-plugin-publish workflow\n          labels: plugin\n```\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n- Triggers on `dify-plugin/v*` tags\n- Downloads dify-plugin CLI v0.0.6\n- Cross-repo PR creation with token\n- Uses yq for YAML parsing\n\n---\n\n### 12. workflows-approve.yml — Approve Workflows\n\n**Purpose:** Auto-approve workflows for repeat contributors\n\n```yaml\nname: Approve Workflows\n\non:\n  pull_request_target:\n    types: [labeled, synchronize]\n    branches:\n      - main\n      - 'release-**'\n\njobs:\n  approve:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    \n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/github-script@v7\n        with:\n          script: |\n            const { owner, repo } = context.repo;\n            const pr = context.payload.pull_request;\n            const contributor = pr.user.login;\n            \n            // Check if first-time contributor\n            const prs = await github.rest.issues.listForRepo({\n              owner,\n              repo,\n              creator: contributor,\n              state: 'all'\n            });\n            \n            const isFirstTime = prs.data.length === 1;\n            const hasOkToTest = pr.labels.some(l => l.name === 'ok-to-test');\n            \n            if (!isFirstTime || hasOkToTest) {\n              // Approve pending workflow runs\n              const runs = await github.rest.actions.listWorkflowRunsForRepo({\n                owner,\n                repo,\n                event: 'pull_request',\n                status: 'action_required',\n                head_sha: pr.head.sha\n              });\n              \n              for (const run of runs.data.workflow_runs) {\n                await github.rest.actions.approveWorkflowRun({\n                  owner,\n                  repo,\n                  workflow_run_id: run.id\n                });\n                core.info(`Approved workflow run ${run.id}`);\n              }\n            } else {\n              core.info('First-time contributor, skipping approval');\n            }\n```\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n- Uses `pull_request_target` for elevated permissions\n- Checks PR count to determine first-time status\n- Respects `ok-to-test` label override\n- Approves only runs with `action_required` status\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Workflow Failure Modes\n\n| Error Type | Detection | Response |\n|------------|-----------|----------|\n| Job failure | `if: failure()` | Upload artifacts, collect logs |\n| Timeout | `timeout-minutes` | Auto-cancel with error |\n| Resource exhaustion | Runner error | Retry on different runner |\n| Secret missing | Action error | Immediate failure |\n| Permission denied | API error | Check token scopes |\n\n### Artifact Collection on Failure\n\n```yaml\n- name: Collect Component Logs\n  if: failure()\n  run: |\n    mkdir -p ${{ env.ARTIFACTS_PATH }}\n    kubectl get pods -A > ${{ env.ARTIFACTS_PATH }}/pods.txt\n    kubectl logs -l app=workloadmanager > ${{ env.ARTIFACTS_PATH }}/workloadmanager.log\n    kubectl logs -l app=router > ${{ env.ARTIFACTS_PATH }}/router.log\n    kubectl describe pods -l app=workloadmanager > ${{ env.ARTIFACTS_PATH }}/describe.txt\n\n- name: Upload Failure Artifacts\n  if: failure()\n  uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4\n  with:\n    name: e2e-logs\n    path: ${{ env.ARTIFACTS_PATH }}/\n```\n\n### Retry Strategies\n\n```yaml\n# Built-in retry for flaky actions\n- uses: actions/checkout@v4\n  with:\n    retry-after: 30\n    max-attempts: 3\n\n# Manual retry for commands\n- name: Flaky Command\n  uses: nick-fields/retry@v2\n  with:\n    timeout_minutes: 10\n    max_attempts: 3\n    command: make e2e\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Workflow Validation\n\n```bash\n# Syntax validation\nnpm install -g @action-validator/cli\naction-validator .github/workflows/*.yml\n\n# Lint workflows\nactionlint .github/workflows/*.yml\n\n# Local execution testing\nact -l  # List workflows\nact pull_request -j build  # Run specific job\n```\n\n### Test Scenarios\n\n| Workflow | Test Case | Verification |\n|----------|-----------|--------------|\n| main.yml | PR to main | Docker build succeeds |\n| e2e.yml | Kind cluster | E2E tests pass |\n| lint.yml | Go changes | golangci-lint runs |\n| lint.yml | No Go changes | Job skipped |\n| python-sdk-tests.yml | SDK changes | pytest runs |\n| test-coverage.yml | Coverage threshold | Codecov upload |\n| codegen-check.yml | Stale generated code | Fails with diff |\n| copyright-check.yml | Missing headers | Fails with diff |\n| codespell.yml | Typos present | Fails with list |\n| build-push-release.yml | Tag push | Images pushed to GHCR |\n| dify-plugin-publish.yml | Plugin tag | PR created |\n| workflows-approve.yml | First-time vs repeat | Approval logic |\n\n### Integration Test Matrix\n\n```yaml\n# Test matrix for comprehensive coverage\ntest_matrix:\n  branches: [main, release-1.0, release-2.0]\n  event_types: [pull_request, push, merge_group]\n  path_changes:\n    - go_code: ['pkg/main.go']\n    - python_code: ['sdk-python/main.py']\n    - dockerfiles: ['Dockerfile.workloadmanager']\n    - workflows: ['.github/workflows/main.yml']\n    - mixed: ['pkg/main.go', 'sdk-python/main.py']\n```\n\n### Performance Benchmarks\n\n| Metric | Target | Measurement |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| CI workflow duration | < 10 min | GitHub Actions logs |\n| E2E test duration | < 20 min | Workflow run time |\n| Cache hit rate | > 80% | Cache action output |\n| Parallel job efficiency | > 90% | Concurrent execution |\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\n.github/\n├── workflows/\n│   ├── main.yml                      # Agentcube CI Workflow\n│   ├── e2e.yml                       # Agentcube E2E Tests\n│   ├── lint.yml                      # Go Linting\n│   ├── python-sdk-tests.yml          # Python SDK Tests\n│   ├── python-lint.yml               # Python Linting\n│   ├── test-coverage.yml             # Go Test Coverage\n│   ├── codegen-check.yml             # Code Generation Check\n│   ├── copyright-check.yml           # Copyright Header Check\n│   ├── codespell.yml                 # Spelling Check\n│   ├── build-push-release.yml        # Build and Push Release Images\n│   ├── dify-plugin-publish.yml       # Dify Plugin Publish\n│   └── workflows-approve.yml         # Workflow Approval\n├── dependabot.yml                    # (Optional) Dependency updates\n├── labeler.yml                       # (Optional) Auto-labeling rules\n└── CODEOWNERS                        # (Optional) Code owners\n```\n\n---\n\n## Environment Configuration\n\n### Required Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Scope | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|-------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `GO_VERSION` | Workflow | No | `1.24` | Default Go version |\n| `PYTHON_VERSION` | Job | No | Varies | Python version per job |\n| `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | Workflow | Yes | — | Container registry URL |\n| `TAG` | Workflow | Yes | `latest` | Image tag |\n| `ARTIFACTS_PATH` | Job | No | — | E2E logs path |\n| `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` | Job | No | `agentcube-e2e` | Kind cluster name |\n\n### Required Secrets\n\n| Secret | Workflow | Purpose | Required |\n|--------|----------|---------|----------|\n| `GITHUB_TOKEN` | All | Automatic GitHub authentication | Yes (auto) |\n| `CODECOV_TOKEN` | test-coverage.yml | Codecov upload | No |\n| `PLUGIN_ACTION` | dify-plugin-publish.yml | Cross-repo access | Yes |\n| `PYPI_API_TOKEN` | release.yml (future) | PyPI publishing | Yes |\n\n### Optional Configuration\n\n```yaml\n# .github/dependabot.yml (recommended)\nversion: 2\nupdates:\n  - package-ecosystem: github-actions\n    directory: /\n    schedule:\n      interval: weekly\n  \n  - package-ecosystem: gomod\n    directory: /\n    schedule:\n      interval: weekly\n  \n  - package-ecosystem: pip\n    directory: /sdk-python\n    schedule:\n      interval: weekly\n```\n\n---\n\n## Performance Optimizations\n\n### Caching Strategy\n\n```yaml\n# Go module cache\n- uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n  with:\n    go-version: '1.24'\n    cache: true\n\n# Docker layer cache\n- uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@v3\n  with:\n    cache-from: type=gha\n    cache-to: type=gha,mode=max\n\n# Pip cache\n- uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n  with:\n    python-version: '3.12'\n    cache: 'pip'\n    cache-dependency-path: '**/requirements.txt'\n```\n\n### Parallel Job Execution\n\n```yaml\n# Jobs run in parallel when no dependencies\njobs:\n  lint:\n    # Independent\n  test:\n    # Independent\n  build:\n    # Independent\n  e2e:\n    needs: [build]  # Sequential dependency\n```\n\n### Resource Management\n\n```yaml\n# Free disk space for large builds\n- name: Free Disk Space\n  run: |\n    sudo rm -rf /usr/share/dotnet\n    sudo rm -rf /opt/ghc\n    sudo rm -rf \"/usr/local/share/boost\"\n\n# Use larger runners for heavy jobs\njobs:\n  e2e-test:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest-8-cores  # If available\n```\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Principle of Least Privilege\n\n```yaml\n# Minimal permissions per workflow\npermissions:\n  contents: read  # Default for validation workflows\n  \n  # Elevated only when needed\n  packages: write  # For image push\n  pull-requests: write  # For PR management\n  security-events: write  # For security scans\n```\n\n### Secret Management\n\n```yaml\n# Never echo secrets\n- name: Use Secret\n  env:\n    TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n  run: |\n    # Correct: secret used internally\n    curl -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" ...\n    \n    # WRONG: Never echo secrets\n    # echo $TOKEN\n\n# Use OIDC for cloud providers (if applicable)\n- uses: aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials@v4\n  with:\n    role-to-assume: arn:aws:iam::123456789:role/github-actions\n    aws-region: us-east-1\n```\n\n### Dependency Pinning\n\n```yaml\n# Pin action versions to specific SHA or version\n- uses: actions/checkout@v4  # Good\n- uses: actions/checkout@a5ac7e51b41094c92402da3b24376905380afc29  # Better\n\n# Avoid using @main or @master\n- uses: some/action@main  # BAD\n```\n\n---\n\n## Monitoring and Observability\n\n### Workflow Status Tracking\n\n```yaml\n# Add status badge to README\n# [![CI](https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/actions/workflows/main.yml/badge.svg)](...)\n\n# Use workflow run summaries\n- name: Write Summary\n  run: |\n    echo \"## Test Results\" >> $GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY\n    echo \"- Passed: $PASSED\" >> $GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY\n    echo \"- Failed: $FAILED\" >> $GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY\n```\n\n### Artifact Retention\n\n```yaml\n- uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4\n  with:\n    name: e2e-logs\n    path: ${{ env.ARTIFACTS_PATH }}/\n    retention-days: 30  # Keep for 30 days\n```\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `main.yml` — Triggers on PR to `main`/`release-*`, runs `make docker-build`\n- [ ] `e2e.yml` — Triggers on PR, sets up Kind v0.30.0, runs `make e2e`, uploads logs on failure, cleans up\n- [ ] `lint.yml` — Path-filtered for Go files, runs `make lint` with Go 1.24\n- [ ] `python-sdk-tests.yml` — Path-filtered for `sdk-python/**`, runs pytest with Python 3.12\n- [ ] `python-lint.yml` — Path-filtered for Python files, runs Ruff with Python 3.10\n- [ ] `test-coverage.yml` — Runs `go test -race` with coverage, uploads to Codecov\n- [ ] `codegen-check.yml` — Path-filtered, runs `make gen-check` with Go 1.24.4\n- [ ] `copyright-check.yml` — Installs moreutils, runs `make gen-copyright`, checks diff\n- [ ] `codespell.yml` — Backups files, runs codespell with ignore list, restores files\n- [ ] `build-push-release.yml` — Triggers on push to `main`/tags, builds multi-arch, pushes to GHCR\n- [ ] `dify-plugin-publish.yml` — Triggers on `dify-plugin/v*` tags, creates PR to `langgenius/dify-plugins`\n- [ ] `workflows-approve.yml` — Approves workflows for repeat contributors or `ok-to-test` labeled PRs\n- [ ] All workflows — Use appropriate Go/Python versions as specified\n- [ ] All workflows — Have correct path filters configured\n- [ ] All workflows — Handle skip conditions correctly when paths don't match\n- [ ] Secrets — CODECOV_TOKEN is optional in test-coverage.yml\n- [ ] Secrets — GITHUB_TOKEN used for GHCR login and cross-repo operations\n- [ ] E2E workflow — Uses Kind action with `install_only: true`\n- [ ] Release workflow — Correctly determines TAG from ref type\n- [ ] All YAML files pass `actionlint` validation\n- [ ] All workflows respect minimum permission requirements\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. **Windows CI runners** — Should we add Windows runners for cross-platform validation?\n2. **SLSA/SBOM generation** — Should release workflow generate software bill of materials?\n3. **Dependabot configuration** — Should we add `.github/dependabot.yml` for automated dependency updates?\n4. **Concurrency limits** — Should we add concurrency groups to prevent queue buildup?\n5. **Notification hooks** — Should we add Slack/Discord notifications for release failures?\n6. **Self-hosted runners** — Should we deploy self-hosted runners for cost reduction and faster builds?\n7. **Performance benchmarks** — Should we add automated performance regression testing?\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- `changes/AR-034/spec/delta-spec.md` — AR-034 Specification\n- `changes/AR-034/proposal.md` — AR-034 Proposal\n- `ci-cd/spec.md` — CI/CD Base Specification\n- `ci-cd/design.md` — CI/CD Design (existing reference)\n- GitHub Actions Documentation: https://docs.github.com/en/actions\n- paths-filter Action: https://github.com/dorny/paths-filter\n- Kind Action: https://github.com/helm/kind-action\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-034/design/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-034/design/design.md","time":{"start":1775883427323,"end":1775883427335}}}}
